Item_Response: The Robot I built wasn't supposed to come to life. It just, well... happened. This story of how the Bobot became to be my best creation... or nightmare... I had been working on a powerful Bobot project. I was in charge of the programming of Bobot. However, my little mistake cost a lot of trouble... AND I mean a lot of trouble.             It was the year of  5-12-1989, Cancun, Mexico. I was excited because to day was Bobot's reveal to the public. Unfortunately, I had forgottten to insert the no-evil programming inside of him ! The lack of that programming was going to cause him to go on an evil outrage! So when the power was turned on, Bobot's uproar began! His hammering arms slammed into the ground killing thousands. Even worse, he released an inferno out of his flamethrowers as well, incinerating everything in the process. My colleagues glared at me because I was the one who forgot include the no-evil programming. I chuckled sheepishly. To stop Bobot's thrash, I needed the selfdestruct remote. I raced to the Lab to get it. I pressed the huge, red, button and flares of oil and fire exploded as Bobot was destroyed...             The good news was that Bobot's rampage came to a halt. The bad news was: We had lost Bobot, thousands of people perished, and their was a lot of destruction me and my colleagues had to pay for. I groaned. This was going to take a lifetime's work to pay off the mess Bobot caused...

Item_Response: Once a long time ago a very magical thing happened. This magical thing happened on Christmas eve- christmas morning.       Once Joes parents put him to sleep they decided to get him a present for Christmas. They decided he was old enough to take care of him self on his own while they bought him a present so they wrote a note and left.Joe was sleeping happily in his bed dreaming about a toy robot he wanted. All of a sudden a loud crashing soud a though something bad happened. he called for r his parents but there was no reply so he got out of bed to check what happened.He saw his parents note and began to became scared. if his parent hadn't made that crash noise who did! Out of no where a robotic voice said greetings.Joe jumped in surprisment for 2c( the robot joe wanted) was life size standing in Joes kitchen.The robot briefly told Joe how he got there and then he told Joe why he had come.he told joe that he had only come here because freum( the land Joe was from) was under attack by space monsters.The robot then told Joe that if he did not come to help get rid of the space monsters he would have to become replaced with another person and Joe would be locked up.Joe decided that either way he went their would be trouble he decided to help 2c.2c started the space ship that was parked on Joe lawn and they began lift off.On the ride Joe asked 2c why out of all the people in the world choose me. 2c had a simple reply of you will find out later.       when Joe and 2c reached Freum Joe was crowded from aliens and robots who wanted to see what a person looked like.A couple minutes later Joe meet his trainer. Joes trainers name was 3b. once they got to know each other they became good friends. When Joe started training it was harder than he thought it would be. he kept getting knocker over,bruised and hit with the training weapons. After months of training Joe became a fierce warrior and was finally ready to fight the space monsters.Right before battle Joe remembered his home and his parent and he missed them.He didn't want to go and fight right now he wanted to tell his parent that he would be safe.Joe asked 3b if he would ever be able to see his parents again and 3b exclaimed 'of course man ,as long as you live through this war!'Joe suddenly became very afraid but when the fighting started he was just dogging weapons and running not using any of the training he learned from 3b.When hoe thought he was on a safe cabin he saw 3b fall from the sky dead.he suddenly felt rage and began attacking all the space monsters.when the war finally died down Joe was tired and wanted to go home and sleep. 2c took Joe home at around 12 and joe saw that no one was home.he decided to leave a note and go to bed.When Joe woke up his parents were waiting for him down stairs.He was fluttered by presents but his parents didn't seem to miss him. he told them that he was sorry about being away for months and they simply said ' Joe it Christmas morning' 'we only went to the store to buy you some presents.'Joe thought it was just a dream and he happily opened his presents.when he finally got to the last present it said from: 2c to: Joe when Joe saw what was on the inside he almost fainted it was a real mini robot that worked. it walked,and talked, and he ever could open and close his hands.Joe kept that present in a safe spot and kept it fro the rest of his life.       the end

Item_Response: 'Robots robots robots,' Grover shouts 'If you don't think robots are real then you better think again.' That was what was going on back when I was a robot that came to life. Everybody was making movies about them but know one noticed how real they were. My name is Grover and I am a robot. I don't do what you think I might do, I work with technology and yes that is me I create the graphics of your video games. You may not think but robots have a big roll in technology. To start us off I can talk, steer, create things, fix things and help people with things like viruses on their computers. If you did not know we only work when people believe in us.       Here in the studios of technology where I work we give people tours and when little kids come saying robots are not real i can't do my job until we make them say 'Robots are real!' Of course all we need to say is that I edit video games and there already loving me! Now I'll talk about my job. My body stores tools that I need for my job. When people call us on the phone saying 'My computer is having a virus' I can fix it. I am only 6 inches and I plug into the computer and collect information about why the computer is having a virus, all the ads that are popping up and more.       To create video games I get plugged into the computer as well and I have all of the cool editing tools. My buddy Jeremy (an actual human) created me and that is when I came to life. So Jeremy makes the designs but he can't do it without the help of me! What ever you can think of, any video game, that you can possibly think of, the graphics were done by me and Jeremy and thought of by Steve. Steve helped to create me but mostly Jeremy.       If you are interested how I came to life it was when Jeremy got tired of having to do all of this work. He went home one night and thought he could make a robot. 'Oh I have the best idea, I can't wait!' Jeremy shouted excitedly.   It took about 4 or 5 years to make me but he knew he could do it. He believed in himself. Jeremy got upset about me that it was taking so long until one day he finally tried me out and I worked. 'YES I got it, Finally i Can't wait!' He yelled. Jeremy was so excited to use me.       So now I am alive and I am working hard. People are very interested in me and I know I have to I have to keep up my work. Some kids think I am cool and others are scared of me. That is okay because not everybody is going to like me. I love working with Jeremy to make new video games for all of the kids that love video games. Next time you go to the Lego store make sure to check out my 3D Video sensor screen!

Item_Response: Mr. Gower                 One perfect day in Boston, Massachusetts a 21 year old-boy named Marcus got a new toy called Mr. Gower. He brought it back to his house and was playing with it in his room. He had to leave for a few weeks so he said bye to Mr. Gower and left. The next day Mr. Gower starts glowing and he is making noises and starts talking. HE IS ALIVE!! He was programmed to work in hospitals, and help doctors and nurses bring medicine to patients. Mr. Gower looks like a small cabinet with wheels. The body is a stack of locked drawers stored with medicine. Nurses and doctors unlock the drawers when medicine is needed for a patient. Mr. Gower can ride elevators, steer through hallways, and move things that get in the way.            This robot is so strong that it could pull 500 pounds. Mr. Gower runs on batteries, so he charges for two hhours and can deliver medicine for twelve hours without stopping. Mr. Gower can talk too. It can say, 'Calling elevator' or 'Your delivery is here.' Mr. Gower works for nurses and doctors and sometimes does their job so they can focus on more important tasks. After a few weeks working at the hospital Marcus comes back in his room to play with Mr. Gower but he was gone. His mom gets the newspaper and Mr. Gower is on the front cover. Marcus llooks at the picture and it looked like Mr. Gower was in the hospital He went in the room Mr. Gower worked at there he was. Marcus yelled, 'Come on Mr. Gower lets go home right now.'             But Mr. Gower couldn't leave. This was his job now and if he left he would leave many disappointed people. Marcus agreed with Mr. Gower and let him stay. Marcus would love to visit Mr. Gower one day. So he drove to visit Mr. Gower every day. When Marcus was old enough he got a job to become a doctor and he got the job! He got to work with Mr. Gower and all the other doctors and nurses. But the best part is that he got to meet snd sometimes play with Mr. Gower at work every day.

Item_Response: ?     There are remote-controlled robot that does search-and-rescue work in mines under the ground.  The robot is less than 2 feet tall and has wheels.  It can go up and down the stairs and can make? tight turns, and it can even roll through water.  The robot is small, but it is strong.  Gemini-Scout carries food, water, and other supplies.  It can even drag hurt people to safety.            Wherever it goes, Leo collects information.  For example, it tests the air for gases and then tells when the air is safe.  Leo also has a thermal camera uses heat sensors to find living things.  When Leo finds a trapped miner, the miner is usually trapped down under the ground so far that know one can reach the trapped miner.  The trapped miner always has his two-way radio with him because he might need to contact the rescue team.            The robot was built to be easy to use.  Its remote control is the same one that is used for some video games.  if you've ever played a video game,you may know how to use Gemini-Scout.  Dante 2 looks for vents, or holes, in the crater.  Then the robot collects information about the gases that come out of the vents.  In the past, scientists could not learn as much about volcanoes, but Dante 2 is changing that.  Now scientists can study a volcano up close while they remain safe in their laboratories.  Dante 2 is a robot with an interesting job---it climbs into volcanoes to gather information for scientists.  Like a spider, this robot has eight legs.  This helps it climb the steep walls of the volcano.  It is also built to survive very high heat.  When a volcano is too dangerous for scientists to enter, Dante goes instead.           Mr. Bower is a robot that works in hospitals, helping doctors and nurses bring medicine to patients.  Mr. Bower looks like a small cabinet on wheels.  The body of the robot is a stack of locked drawers that store medicine.  Nurses and doctors can the drawers when the medicine is needed.  Mr. Bower can go anywhere in the hospital.  It can ride elevators, steer through hallways, and move things that get in the way.  The robot is so strong that it can pull 500 pounds.  Mr. Bower runs on batteries.  After charging for two hours, the robot can deliver medicine for twelve hours without stopping.              An Agribot is a robot picks fruit.  It might pick berries, oranges, grapes, or apples.  Agribots are not yet widely used, but farmers are very interested in what these robots can do.  Because picking a strawberry is different than picking an apple.  Agribots come in all shapes and sizes.  Some have giant arms that are towed behind trucks.  Others are able to move around on their own.  In Japan, there is a strawberry-picking robot that can sense the color of the berries.  This helps the robot know when each berry is ripe.  Not only does it work long days, but he can talk.  It has been programmed to say hundreds of phrases.  For example, it can say,'Calling elevator' or 'Your delivery is here.'  Mr. Bower does work that doctors, pharmacists, and nurses used to do.  This allows them to focus on other important tasks.

Item_Response: It was another busy, tiring day at the hospital for Mrs. Peterson, a nurse.  She wished desperately that there was a robot that could help her do the job for her as she eyed the dusty lump of metal that had a shape like a robot.  Miraculously, the clump of metal came to life and wheeled itself in front of Mrs. Peterson.  She jumped, and nervously asked, 'Who are you?'           The robot replied, 'I am Mr. Gower, a robot, here to help you do work that nurses and doctors do.'           'Oh, I see.  So there are robots that help around in hospitals.  How convenient!' Mrs. Peterson exclaimed with a smile, now not so suspicious.  She then ordered the robot to finish her duty for the rest of the day.           The next morning, Mrs. Peterson found Mr. Gower in the corner of a room not moving.  She gently shook the robot, but Mr. Gower still did not budge.  At last, Mrs. Peterson decided to finish her shift at the hospital without him.  When she arrived home late at night once again, a thought occurred to her, Doesn't Mr. Gower run on batteries?  Instantly, she was relieved.  She had forgotten that all robots needed to be recharged at the end of the day.  That meant her work load would be cut in half if Mr. Gower worked alongside her every day.            For the next couple of years, everything went smoothly as Mr. Gower worked with Mrs. Peterson at the hospital.  Mrs. Peterson was extremely content because her work was cut in half.  From then on, she lived happily ever after.

Item_Response: One day a boy named Alex was trying to make a robot for the science fair,he worked on it for weeks and weeks,he couldn't figure out how to make it talk.Finally he got it 3 hours before the science fair,he went down stairs to get a snack and tell his mom he finish the robot but when he went back to his room the robot was gone! 'MOM' he shouted 'What is it sweetie' said his mom 'My robot is gone, what am I going to do'!?       Alex and his mother showed up to the science fair with no robot.Alex's teacher asked to see his robot but Alex didn't have one, his teacher said 'well if that's the case then you have a F'. Alex was very disappointed about his grade but there was nothing he can do,so Alex and his mother walked around the science fair to see what other students came up with. One kid had a robot that cook his breakfast, lunch, and dinner, another kid had a robot that did his homework,a lot of students had a lot of great robots, but just looking at the other students robots it made Alex very upset.Alex and his mother left, about 15 to 20 minutes later a random robot walked into the science fair.       The robot walked up to Mr. Gomez and asked for Alex 'Oh, you just missed him,and who are you?' Mr. Gomez said ' I am Alex's robot' said the robot 'You don't look like a robot, you look like a human bean'said Mr Gomez well that must mean Alex did a great job on me,right'? said the Robot 'Yes' said Mr Gomez and the robot walked away ' Oh and can you tell Alex he has an A, please'said Mr Gomez 'sure' said the robot. And that's how Alex got an 'A'.

Item_Response: It was Friday evening and I was watching a basketball game. The guests were wining but the home team,the Lakers, were losing. So that night, I went to sleep sad and angry. When I woke up, I had a wierd feeling someone was watching me. Scared, I went to the kitchen for breakfast but there was no one there. I looked all around the house for my parents but they weren't there. Thinking I was in a dream, I hit myself really hard on the head. Sure enough I fainted. When I woke up I thought I saw a robot, but when I blinked a couple times I saw my parents looking at me like I was crazy. I was wierd because one moment I saw a robot the next I saw my parents.                 I got up and asked my parents whats for breakfast. At first I thought they said screws with oil but then they said cerial. When I was done, I went to my room to study for my social studies test. When I opened my book, I found a page that I have never seen before. It was about a boy facing a fleat of robots. It said he defeated them, but they keep coming back every one-hundred years. The page was written in 1908 and it was 2008 now!                When I went to school, everything was normal. Nothing seemed unnatural. But when I came home, My parents were acting wierd again.

Item_Response: The             There was a boy named John, he was  in a collage robotic class at the University of Washington. The head coordinator of the robotics class was Mr. Howwenski. His class was about to go to a championship game in Los Angles and his team had decided that every person was going to build a robot, so they could have a better and bigger chance of winning 1st place and getting the grand prize. Their teacher, Mr. Howwenskie and the whole team were all extremely excited for the championships because they have all been practicing for over three and a half years and they finally made it to the top and if they won this finial competition that would mean that they were number one.         Everybody on the team was almost done with their robots, everyone but John. For his only excuse was that he has been extremely busy and that he has been studying for his big exam.'The championships are next week,' Mr. Howwenski would tell John after every practice and John would always say the same thing,'I know, i am just to busy.' Until one day when John came to practice    Mr. Howwenski told John that if he did not finish his robot that he would be kicked off the team. Of course Mr. Howwenski didn't mean it but he thought that if he told him that he would get scared and actually make his robot because the championships were the next day and poor John hadn't even started hi while everybody else was already done and had time to spare. Time that really needed.        Later that night when John was going his dorm he got straight to work and started to build his robot. That day he did not leave his dorm once and didn't even go to the bathroom or take a break he just kept on working. Once it was midnight John decided to finally go to the  bathroom when as he entered he heard a loud thump! When he went to go and see what the loud noise was he realized that his robot was gone.

Item_Response: The Friendly robot       I was once in the park minding my own buisness just listening to my music and relaxing because it was a warm sunny day out and i just wanted to be alone when i heard a man yelp and i got startled but then he said sorry and i went back to my music,when something caught my eye.I got up from my spot,put on my shoes,and went to a store where there were selling some kind of robots and there were really expensive,plus i didn't have that kind of money on me so instead i just went into the store and see what was inside and i saw a man standing near the counter so i walked right on out of the store and went home but,i felt like someone was following me so i started running.When i got home,there was robot siting all alone on the chair of the table and i just ignored it and went in my room and my parents wernt home at all but then i heard a pan clang on the counter of our kitchen,I got so scared i didnt want to come out of my room but instead i just couldn't help myself and went out rushing.When i got to the stairs,i went down slowly and calm down the stairs and sneaked into the kitchen and when i went in the kitchen,I saw the robot moving like a normal person and i was really really scared it might do something to me like to try and scare me away.But it just turned to my direction and said:hello their,i didnt mean to scare you or make you jump out of your skin. And i said:Its okay i guess and you kinda did scare me...a little.Robot:I am truly sorry! Me:Its ok  and its my fault for being such a chicken and how did you come to life?Robot:Oh well..i was made to be alive and i got cursed with something.Me: Oh well pkay then.Me and the robot went outside to play for a little bit,Eat something very yummy,and come back inside to rest a little and see what was on the Tv. The next morning my mom and dad came home and it was only 6:00 but it didn't really matter to me that it was early,I was just soo happy my mom and dad cam.Me:Mom,Dad,The robot can talk and its alive..Really!!Mom:That is ridiculous and I would never believe such a thing..That is not true and you were maybe sleeping and dreaming about it.Me Fine,maybe it was just a silly little dream.I went into my room to read to take my mind of of things.But then i saw it,the robot.It was just cleaning out my closet of clothes and puting it in the laundry basket and i only had 3 or 4 shirts that were dirty and i told the robot:What are you doing?Robot:Im just tring to orgaze some stuff around here.Me Oh okay then but don't come outside because i told my parents that you could talk but they just told me that i was maybe just dreaming about it.Robot:Oh well that is fine with me then!Me:Okay thank you by the way.Robot:You are welcome.    *The next day*    Me:Mom i was not dreaming at all!Please just believe me and see for yourself. Mom:Okay but just this once!Me and my mom go to my room were the robot was.Me:Mom...meet my robot.Robot:Hi there nice to meet you!Mom:AHHHH!!Me: MOM stay calm,its not going to hurt you but i felt the same way at first.Mom:O...kay... Sorry if i scared you robot.Robot:No its okay..I think im the one who should apoligize Sorry.Mom:Its okay...well kids lets go eat!And then we had a great time together.           1YEARS LATER       Mom:Honey I need to talk to you just for a little bit please.Me:Okay mother.As we walked to my room the robot was still cleaning dishes.Mom:Okay well we have to get rid of the robot you have right now.Me:Why?!Mom:Well its not good for us to just use the robot and and not make us do anythink.Me:Okay we will get rid of it but how do we convine the robot to leave the house?Mom:Well..we could take it back to the store that you got it from!Me:Okay then. Me and my mom walk back down the stairs and tell the robot we had to give her back to the store and just to give us spare time on our own.Robot:Okay i understand.Me:Okay then lets go back to the store and give you back to the man so other people will be able to bye you and love you to.Robot:okay lets go.Me,my mom,and the robot walked down the street to the robot store and told the man that we would like to give it back.Man:Okay well have a nice day.Me:Bye robot,I will miss you so much!As me and my mom left home,tears formed into my eyes and let the memories flow through and i watched as the robot i had started going far away as me and my mom walked.Me:Bye robot.           The End.

Item_Response: It was freezing.  I lay in bed, and I tightened my grip on my soft blanket and opened my eyes.  Something seemed different.  'Is it the cold?' I thought, 'No, it's always cold here in New York.'  I looked around my room.  Through the dim light of the moon, I saw the baby blue color of my walls, my wooden desk, and my robot, Mr. Gower, sleeping on my desk.  'Wait a minute... How can Mr. Gower sleep?  He's not even alive!'  At the sound of my voice, Mr. Gower woke up.  Excitement filled the room.  I jumped up, and ran up to him.                He seemed very happy to see me, and he said in his robotic voice, 'Hello Erin, nice to meet you.'  I was so excited and surprised that no words came out of my mouth.  All I could do was to stare at him, because my kindergarten teacher never told me the robot we made would come alive.                 When words finally came out of my mouth, questions spilled out, 'Hi Mr. Gower.  Why are you alive?  When did you come alive?  Where did you come from? and What...'              Mr. Gower cut me off, 'Please save the questions for tomorrow morning.  Let's go to sleep.  I am really tired.  And with that said, he fell backwards, snoring.  Almost paralyzed, I went back to bed.  I couldn't sleep, but somehow, I soon fell asleep.        The next morning, I woke up, and remembering Mr. Gower, I looked at my desk, but he was'nt there!  Thinking of what my parents would do if they found him, I jumped out of bed and ran downstairs.  Thankfully, I found him peacefully eating a bowl of cereal. 'Would you like to go to the hospital with me, Erin?' he asked.         'Why?' I asked, 'Are you sick?'        'No, I go there everyday to help the doctors and nurses bring medicine to the patients.'        'Cool!  I'll gladly go there with you.'  When we got to the hospital, I saw many doctors and nurses very busy.  However, when they saw Mr. Gower, all of them started calling him.  Mr. Gower went over to put batteries in himself, and started getting busy.  I watched as I sat in the waiting room, and thought, 'Wow, he seems very important here.'  That day, I realized that the future has arrived.

Item_Response: There was a kid named Sam and she had a robot. On a sunday night she was sleeping and all of a suden her robot came alive! 'Ahhhhhhh!!!' she scream frightened. Her robot was coming towards her and there was nothing she could do now. This is how it all started.                  Sam woke up on a Saturday morning and new she was late for her basketball game. She quickly got dressed and headed out to the court. 'Why are you so late?' her coach shouted at her. 'I'm sorry I woke up late,' she replied. 'Your robot will soon do something to you,' the coach replied. That got Sam really scared but she trusted her robot and new it would not do anything to her. The won the game and after the game was over Sam went to go play at her friend's house. She told her friend about what her coach had told her and her friend told her not to worry but Sam and her friend were both super worried.                    That night when Sam went to bed and it was all dark and gloomy, Sam got really scared. She was thinking about what her coach and her frind said bit she just couldn't get her mind off of it. Then, all of a sudden, her robot just came alive and started coming towards her. Sam was scared to death. 'My coach was right!' she screamed in horror. 'What are you going to do to me?' she shakily asked the robot. But the robot didn't say a word, instead it just started getting closer and closer. 'I can't take it anymore just do what you want to do with me already!' she said terrified. The the robot came even closer and closer and then it stared tickling her. All of a sudden Sam calmed down. She knew she could trust her robot not to do anything bad to her. Then Sam went to sleep and so did her robot.

Item_Response: It was a sunny day in Hawii, but lke it was always. Jo was about to leave, saying goodbye to his mom. He thought he was going to see her later...but than something happened.       Later on, Jo met up with his friends Annie, Alex, Rain and Fall. They all, friends, were in a creative writig club. Usely they did stupid stuff says so Annie. But Fall on the other hand, love it! She loved science too... One time this club promise that they would find something so grand, something so amazing, something that you couldnt even believe that has comed alive. Or even be helpful in the near future.       When this class was all done, they all walked home together. (Let me tell you how this all begin...) ' It was about three years ago when all five of them met. They live on SpringLake Loop. They all have been friends for quite a long time! They had made sectret club house and handshakes. Everything you could imagine friends do. They even started there own clubs, which is one there is this Creativing Writing Club...they made it up, it was there idea. Not even their parents know. They have always been friends and alwas will. '        But when they got half way to walking back to the neiborhood...there was a strange smell, and  a huge cloud of a dark gray, charkly smoke. Aand flying balls, hard rock, bright red, steaming...it was lava. Volcano, History blew up. Jo and his pantic, the didnt know what to do...go home, which was heading History or heading the oppitsite way, but they thought about every possible way. When they tryed to call their parents, their mom, dad, grandma, grandpa, but the powerlines were down. Fall was screaming and noody knew how to stop her, to calm her down. There was know possible way! The only thing they thought of was running...the Volcano was errupting, more and more! They ran forever, well it was for a long time. Finally they had came to a valley with a huge body of water, conneted to a beautiful, wide, calm, soothing, waterfall. Right next to it they found a cave. But it wasnt a cave would would want to sleep in...but that maybe could have been the case. It was deep dark, pitch black cave...no light was in it. At the farest distance. But at the time, it was the best they got. It was pouring rain at the time, almost about to hail! So it was Jo, than Alex, than Fall, than Rain, than little Annie. Huddling so close to each other...it was super chilly in the cave. They just wanted to stay dry...       Jo knew they needed a fire, or something that would keep them warm now and later in the night. Thinking about what all happen, so quick that they all were still processing their brains. Thinking about how they could loose their own mom or dad. And thinking, about what happen to their sibblings. Brothers, sisters...But than they thought about History, the volcano. They thought it would at least be done now...it had been like 5 hours! But they didnt want to risk the thought, or even seeing their own lives past before them.       13 hours later they woke up..it was a beautiful day, bright and shining! But it was a hard night for them, hearing drips off the ceiling of the cave, drip, drip. The were starving! Non of them really thought of a tragic like this would happen. later on, Jo thought about finding finding some cocmuts to eat. Cocuts are a thing where you can eat it or drink it, well not the counut it self, the milk. Once he found a cocnut tree he grabbed a cocnut for everyone. Trying to cut it open, which was very difficults for them...trying many times. Finally, one cracked open! It was juicy, delicous...but they had to share cause the others wouldnt open.        5 hours later, fall was scoping around the area...she has heared a radio, but it was very dim. Its was fuzzy, on and off. Than a voice can on! But than it went a way. She couldnt tell where it was coming from just that it was near her. Item_Response: Robots to the Rescue!   by Sophia Parker              Robots can be a big help. They can help in all daily life purposes. Have you ever wish you had someone to help you? Well, robots are now becoming more popular. They can play with you, and even save your life! Robots can go inside a volcano and find craters, send images to the scientists, and tell when the volcano will erupt. Robots also can go inside mineshaft and rescue people or bring food, water, and other supplies. They also help doctors by bringing medicine to the doctors so they can focus on important tasks.       Driving Robots         Have you ever wondered what its like to sit back and relax while you are driving? Well now scientist  are making cars that drive all around and you don't have to touch the steering wheel! They can see much better than humans can see when driving a car. This idea is safer because you don't have to keep your eyes on the road and you can text and call while driving. There have been hundreds of incidents from people dieing or having serious injuries. Scientist think that this is a safer way to drive.       Conclusion           In conclusion I think that having robots all over the world will be a big help. People will have easier life's than they do now. This of course, will happen in the future. So be prepared, it will be a wonderful time!

Item_Response: Robots can do lots of things. Some are remote-controlled. This robot is called Gemini-Scout. It does research and rescue work in mines under the ground. The robot is less than two feet tall and has wheels. It can go up and down stairs and make tight turns, and it can even roll through water. The robot is small, but it is strong. Gemini-Scout collects information. For example, it tests the air for gases and then tells miners when the air is safe.               Another robot has an interesting job. This robot is called Dante 2. It climbs into volcanoes to gather information for scientists. Like a spider, Dante 2 has eight legs. This robot is a very fast climber. It is different from other robots. Talk about fast climber! It can tell scientists whats in the volcanoes, and/or what they do in the inside. Scientists can now study an up-close volcano. Isn't that cool?               Now, this robot is very helpful. It works in hospitals, and it helps doctors and nurses bring medicine to patients. This robot is called Mr. Gower. Mr. Gower looks like a small cabinet on wheels. The body of the robot is a stack of locked drawers that store medicine. Nurses and doctors can unlock the drawers when the medicine is really needed. It can ride elevators, steer though hallways, and move things that get in the way. Not only does it work long days, but Mr. Gower can talk. It has been programmed to say hundreds of phrases. It can say 'Calling elevator' or 'Your delivery is here.' Mr. Gower does work that doctors, pharmasists, and nurses used to do. This allows them to focus on other important tasks.               This robot is also helpful. It picks fruit, and this robot is called an Agribot. Agribots are not yet wisely used, but farmers are very interested in what these robots can do. Because picking a strawberry is different than picking an apple, agribots come in all shapes and sizes. Some even have giant arms that are towed behind trucks. The agribots are like robot farmers. They pick up the fruit, and bring it to the farmer.                Now, the last robot is very, very cool. These robots are called 'Playful Robots.' Robots can, believe it or not, be just like animals, they can even act like them! There is one difference, though. You don't have to take them outside or feed them! Some robots can even play all by themselves. Students in Oregon have created robots that can play hockey or shuffleboard on their own. All year, it takes students hours, and hours to work on robots everyday. The robots can grab the puck, turn, twist, and compete to score. In the final test, the robots must push the puck to the goal without being told what to do.

Item_Response: Once there was an old man who had made a robot that could do just about any thing. It can sing, dance, cook, and so mush more. Then one day he realized that his days where coming to an end, and he wanted the robot to be in the hands of someone that he knew would not abuse it. That is when he made his choice to give it to his loving grandson named Billy. Billy was 13 and did not know how to use the robot, but did know about the robot and was determined to figure out how to use it. So that is just what he did             It had been 12 years from when he had gotten the robot from his, now dead, grandpa and he had just figured out how to use it. The robot was not difficult to use, but there was one complication that stood in his way. The robot came to life. The robot did not like to fallow its orders, but it wanted to be a normal human like Bill. The robot tried to do regular human activities, but always got laughed at when it failed.             Yet the robot never gave up, it just kept trying and trying all day and all night. Then one night the robot thought about looking in its memory banks for information about Bill and his grandpa. Once he did that he copied their activities and with the help of bill started to turn in to a human. then after years and years of practice and work you could never tell that the robot was a human.

Item_Response: One day I thought about building a robot and I wanted to call it Jeffery. If I was going to make a robot I needed some materials.  So tomorrow I went to the junk yard and found some stuff to make a robot.  I brought the stuff home and started to build the robot.  Then when it was done I said, 'It took a long time but I'm done now'.  The next day I was still in bed when I heard something talking.  Then when I opened my eyes I saw is was something walking around my room.  I thought it was my mom or my brothers or sisters but when it talk it sound really weird.  Right then I jumped out of bed and then there it was my robot that was walking around my room and it made a huge mess it pulled out all of my clothes.  Then I went to it and grabbed it and I just looked at it then it said, 'Hello I'm a robot and I'm alive.'  Then I said, 'I can tell but how did you come to life.'  Then it just shrugged.  Then I just took it to my family and I said, 'What am I suppose to do with it now.'  Then Jeffery said, 'Hello I'm a robot.' Then they just said keep him. It was pretty hard to figure out what he was going to eat because he is a robot and I didn't know what robots eat so I ask him. He said he eats junk. Then every day I brought him junk everyday.  Then after that day forward me and Jeffery were best friends.

Item_Response: One Christmas morning, Devyn woke up from a bright flash in front of him. When he opened his eyes it was just his parents taking a picture. 'Merry Christmas', they said. Mom dad i`m 15 now, i can wake up by myself. Come downstairs. Fifteen more minutes please. My parents walked out of my room with a grin.      As i went downstairs I noticed a box about as tall as me it was normal size but tall. I ran the rest of the way down the steps and jumped on the couch.      Can I open it? My parents nodded. I jumped up grabbed the wrapping paper with both of my hands and ripped off the wrapping. It was just a big brown box.      When i opened the large brown box all i saw was a piece of paper and a shovel. My dad asked if I liked it, yes i answered unsuringly.   What is it, I asked. My dad explained there was a story that goes with it that he heard at work. There was some sort of treasure out in the forest of hands.      About three hours later i called my friend Drake to come over and help me find this treasure my dad was talking about. Drake and his girlfriend Natalie both came over to help me find the treasure. We were digging for about five days until finally Drake was digging far away and he yelled 'I found something'!     Natalie and I both ran over to where Drake was and we were digging around the object to try and see what it was. I.. its a robot. We all stared at the seven foot tall robot all dirty and rusty. I called my dad to come bring his truck over and help us lift it out. My dad tied a rope around the robot and then the back of his truck and pulled it out.     As we got home We put him on the floor of the garage, I noticed a green switch. I flicked it up and the whole garage turned blue from the robots eyes. The robot looked around and jumped up, ran into the corner and was blurting out random numbers.      We all freaked out and we tried to calm it down and finally it stopped. We all introduced ourselves trying to calm it down, He also introduced itself. My dad quietly whispered ' is this the treasure? I sure hope not'. The robot heard what my dad said and it said, yes i am the treasure. The robot grabbed its chest and ripped it off, There were about thrity-two apple sized diamonds that fell on to the floor We all fell to our knees and searched thorugh the diamonds. The robot explained that its creator created it to protect the precious diamonds and we all took our share for finding the robot. The robot had left back to his creators grave and layed there for the rest of its life.

Item_Response: All Type Of  Robots Can Be Useful            There are all types of robots that are useful.  There is a called a Gemini-Scout, a robot called Dante 2, and Mr. Gower.  All of these robots are really useful to our world today.  As you can see there is many robots in the world, but I only have time to tell you about a little by little.               First, the Gemini-Scout is a remote-controlled robot that works in the mines under the ground.  The Gemini-Scout can do many things.  Gemini-Scout carries water, food, and other supplies. It can also even drag injured people to safety.  Wherever it goes, Gemini-Scout collects information for the miners.  For example, the robot has a thermal camera to help find miners.  When the robot finds the trapped miners, the miners can use the radio to talk with the rescue team.               Next, the robot Dante 2 is a robot with an interesting job.  It climbs into volcanoes to gather information for the scientists.  This type of robot is built to survive very height heat.  Dante 2 looks for holes or vents in the crater.  in the past, scientists could not learn that much about volcanoes, but Dante 2 changed all of that.  Now scientists can study volcanoes up close without getting hurt.               Then, there is a robot called Mr. Gower.  This type of robot works at the hospital.  Mr. Gower can go anywhere in the hospital.  The robot is so strong it can pull 500 pounds.  After charging for two hours, the robot can deliver medicine for twelve hours without stopping.  Not only does it work all day, Mr. Gower can talk.  This machine is programed  to say a hundred phrases.               All these robots are useful to the world.  They all do many different things, such as helping out the hospital and saving people that get lost in the mines.  Also some help scientists.

It is used to climb the steep walls of volcanoes to check out the inside. Mostly scientists use this robot, to see the inside of a volcano. The Dante 2 checks if there is vents, holes, or anything in the crater. The robot also collects information much like the Gemini-Scout.            Mr. Gower       Mr. Gower is a robot mostly used in hospitals. They use this robot for carrying medicine and for delivering it to sick patients. The Mr. Gower can talk, saying phrases like, 'You're delivery is here.' This robot is built like a dresser in order to hold medicine in locked drawers. It is also battery powered. Item_Response: The dream of the Future by:Carlos Berton      The day was January 3rd 1968 in Hameltontown U.S.A.  when young Jimmy Balteron was bolted awake.'Mom,Dad,' he shouted.His parent came running into to his small little room.'I had that dream again,' he said starting to cry.His father became furious with him.'When are you going to learn,robots are not real.They are some moronic idea you thought of and if you keep this up I'll send you to military school.      This was Jimmy Balteron's life.He'd always imagine of a world where robots could do amazing things.Cars could drive themselves,robots could help patients, and even keep you entertained.These seemed like the dreams of a child until one day when Jimmy was walking home from school he stopped by the local junk yard.'Look at all this metal and car parts.I'll make fantasy a reality.I'll make the first human like robot.'Jimmy said.he grabbed a few tin cans a car door handle and a lite bulb.      When Jimmy arrived home he ran up to his room and constructed a little model out of the materials he gathered.It was a  model of the robot with one rubber band amazingly he was able to make his own little contraption which could carry a water bottle.      Jimmy wrote this in his journal.Everyday he would stop by the junkyard and grab some items.He made a robot tat could climb a wall with suction cups,kind of like the robot we have today that climbs up the side of volcanoes today.He also made a miniature car which if you wind up could could drive itself.This is where wind up toys come from.It was invented by just a little kid.      Jimmy wrote all of his inventions down in his journal.When he grew old he still had the little book of his creations with him.One day he passed away of age.The family came to clean up the house and take all his possessions to remember him by.His brother found his little book in a drawer.and his eye caught on the little wind up car invention.He saw how Jimmy wrote how he in visioned it.His brother worked for Google so he showed his boss Jimmy's idea and how he in visioned it.Google is actually now working on it.It is the first car to drive itself.

Item_Response: Plan:       Intro:   Emmie(a 5 yr. old) loves to play but all she can do is train to go to kindergarden for b-day she gets a robot and it only comes to life when her parents are not home she loves it because it always plays with her thinks its games but the robot teaches her   First:   first alphabet games with prizes competition friends come over   Third:   reading Picture books (make up the words) little easy books normal books   Second:   writing letters(drawing book) cursive block letters   Conclusion:   school comes she already knows everything smart has fun   helps other kids           Writing:          Once upon a time a little girl named Emmie(who hated school and work) had to start preparing for kidergargen. She moaned and groaned to her parents how horrible it was to spend the summer studing and practicing but all they said was, ' We know you don't like it but please try hard. You will thank us later.' With that little Emmie stomped up to her room. When she came in she was amazed at what she saw, a beautiful blue robot!She ran back downstairs but too late her parents were gone. Oh well she thought and went back upstairs.When she came into her room she was even more amazed the robot had come to life. Yay! she thought but little did she know what was going to happen next.          Emmie wanted to play with the robot but he had different plans for her. 'So young lady,' he said 'What shall we start with.' 'Games, games and more games!' she shrieked. 'Ok lets start by calling all your friends and telling them to come over.' And so they did and all 11 of her friends came.'Lets start by playing the tebahpla game,' said the robot(Ben)'What's that.' asked a little red headed girl named Ruby.'Oh you'll see,' Ben replied. The kids didn't even notice that tebahpla was alphabet backwards until Ben said, 'Congrats kidos you all know the alphabet now. Wasn't that fun? But guess who's the smartest... Emmie!' And so Emmie got a big bowl of ice cream as her prize.          The next day Emmie ran up to her parents and yelled 'THANK YOU SO MUCH! THE ROBOT IS ALIVE!' but of course the parents didn't belive her and just smiled and said, 'We're glad you like is Em.' An went away to work. Emmie skipped up to her room and said, 'So Ben what game are we playing today?' The robot laughed and gave her a book that said gniward srettel(drawing letters) 'Oh that looks fun!' she said. And so she started working on the book when she finished Ben said 'Glad you liked it now you know how to write letters. Now if you liked that do you want to learn how to write fancy letters.' 'Umm that sounds soo uncool but fine lets try,' she replied. When they finished she was so happy that she asked 'Ben I heard about cursive can you teach me how to write in cursive?' With that they started to write in cursive. By the time her parents came she already wrote them a note saying: 'I love you so much! Thanks for the robot,' in cursive, block letters, and regular writing.          On Monday(a week before kindergarden started) Ben told Emmie it was time for her to learn to read of course like always Em started complaining but still decieded to learn to read. At first Ben gave her picture books that she had to look at and write the story. Then he made her read little tiny easy books. When she learned that he told her that if she wanted she could even read harder books. And so in two days Em learned how to read.          When the first day of kindergarden started Emmie was ready to go. When she arrived she found out that what she and Ben were doing was kindergarden.

Item_Response: As my friend and I started walking down the road taking a break from all our experimants, we saw the dump. there wasnt realy anything special about it but it was something we saw. In the distence was a little gleming lght in the dump. That light soon stated moving like crazy until we saw the whole body. As we scientists we like to know everything thats unknown or mysterious. We went into the dump. Two hours later that little light was part of a robots eye. The whole body was torn up and dirty, it even smelled!                  Back into the labb we studied the robot carefully so that we could ajust a few things to the robot. We had figured how old it was, and it happed to be 50 years old. We now knew that the robot had just came back to life. with all the tools we had we had to do something with the robot now that it came baclk to life. We used all the information to find out what to do with him.                  Instead of dealing with the robot we found out all the information tracking down the robots memorise. of course this robot had a name it was HP-48463. there was nothing realy scary about it but we turned its memroise into a little movie to show it to the world.   The movie didnt give us a lot of information we were looking for to find out who the HP-48463's owner was.                  As we vidoed it there was a voise talking to us. ther we found out it was calling out who the owner was. It said, sir Hennry! we noticed that it was calling the owner or should we say creator's name.   Finaly we sdearched the name and the creator died in a fire. Amased by alllthe history we found we goave it a little question and aslked it if they were the ones who saved a robber. We didn't know what to ask it was just a creative quetion that came in our heads.                 The robot reponded saying yes over and over again. After alll this time. Item_Response: The Robot                        A long, long time ago there was a robot named Roby the robot he was a working progress he won't work. Then one magical day he was left outside and struck by lightning and he was brought to life! The next day he went out to explore the world. When Roby was exploring he found a mine, then a robot popped out it said, 'hello' It was in a human voice Roby talked back and said, 'Hey there my name is Roby what is yours?' he responded 'Oh a talking robot that's new my name is Bob I'm a human he are talking through a two way radio I'm operating a Gemini-Scout.' Roby replied, 'Whats a Gemini-Scout?' Bob replied, 'A Gemini-Scout is a remote control operated robot that rescues people in mines it has a thermal camera and it is very important.' Roby was glad for the information and he went off on his way.                      Roby kept exploring when he explored he wondered about the Gemini-Scout. Then he found a robot store it selled toys, books, and even robots. There was a lady reading to children about robots. Roby was curious and went over to take a better look he walked until he was close enough to hear what she was saying. He learned a lot like about this robot called Dante 2 it climbs steep walls and other things and like a spider it has 8 legs and gathers information for scientists on volcanoes. Next he learned about a robot called Mr. Gower that is a robot that works in a hospital and bring s medicine to nurses and doctors he even carry things, even better he can talk like Roby. After that he learned about a robot called an Agribot it picks fruits and vegetables, it even plants a censer so they know when the fruits and vegetables are ripe. Roby was very satisfied in what he learned so he moveed on.                                                                                                                                                     Roby was now ready for a recharge so he went to sleep. The next morning something seemed different he can no longer talk either. So he went to investagate when all the sudden he saw in thermal vision. Roby thought back and remembered Gemini-Scouts have thermal vision and he figured out he had turned into a Gemini-Scout. Roby didn't know what was happening. Then he heard voices saying, 'Wake up for school Jimmy you don't wanna be late.' Then little Jimmy woke up and realized it was all just a wonderful dream.

Item_Response: The Robot That Came Alive    I was told that my best friend got a remote for her birthday and I went to check it out. When I got too curious and tried to help her brother get away from a robot. I made a terrible mistake.                         On Friday afternoon I was sitting on the back porch of my neighbor's house sipping on a tall glass of lemonade  when I heard a faint, but strange, noise. I looked up to see my best friend, Morgan, standing there. She was holding a remote that looked like it controlled the television set and VCR. I asked her what it controlled and why she had it. she said 'We'll it was my birthday yesterday and my mom gave me the remote but didn't tell me what it controlled. I wanted a new remote for my television because my brother, Jarred, won't stop throwing it on the ground during his temper tantrums over what he wants to watch, but it wouldn't work. I think my mom hid one of my presents in the basement and I'm determined to find it.' 'I didn't know that you had a brother, how old is he?' 'He's six.' she said.                          I told her that I would help her find what it went to, so we walked down the porch stairs and she unlocked the basement door with a spare key. She always keeps it under the door mat that no one else knows about but us. When we got in I didn't know where to look first, all I could see was stacks of Jarred's old toys. I saw strollers with action figures in them, a really small basketball goal and a little basketball to go with it. I thought I saw a little head popping out from behind storage bins and it was him alright. Morgan told him to help us look for what the remote went to and he wouldn't unless we gave him some money. we tricked him by saying that a pennie was worth fifty dollars. He didn't believe us so we gave him a dime and said it was worth ten dollars. Apparently that was more believe able to him.                After a while I got thirsty and Morgan was, too. We went back outside and sat on the swings while I drank the rest of my lemonade. Morgan got a Pepsi and a Mountain Dew and a very tall glass. I was thinking about what she was going to do and she mixed both of them into that really tall glass and put  a candy cherry in for good taste. We had been sitting there for about ten minutes when we heard screaming coming from the basement. A wierd looking robot was holding Jarred by the arm and dangling him over a huge tub full of old action figures. I knew they were his because of the way he looked at them.               I inched closer and closer to the robot until I saw writing on its arm. It said  'My name is Nik if found please return to this address.' and had her address on it. her address was 2431 Cranberry Road.               It came at me and I yelled 'Morgan push the unlock botton on the remote, Aaahhhahahaha.' It dropped Jarred and got on all fours like a dog and made wierd noises that kind of sonded like an electronic bark. she used the remote to make it different animals and the n kept it as a duck.               When we got done playing with it we went in the house to tell her mom what happened. She said that she knew we would find it so she wanted us to go on a little adventure. Since everything was okay I went back to my house and found a remote on my bed with a sticky note on it that said 'You have to find the present or you don't get it.mom. The process started all over again and I had a great time finding the little robot.

Item_Response: The Robot crisis                               It was a nice and sunny day me Colby, Austin, david, and Steven were playing outside in my back yard. Then we suddenly heard a 'Thump'. We  rushed toward where we heard the noice and we found a giant hole right behind the trees in the forest near my house. We looked inside and there was a robot.We brought it up to have a better look. It was a robot but it wasn't alive so we all thought t was a waste. Either way we decided to keep it. As we walked back we thought of  ways to hide it because we knew we weren't going to be able to keep it. 'I know where i said'. 'We can hide it in my tree house and play with it when ever we want. We walked back in silence. When we arrived at my house we hid the robot. Then we all made a wish ''I wish the robot was alive'we all said.             The next day we all met up at my house we saw the robot it was moving and making itself some oil. we screamed in fear from this but then  we smiled. 'It came alive just like we wanted ' said Colby. Months passed as we played with Robert that was his new name. We played tag ,video games ,and dodgeball. We also went to the movies, the arcade, amusement parks it was the best time of my life. One day Austin told Robert ' I hope you never leave ' he said. Steven said 'your family now Robert and you'll always be safe with us'.  'Here is a present for being our friend' said David.Then out of nowhere Robert told us he had to leave

Item_Response: 'Bolt?' Screamed 12-year-old Allie, trying to find her dog.   'Bolt!' She tried again.  She tapped her foot, figuring out what had happened.  'Alex I know you took Bolt!'   Alex, her older brother came out of a closet, holding the small dog and laughing.   Allie groaned and snatched her dog away.  She ran up to her room and plopped on her unmade bed.   Snap, snap.   'Hello?' Allie called, facing the way she thought the sound was coming from.  She knew it couldn't be Alex, since she just saw him downstairs.   Snap, snap, snap.   'Whatever,' Allie said, deciding to ignore the sound.  After all, they lived in an old house, so it was probably just some creaking floorboards.   Allie burried her face in her pillows and fell asleep.       'Huh?' She croaked about an hour later.  A large figure towered above her.   'Alex, go away!'  She threw her pillow at who she thought was her brother.  But the figure stayed put.   Finally, the large body stepped into the light, where she could finally make out who or what it was.    'Ohmigosh,' she said, stunned.  The figure wasn't her brother at all.  It was a large robot.   'What the heck?!'  She turned away and closed her eyes, thinking it was all a weird dream.   'Oh, don't go!'  A sweet voice pleaded.   Allie turned to face the robot, amazed that it could speak.   'Where did you come from?'  Allie asked quietly.   'Your brother,' the robot replied.   'What?'   'You know how he always creats things?'   'Yeah.'   'Well, he made me about a week ago, but I have no idea how I'm alive.'   'Um, okay.'  Allie said, surprised that her brother could actually be successful. 'What's your name?'   'Oh, I never really thought of that.  Um...'   'It's okay, I'll name you.  How about Mia?'   'Okay!'  Mia replied, cheerful.   'So, um, why did you come in my room?'   'So I could kill you.'   'WHAT?!'  Allie shrieked.   'What, what?'  Mia cocked her head to the side, innocently.   'Nothing, I must be hallucinating, or something.'   'Okay.  Why don't you go back to sleep.  I'm sorry I woke you up.'  Mia sounded sincere.   ''Kay, thanks!'  Allie retrieved her pillow and fell asleep.       While Allie was sleeping, Mia stayed put for a while, making sure Allie was not awake.  After about 10 minutes, Mia tip-toed down the stairs and got a hammer from the cabinet.  Next, she walked back up to Allies room, and fake hit her on the head with the hammer a few time, making sure she knew where to hit.   'Allie?'  Alex yelled from the hall.   Mia didn't seem to hear, because she was continuing to do what she was doing before.   Alex saw Mia, and quickly rushed inside to save his sister.   Knocking the hammer from her hand, he picked Mia up and chucked her out the window.   'ALLIE WAKE UP!'  Alex shrieked.   'WHAT do you want?'  Allie jerked up from her sleep, alert.   'My old invention, a robot, was about to kill you with a hammer!'   'You mean Mia?'   'Whatever.'   'Um, okay, so where is she?'   'I, uh, threw her out the window.'   'Are you insane?!'  Allie rushed to the window to see the robot passed out on the ground.   'Don't do that.  Next time just call the cops.'  Allie insisted.       Together, the called 9-1-1 and told them the details.  The cops seemed skeptical about taking a robot to jail, but finally gave in.  After that day, Alex and Allie tried to never fight again, and created a really strong bond.  Mia was never heard from again, and probably never will be.

Item_Response: It was the beginning of summertime, and all the other kids were outside playing in the warm sun, but not Jimmy. For months, he had been in his garage, working on making a robot. Jimmy's biggest dream was to be tall. Jimmy had always been the shortest kid in school, and he always got picked on for that. It made him furious. So he came up with an idea to make a gigantic robot that could lift him up so he'd feel tall.       Jimmy's dad came in to the garage. 'Hey Jimmy, want to go throw the baseball around with me?'       Jimmy didn't look away from the robot. 'Not now, Dad. Maybe later.'       Jimmy's dad sighed. 'Okay, maybe later...' Jimmy's dad wished Jimmy would come out of the garage sometimes, but he knew how much that robot meant to Jimmy.       Weeks went by, and it was the middle of summer. Finally, one night, Jimmy was so close to finishing his robot. His robot arms and legs could extend just by the touch of a button on his remote controller. Only one step had to be finished, and that was adding the head. Jimmy was tired that night, so he thought he'd do it in the morning.       As Jimmy was walking up the stairs, he heard a loud crash. However, he was so tired that he just ignored it. All night, Jimmy dreamed of what his robot would turn out like. He imagined his robot lifting him up so he could dunk on the basketball hoop, like the other tall boys at school.       The next morning, Jimmy ran downstairs excitedly. When he walked into the garage, he screamed. His mother and father came rushing in. When they saw the big commotion, they gawked at the huge mess of various robot pieces laying around.       Jimmy went and picked up the pieces. He sadly laid them on the work bench, but didn't bother to put it back together. His father took him out for ice cream to make him feel better, but it didn't help.       Jimmy sat on the sidewalk all alone, with his head hung down as he watched his ice cream drip onto the ground. He was too upset to eat. 'Jimmy, what's wrong?' He heard an unfamiliar voice behind him. He turned around to see who it was, and...       It was his robot! He was too shocked and surprised to say anything, so he just stared. His robot came over, picked him up, and spun him around. Jimmy was so happy and surprised! Jimmy and his robot became best friends.

Item_Response: Robots   by: Alanah Malone       Robots use to be considered a thing of the future. I remember those days well. As a young boy I regret wanting robots to be a part of your society.   There are many robots now. They have taken over, scientists didn't realize how powerful they made their beautiful yet terrifying creation. There are the three most powerful robots, Mr.Gower, Dante 2, and the self driving car.   Every Mr. Gower created has medical smarts. This intelligently designed piece of equipment has created a mind of it's own. it has learned how to change medicine into poison and with great accuracy can shoot needles filled with toxic medication.                                     The next robot is Dante 2, used for research. This robot learned many things about volcanoes and finding it's way through the craters and looks for vents and/or holes. It has eight legs like a spider, but recently it has gone roge and learned to harness the energy from the magma and uses tht energy to destroy the human race.                           Finally, the biggest robot. The self-driving car, has unlimmited sense of data and can see all of its surroundings. They are infectionus and almost impossible to get rid of! Because of it's $80.000 cone-shaped laser it has umlimmited vision all the way around. Also, its unlimited data comes from its wireless gps navigator system. I used to want one of those cars so badly. Now i regret they were even made.                   Hopefully someday someone will be brave enough to come save us here in the prison.                                                                                  Sincerly, Hank

Item_Response: Drake was in his room on his bed reading a comic book like he does everyday afterschool.   He finished the comic and looked on the back 'lets look on the back to see when part two is coming out.' Instead of  an ad for the comic book it was an ad for a toy, but not just any toy, it was a robot it said 'robot best freind only 19.95$.' Wow, it must not work if it cosy that much.   But drake changed his mind, even though he already have a best freind 'Ivette' but he thought this would be cool.    Drake got some of his birthday money he got 21$ out of 102.09$ he sent it to the adress and waited. He waited for 3 weeks. The robot was 1 foot tall maybe a few inches shorter. He was all white, he had two black dots for eyes and a cheezy looking smile, and he had no shoes, no shirt, and no hair. I named him Bob. The AD said that he walked and talked but all he did was a marchimg walk and say 'your my bestest freind' that really creeped me out. I didnt care it was still cool looking.    I went to bed early becuase it was sunday so that meant school. I had put bob on my shelf next to all my action figures. I stared at it all night thinking what if i missed a button on him? what if he could fly?' All that thinking got me tired even more so I fell asleep. The next morning I found out that bob was missing. it was quite I heard loud snoring I thought it was my annoying older sister 'natalie'. But it wasnt. It sounded like It was In the room. I felt the bed vibrating, I grabbed the covers threw them off and I screamed. Bob was sleeping in my bed, he was in a cuddling position and snoring awfully loud. Bob sounded like a pig sleeping. Bob got startled by my scream, I didnt know it but, my mom did too. Bob woke up shouting 'AHH, dog dont eat me!!!' I was amazed ' y-y-y-y-you can....... talk?!' 'yep' but why werent you talking to me yesterday ?' 'well-' but before he could finish 'Honey are you okay?'the door knob started to turn    Before drakes mom could open the door he stood up put bob behind his back 'I heard you scream' 'oh I woke up falling off the bed 'oh, be carful and get ready for school.' 'Okay' 'phew that was a close one' 'yep' 'well I have to get ready for school' 'Okay'.

You need to go now. We've to change the future. Goodbye now.' Then the robot left and I was very confused.       The robot was still there and it said, 'I'll obey your command.'   Then I said, 'Teleport me to back to my house,' and I was in my bed.

Item_Response: The Muffin Man                  One foggy morning, a plane flew over a valley in California. The plane was experiencing problems. Then the plane went down, like a bird that didn't know how to fly, and crashed. Dust whirled into the air and created it's own sandstorm, then it settled down to rest on the ground where it came from. A small boy who saw the plane ran to the crash site. Out from the plane rolled a piece of machinery the size of person. It rolled until it hit a rock that pushed a button. The machine's lights flickered like firefly, then steadied to solid colors. It appeared to have a head, a body, limbs, and lights on its highest section that resembled a face. It then stood up on two legs. The boy watched in amazement. The machine looked at him. 'I am the Muffin Man,' it said. 'I am a robot.' It didn't talk in the choppy voice you'd think a robot would talk in. It sounded just like a normal person. 'I'm John,' said the boy. The Muffin Man looked at John with its bright, colorful eyes. 'I am a robot that makes muffins. It is my destiny to make delicious muffins.' John thought this was amazing. 'Can you make me a muffin?' John asked. The lights on the Muffin Man's face showing a smile shut off and in the same instant new lights turned on that showed a frown. 'I'm afraid I can't,' he said. 'A couple of my parts had fallen of of the plane in the crash. There are only two but they could be anywhere, and now I will not fulfill my destiny.' John wanted to help the robot. 'What if I help you find the parts?' he said. The Muffin Man smiled and said, 'Really, you would do that?' John said, 'Sure.' 'Okay,' the Muffin Man said. 'Then let's go!' John and the Muffin Man set off to find the missing muffin making parts.                 The first place they went was the city. Enormous skyscrapers towered over John and the Muffin Man. The part could be anywhere. 'I wish I didn't have to walk,' John said. 'Well, why didn't you just say so?' said the Muffin Man, and just like that, he twisted and turned and transformed into a go-cart. 'Get on,' said the Muffin Man.' John got on the brightly colored cart and sped away. They flew through the city on the small cart, but they didn't find any parts. Then John spotted a construction site. 'Let's look in there,' John said, and they sped through the gates. Then there, in the middle of the site, was a piece of machinery. It had words on writing on it that was cut off. ' There,' said the Muffin Man, 'that's one of the pieces. The construction workers must have thought it was for their building.' Then a construction worker saw them. 'Hey, kid, what do you you're doing here?' he said. 'Step on it, Muffin Man!' yelled John. Without hesitation, the Muffin Man accelerated toward the part. John snatched off the ground and the Muffin Man drove up an improvised ramp. They soared over the fence and raced out of the city.                The go-cart stopped at a small shop outside the city and transformed back into the Muffin Man's normal shape. 'That was close,' he said. John nodded. 'Just one more part,' John said. Then he noticed the sign in front of the shop. Muffin Factory, it said. John noticed a big truck pulling into the back of the factory. 'Hmmmm.' John thought about something. 'Follow me,' he said to the Muffin Man, and they followed the truck. Two men started unloading packages. John noted what they took out: muffin mix, blue berries, chocolate chips, vannilla, muffin mixer-wait, muffin mixer. John noticed the mixer had writing on it that looked like it matched up with the writing on the Muffin Man's other part. That was it. 'Muffin Man,' said John, 'transform into a go-cart, I've found the last part.' 'Really?' said the Muffin Man. 'Really,' said John. When the men weren't lokking John snatched the part and ran back to the cart. The Muffin Man immediatly sped away just as the men turned around and realized the part was missing. The go-cart stopped back at John's house and transformed back into the Muffin Man. 'Now let's make some muffins,' said the Muffin Man. He put the parts together and the words spelled, 'Muffin Man.' John pushed a green and the mixer started to turn. John watched as the Muffin Man created creamy and delicious muffins. The Muffin Man shouted with joy. 'YES, I AM FULFILLING MY DESTINY AS THE MUFFIN MAN. WWWWHHHHHHAAAAAAA!' he screamed, and out popped a delicious muffin. John bit into it. It was the most wonderful he had ever tasted. 'We should do this every day,' said John. 'We will,' said the Muffin Man, and they went into John's house for the night.

Item_Response: Robots are very useful items to have. they can go all the way from picking fruit to saving peoples lives. Robot stories were realistic fiction a while ago, but now some of it is starting to come true! now that we have all of this technology we are actually starting to build robots similar to stories.       The Gemini-Scout is one type of robot. It is a remote-controlled robot that is designed for search-and-recuse type of things. It can go up and down, make turns, and even roll through water. It is a smaller built robot, but it is definitely a strong one! they can also carry many supplies. Wherever it goes though, its always gathering information. Controlling a Gemini-Scout is pretty much like controlling a video game. This robot sounds truly amazing!       Another type of robot is the Dante 2. This robot has a very interesting job though. It climbs into volcanoes! Why does it climb into volcanoes exactly? It gathers information in very hot volcanoes that scientists cant go into. It is built to survive extremely hot heat! The Dante 2 looks for openings like vents or holes in a volcano. Then it collects up a bunch of information about the gases and the magma. This device has allowed scientists to get information while remaining in their labs.       The Mr. Gower is yet again another spectacular device! It is a robot that works at hospitals for assistance. He helps doctors and nurses with many things. Mr. Gower is like a big cab nit with wells and a head. He carries important tools and medicines for patients. he is also very strong because he can lift over 500 pounds! Mr. Gower runs on batteries. once he is charged for two hours, he can work for 12 hours! Another cool thing is that he can also speak! he has been programed to say many phrases. this allows doctors to be more proficient.       Lastly we have the Agribots. This robot is a robot that picks fruit! it can pick berries, oranges, grapes, or apples! Any fruit you name it! Not very many of these are used but they are causing an interest with farmers. Agribots come in all different shapes and sizes. Some of them are able to around on there own. There is a robot in Japan that picks strawberries but also can sense the color of it to tell if its ripe or not. Pretty neat isn't it? Agribots are like robot farmers.       Robots are truly a great technology and i hope we will all be using many of them soon. It is amazing that technology has gone this far! Robots hopefully will be popular in the future. This is really a great technology!

'It wasn't long before I finally heard it talking at me.'

Item_Response: The Big Bad Robot                                                There was once a robot named the Boogey man. He had three human friends named Justin, Jake, and Johnathon. While at the park, Johnathon decided to have a game of catch with Jake and Justin. Although John wanted to play catch, Justin and Jake refused. Instead, they wanted to play with the big bad robot, Boogey man. Jake quickly activated the big bad robot and tested it out by voice command, seeing if it could talk, and it's mobility.                   The Boogey man reached all of Jakes expectations and because of this the three boys started playing with the Boogey man more often. One night, Justin was incredibly bored, had nothing to do, and wanted to play with the Boogey man.                          The only problem was, is that the Boogey man was at Jakes house. Justin gives Johnathon a call planning to sneak over to jakes house to steal the big bad robot to rearrange him to program him to be a evil robot. The only problem Justin and John didn't know was that The Boogey man was already evil.            Jake is on his computer, chatting with his friend, Charlotte on facebook. As jake is about to send his goodbye message he feels a grasping metal hand on his shoulder. Jake screams ' HELP HELP HELP!'  But this came to no one's attention because no one was home. As jake and the Boogey man tangle in Jakes room, Justin and Johnathon sneak in through the back door of jakes house. 'Hello?' John yells, with no reply. 'He's probally upstairs' Justin said with his first step up the stairs. During this fight, Jake noticed the Big Bad Robot had legs and arms that made him look like a spider, and had the ability to talk, like the Dante II and the Mr. Gower robots.           'Boogey man at your service' the boogey man calmy announces.   BOOM, the door claps open as Justin and John hurry to the room trying to take the boogey man off Jake. With a final punch, the Big Bad Robot, the Boogey man, falls to its collapse. For their cellabration of the fall of the boogey man, the boys sleep over  Jakes house with a nice bite of fried chicken.
