Item_Response: 'What is it?' my friend Lily asked. 'I don't know,' I said. My name is Ashley. My friend Lily and I are at the junk yard. We were trying to find something interesting for our science project. This is interesting but, what is it? 'A metal person!' Lily exclaimed. 'What?' I asked. 'Look there's a head, an arm, and I think that is a foot,' she said. I sighed, 'It's a robot.' It was pretty cool, but how was I going to use it for my science project? Meanwhile, Lily kept rambling on about how she loved anything to do with robots and knew everything about them. 'They can save live you know,' she informed me, 'they save miners trapped in caves, carry off injured people, and even bring medicine to hospital patients!' 'Yes, but can they get me an A+ on my science project?' I wondered out loud.           As soon as I said that, I heard a metallic voice reply, 'Yes.' For a split second I was surprised. 'Stop messing with me Lily!' I scolded. I then turned around. The robot we had found was staring back at me. I nearly fainted! I slowly backed away, in fear that the robot might hurt us somehow. Lily, on the other hand, just kept gaping at the robot. 'What's your name? What type of robot are you? Is it really true that you can help us with our science project?' Lily asked the robot all at once. The robot looked very confused, I know I would have been. 'I am MultiBot.' It said,' I have all the skills of robots such as Gemini-Scout, Dante 2, Mr. Gower, and an agribot.' Lily's jaw hit the floor. 'What else can you do?' asked Lily eagerly. 'As well as working I can also entertain people by singing, dancing, and even playing music,' replied MultiBot.           I have to admit it's fascinating to see this robot but, I just really want to know how it could help me get an A+ on my science project. As if reading my mind, the robot said, 'For your science project, bring me and pretend that you invented me. If they ask how I was invented, I will answer that for you.' This robot is amazing! 'If you can do so much, why are you in a junkyard?' I asked. It didn't reply. I guess it was a sore subject. Do robots even have those? I shook off the thought. The science fair was in a couple of days and this robot was in no shape for presentation.            At my house Lily and I polished, waxed, oiled, and repainted MultiBot. He looked as good as new. The day of the fair, Lily and I fixed up MultiBot one last time and headed to the school where the fair was being held. 'I hope this works Ashley,' said Lily with a shaky voice. I could tell she was nervous, I was too. 'Don't worry Lily,' I whispered. After the judges had viewed all the projects, they went on stage to announce the winner. I crossed my fingers. Everything had went smoothly with our project but I was still very nervous. 'The first place winning team is: Ashley and Lily with their MultiBot invention!' announced a judge. Lily and I cheered as loud as we ever had before. Many other contestants gave us dirty looks but we didn't care. We got an A+ and a gigantic trophy after that. Sadly MultiBot broke after the science fair; Lily and I didn't know why. We were very sad and Lily cried for a week. Lately, in my sketchbooks, I have been designing a new, improved MultiBot. I hope my design is built one day in the future. I know I would see him again someday, I just feel it.

The enginer, however, was thinking about its look, so he said,''I'll make it buff, fast, and rolls. Item_Response: Hi im James. I'm 16 and heading towards the driving test. I cant wait to get a new car so i can gat money by taxing people sround. Little bit of backround, I live in new york and know almost every inch of it. Ok im heading to the test and going to try to pass ,obviosly. It feels like hours till we reach the place. When we reach there it feels like time slows down. I just cant wait to get my license to drive. The things i caould do without my parents, actulally spend time at partys instead of being 1/2 hour late and leaving a 1/2 hour early.When we walk in I give all my personal info and wait and wait and wait till i can do the driving test. Finnaly its time I step into the car and set my destination 10 blocks away, The bar. When I get there my friends cheer that I didn't crash the car unlike poor Mrs. Envers who lawn mower I crashed, (not my fault its her dogs fault, the dog got in my way.) I turn around and head back towards the drivers ed place. When I gat there im presented with two things. One my license to drive, yay and a texi cab awsome.       When I get in I decide to head to a party that night and see if there is going to be any drunks that need to be driven. sure enough there is two rich people whr drunkaly wave me over and gat in. I imput the adress into the gps and put on headphones so they dont hear the annoying directions. comming from the gps system. It seemeed though that whenever i needed to turn cth car started the turn a little bit before me.       That night i pick up my friends,  (im the oldest so im the only one with a car) and tell them my car is steering itself an all my friends do is laugh, and laugh, and laugh. I decide to show them but the car makes some mysterios wirring soundes and only tugs the wheel a tiny bit so they said its the cars normal swaying. Life went as normal I toured people around but eac time the car seems to be driving more and more. Then one day about a week after i got the car I picked up my friend from his house and took him to the drivers ed place so he could drive himself. That day i  imputed the route into the gps clicked go and the car drove itself entirely. My friend then believed me but warned that self driving cars were illegal. When my parents foung out about this a couple waaks later they tried to make it leagal for self diriving cars.       When we were going to the celebration for self driving cars to be leagalized in new york somemone saw the car was driviong itself and started yelling at me. Whiel he was destracted his car swerved into the rail in that we were all injured from a quite fast flying beer bottle and stoped us fom driving. When I fell I took the key out and the car stoppped. A stranger saw that my car drives itself and put the man who was in the accadent in my car closed the door but not befroe imputing the location of the hospital.       a week later the car had saved four lives and the press was going crazy. By the time we were done every state but new york had leagalized self driving cars. Whe I was healed i got to sighn the document that leagalized self driving cars. From then on I did a nice taxi scirvese and earned decent pay. At the end  I owned the major self driving car taxi servise, in the world.

Item_Response: Robots were never even thought possible just over 100 years ago. Zoom to today and you have robots everywhere. Robots that help in the mines, explore vocanoes, are assitants in hospitals, can farm and pick fruit, dance, sing, their is even a robot that is a car that is self piloted. All of this has a huge impact on everyday human life. Some even save lifes in ways you never would've thought possible. You may even think that these robots are miniscule, or non-needed in our enviroment. Some inventors would beg to differ.        Gemini Scout is a robot that helps in the mines. This small robot is cabable of many things. For exapmle, it can collect information, climb stairs and take sharp turns, help hurt miners, and help rescue crews get to the wounded. This robot is small, but strong. Gemini is a remote-controlled robot, and the device to control it is similar to those in a video game. So if you have ever played a video game, than the controls to Gemini will probably be quite familiar.          Dante 2 is a very interesting robot that helps scientists in many ways. Dante is used to navigate volcanoes. It can collect information, find vents and holes in the volcano. The robot can also withstand extreme heat and would go places where scientists never thought could be explored.          Mr. Gower is a medical robot that helps in hospitals. Gower runs on batteries, and can work long days without fatigue. Certain features that this robot has are;   100s of phrases Can deliver medicine Dosen't need to be paid          This Robot would save many lifes and has a very high potential when they and if they are mass produced.           Agribots will also have a big impact on lives. These robots have been programed to farm, harvest, and in some cases, pick fruits. These robots are still prototypes are are being experimented on. However, that didn't stop them from making and growing their own garden.           The Google car is a car that is self-driven, or in other words, dosen't need a person to drive it. This is, again, another robot that has the potential to save lifes. The Google car dosen't text, drink, tire, fatigue, or get distracted whilst driving. The way that it works is the censors on the roof, back, and front of the car will sense where the car is going, and it will generate maps to the passengers while its moving, almost like a GPS. A problem that Google faced was getting this legalized and making a law that these can be on the road. Then, in Nevada, a law was passed saying that these self-driven cars were in fact legal.           As you can see, there are many robots out there that are going to, and may already, have a large impact on our everyday human life. These robots may even end up saving our life someday. Some of these fine inventions may not be available for quite some time, but we can only hope, that the wait will be worth it.

Item_Response: Robots Story       Plan       1.  There are many different kinds of robots   2.  Robots can save lives   3.  Robots can help collect data   4. A paragraph for each robot           Story       Robots are a new way to help people that need it.  Robots can collect data, save lives and much more.  They help scientist, doctors, miners and animals.  Each robot has a different role that is unique.  Some robots can move by themselves and some use a remote.  Some robots can climb volcanoes and some can collect data.  Clearly, There are many different types of robots and roles.        Robots can save lives by helping miners and rescue teams.  The robot that does this is called the 'Gemini-Scout'.  The Gemini-Scout is a remote controlled robot that does search-and-recuse work in mines under ground.  The robot is small and fast.  It is very strong and can carry many supplies for people.  It also has a two way radio to let the trapped miners talk to the rescue team.        Robots can also help humans collect data and go where humans can not. The 'Dante 2' is a great example of that.  The Dante 2 climbs volcanoes to gather information.  It looks for vents, holes or craters and collects information about gasses.  The robot has eight legs (like a spider) to make it easier to climb and get in small spaces.  Now, scientists can collect more information and still stay safe.       Robots can act like doctors too.  'Mr. Gower' is like a nurse in the hospital.  Mr. Gower is like a cabinet on wheels.  Doctors and nurses can store medicine a tools in there and Mr. Gower will bring them what they need when they need it.  Mr. Gower is also very strong and smart.  He can pull up to 500 pounds and ride elevators.  Mr. Gower can even talk.  Mr. Gower is now even helping to save lives.       Robots can even plant and cook. The 'Argibot' can pick fruit and vegetables and plant them too.  Some can move around and some have very long arms.  The Argibot can grow almost anything with no human input at all.  The 'Massachusetts Institute of Technology' is hoping one day the Argribots will become common of farms all over the world.       Clearly, Robots are a very good idea and we should make more.  They would make life easier for not only doctors, miners, scientists, and cooks but for everyone.  With this data and helpfulness they will one day make the world a better place.  They already are starting to.  Clearly, robots are the next generation of everyday life.

Item_Response: One day I was walking along when I looked into a building and saw a robot walking around in the building. So I said to myself ' I should build a robot!' So I ran back to my house and told my mom that I going to become famous. She said ' OK honey dinners almost ready.' Then I started researching online wire work. So after a day or two I got really good with wires. Now it was time for practice.          When I was walking home from school I went to the store and bought more wire and scrap metal. I drew a design on my note book of what it was going to look like. Then I decided on a name for it. His name was Toby. So I ripped it out of the note book and put it on my wall above my bed. After that I went to bed. The next day during school I got really bored and started drawing Toby again. But this time he looked more realistic and colored! I got home and started working on the wiring.            When I was done testing the wiring I started working on the metal. I made the head in one week exactly. Then I realized that it was too small!! So I took the nuts and bolts out of it and put them in a little bag. Bent the metal back with some of the tools I bought a while back. I made a bigger head. I was very proud of myself. Then I showed my mom. She said it looked amazing. The next thing I did was put the wires in his head. I also put a voice in him. When I put the voice in him I also put a dictionary with him too so he knows all the words in the world. Once I was done with the wiring in his head I tested him out. He worked perfectly!!! now it was time to make the rest of the body. I got done with the feet that night. The next day At school I was very excited to go home and finis Toby. When I got home I finished the rest of him!!! Now to put the wiring in. I got the wiring in that night. But I didn't get to test him out. I was so excited I totally forgot about home work. I got detention at school. But I got home and tested him out. He worked perfect!!! He was the best robot you can get. We went outside and played everthing you could possible imagine. Everone was complimenting me on my robot. My mom also thought he was great he helped around the house and everthing!! We went outside and played more. When the sun went down we started our way home.

Item_Response: It was a normal day here in the RMI until it happened. The most unique but terrible incident happened. It all started when we were making the perfect robot. We thought it was just an experiment ,but we thought wrong.                           In the RMI ( Robot Making Institute )  we decided to built a robot that can shoot lasers and stuff, but one day when i woke up and went to do lab I saw the robot move.I tried to figure out if it was a prank ,but it wasn't .I saw the robot  move .I thought in my head it's a miracle . Since then the robot got bigger and bigger, until  I couldn't stop him .It destroyed the rest of the world along with my family.Now I regret every day what have I done now i'm alone.

Item_Response: 'Let's go eat!' yelled Mom. 'But, Mom, I'm sick, remember!' I cried from the couch. Jessica came over earlier to keep me company and knew I wasn't really sick. I was glad she din't say anthing. 'Fine, we will bring you back some egg rolls, stay here and do not go anywhere.' she said sternly as she and Dad walked outside to the car. As soon as door closed, I jumped up mand started yelling, 'Yes, yes, yes!' I and Jessica had planed this whole set up. I was not sick and now we were home alone and able top explore the house. My family had just moved in a few days ago, so we were ready to sneak around.       'Hey Isabel! Why don't we check the basement?' Jessica said. I responded by opening the trap door with a rickety ladder that leads down into the basement. I had to connect the string on the top of the door to the hook on the celing to keep it open. As we climed down, I began to rethink this whole plan. Here we were, climbing down into a small dark undiscovered room at the bottom of my house. I heard a thump when Jess hit the bottom. I fumbed around for a light switch. As it flickered on, I heard another thump. 'What was that?' I whispered. We both looked upward. The door, our only escape, had closed. The string had snapped, and the auto lock looked the door. The day we moved in, my parents had told me to always connect the string to the hook. I guess they hadn't expected the string to break.       We looked around for another door, but that was it. 'Why don't we make a robot?' Jessica said. She was holding up an old robot kit. I looked at the cover. Creat your own mini robot! it screamed in bold red letters. I dumped the contents on the floor. We connected all the pieces. The robot was a small little cube with wheels on the bottom and a control pannel on the top. I pressed one of the three buttons. The robot rolled forward, toward the lader. Sudenly, it started to climb up. It was small, but strong. It pushed it's little arms up and the trapdoor came open. It had been close to an hour since we got trapped, so we sprinted out. 'Can we be friends?' a voice said. We turned and looked at the robot in my hand. 'Yeah, sure.' we said in union. We took the robot upstairs and put him in my room. To this day he still stays in there. He even follows me to school. Eventually, we told my parents, and they joked that they were glad the robot didn't take over the house. We never did find out were the robot kit came from, and we never went back into the basement.

Item_Response: It was a stormy day for the state of Nevada and a 15 year old genius by the name of Cole was in need of something to do so he decided to build a robot. So that morning Cole went to the junkyard to collect some parts he found a some tin cans, a box of wire, a coat hanger, four small wheels used for a trycicle, a steering wheel, and a steel box. 'This should be enough.' Said Cole as he paid the man for the parts he needed.     When Cole finished his robot the robot was struck by lighting and began to move around on its own. Cole was terrified when the robot finally said 'Hi how are you im Bob.' Cole wanted to scream and run out of the house but realized that he had just made a real living robot with the help of lighting of course. He wasn't exactly sure how to react to his new invention so as the robot began to come towards him he decided to give Bob a hug. 'What is this hug you speak of, it feels... nice almost like a strong embrace from another.' 'Thats exactly it!' Screamed Cole as he tried to think of other things to show Bob. 'Hey lets go to the biggest rollercoaster in the country.' Exclaimed Cole as he already started to pack up. 'The only thing is that it's 6 hours away from here.' Said Cole as he put a frown on his face. 'I can fly there lickety split.' declared Bob. 'Okay then let's go' As they got to the rollercoaster Bob already began to get scared. So then Cole told him 'Hey being scared is part of having emotions so dont worry this is what I wanted you to do when you came to life.' 'Okay then I guess I don't have to be scared I should be, ah what's the I'm looking for.' 'Exited?' 'Yes! That's it thank you.' As they got on the rollercoaster Bob realized he didnt have to thata scared and rode the rollercoaster as hapily as can be.     After that day of emtions Cole and Bob became best friends and they went on many more adeventures. When Cole grew old Bob had to start taking care of, it was a good that Cole had taught him how to make homemade medicine with simp,e ingrediants. Unfortunately after Cole died Bob had no other uses and dismantled himself in Cloe's honor.

Item_Response: The Robot That Suddenly Comes Alive             A few months ago,I started building a robot that I named      Robette.Finally,after a few months of building,I was finished.But the thing is,I didn't build it to do anything,I just built it.But that all changed last night.                While I was busy eating,I heard a thumping sound coming from my room.Suddenly,everyone sitting at the table got very quite.Then I realized that they had heard the sound as well.My dad looked at me and said,'Why is there a thumping sound coming from your room?'I replied by saying that I didn't know.So I got up to go see what was going on but before I reached my room,I grabbed a bat-just to be safe.Slowly,I opened my bedroom door,and what I saw almost made me faint.                My robot was alive!I guess a must have put too much chemicals in it.As I tiptoed inside,the robot stopped moving around and looked directly at me.I was so shocked that I screamed,then the robot started screaming.Then the robot said,'Why are you screaming?'I said,'Because you're alive!''ell,of course I'm alive,'then she said,'I'm alive to help you out and to play with you.'                     At first I was a little nervous,then I realized that I'm pretty lucky to have a robot that is alive.After I explained everything to the still terrified people sitting at the table,my parents said that I didn't have to get rid of her.So for the rest of the night we sat in my room watching movies and playing games.I really enjoyed having a robot.

Item_Response: Billy              Ounce upon a time there was a robot named Billy.  He was a fun and interesting robot that had many uses and was very helpful.  He was created by a scientist who made him but when he didn't work accidentally threw him into a bucket of toxic waste and then he came alive.  It turned out that all it needed was toxic waste to jump start it and then it would work forever.  The robot is used to take care of animals and play with them and something that is cool is that he floats so that he doesn't step on any tails or paws.  Those are some of the aspects of Billy.              There is a lot more things you will want to know about Billy.  He also has multiple extendible arms that each have a different function, like one has a hose to fill up water bowls and another has a soft hand to pet the animals and another has a kind of rough side to scratch them.  Also he has a treat despencer inside of him so he can always give the animals treats.  He never needs to be recharged because the toxic waste makes it so he is charged forever and also he has a built in system that memorize the names of animals and a picture of them with every piece of information anyone could want that he can print out at any second.  Finally he plays with the animals and helps people pick out the perfect pet for them and helps teach them how to take care of it.  Those are just some of the features of Billy.              Billy can help you if you run a Shelter or if you just have a lot of pets.  He is very helpful if you are at work or away a lot because he is completely self sufficient and never needs to be recharged and can think on its own.  But if he does need help he has a build in phone that he can call you on and ask.  Another thing is he can go and buy things for your pet like food, treats, or other stuff we have a company that delivers pet stuff to Billy within 30 minutes.  Billy is the best robot helper you could have.

Item_Response: Robots              Robots today can be used in many different ways and are used to help people around the world. One robot called Mr. Gower helps in a hospital. All in all, I think robots are making a huge difference in the world today. With technology more robots will come to be and become more and more helpful around the globe.

Item_Response: Me and my freind kylie where talking about robots because both of us are interested in inventing one so we decided to try and make one.We both agreed to plan on making one that can help blind people since my Grandmother is blind but she is also alergic to dogs so she can not have a dog to help her also kylie's uncle is blind.We planned on first getting the materials to try and make this robot.We haven't quite thought about a name for it but we will and we will become famous if this actually worked!So we did research on how to make robots.We got all the materials we needed and started on the steps to make the robot and make sure the technology actually workes.We put it all together and programed it.But sadly we failed i thought we did it right but we did not have the right materials to make it help blind people so we did research again and found information on how to do but we worked on it all night.In the morning we discovered it did work,but did it help blind people?No it didn't so we took it to a professional who knew how to and he did it correctly and he worked on it and called us when he was done.So I called my grandmother and kylie called her uncle and we asked our mom to pick them up.We tested it on them,And guess what?IT WORKED! but we still have to come up with name for it.We kept saying silly names to play around but then we realized we need too seriously get working on the name.Then it hit me!The ihelper as in eye helper because it helps with people that are blind.We showed it too some of our freinds and they thought it is an amazing robot and said that we should show a scientist this so we did and thankfully we wrote down the steps we did.He contacted our parents and he said he will pay us for our invention it seemed so unreal so i pinched myself to see if i wasn't just a dream,but oviously it wasn't because it hurt.We made a deal he makes more of those but the credit goes to me and kylie witch is amazing!im so proud of myself and kylie hopefully in the future we can create more robots and other technology to help people and the enviorment.

Item_Response: The Living Stereo                           One sunny yet fresh day Stephanie and I were practicing our dance for the talent show in my frontyard.Every time we messed up we put the song all over again.We danced the song over twenty-five times, then that's when it happened.                        All of a sudden,our stereo started yelling 'Stop'! He told us that the song was getting really annoying and was on his last nerve.He yelled again ' You've played the song like a billion times already'. Very mad he said ' Can't I just relax when I want to'. I told him that apparently I could do whatever I wanted to because I owned the stereo.                                                                                                                               Then, he said 'I'm sorry I did not introduce myself, by the way my name is Bob'.'I think you can tell I am not very patient, at all'.'Also you might of noticed that I have some sort of anger issues'.'Will you two girls accept my apology and forgive me for being rude'?We said 'Yes of course we will Bob'.                          Finally,We both agreed that we already had to change Bob back to normal. Stephanie asked him'How will we be able to turn you back into a normal stereo'? Bob responded with 'I only turn like this when I get mad, so I got mad because you put the same song now mix up all the songs'.'Alright'we said 'then that will make him feel normal'.Before we knew it Bob was already gone , we did not even say bye.                     I will never forget that mean yet pretty nice Bob. That was the robot that came alive one day. Maybe I will bring Bob back another day.Also a little tip please do not try this at home.

Item_Response: 'We did it Jonathan'. 'We built a robot!' Dr. Callington and his assistant Jonathan, had been working on this robot for months. 'What will we name it?' asked Jonathan. Dr. Callington thought for a moment.'We shall name it KK-3.' 'Lets turn it on.' Jonathan pushed the on button, and KK-3 popped to life. 'What did you program him to do?' Jonathan questioned. 'I programed him to to mix characteristics of animals together. And if anything goes wrong, he has a laser beam on his head.' Dr. Callington replied excitedly.                                                          The next day, business as usual, Jonathan opened the cupboared that KK-3 was stored in.  He got KK-3 out, but it wouldn't work. Jonathan then realized he forgot to turn it on. He got a shock when he pressed the button, and KK-3 fell apart. 'Uhhhh..... Dr. Callington, I think KK-3 is broken.' 'WHAT!? DO YOU KNOW HOW LONG AND HARD WE WORKED ON THIS??!!' 'Yess...bbut' Jonathan started, but then realized Dr. Callington was laughing. 'That's not the real KK-3.' 'I am.'       'Dr. Callington' tore his face off, reavealing the shiny metal head of KK-3. He laughed a truly mechanical laugh, and shot a sigle laser through some science formulas, burning a hole clean through them. 'What ddid yyou ddo wwith Dr. Callingtonn?' Jonathan stammered. 'I put him.... why would I tell you that?' 'Because I helped create you.' 'Fine. He's in the animal testing room. Good luck trying to get there.' The animal testing room was on the other side of the lab, meaning Jonathan would have to go through about 3 doors. He was pretty sure he could outrun the robot, but not the laser. KK-3 shot at random, while Jonathan ran and hid, only to have his hiding place blasted away. He ran for the door. He made it just in time. Since KK-3 didn't have the best aim, it was now shooting down parts of the ceiling. Jonathan had already made it to the ATR, while KK-3 was still getting through the rubble that he caused.       When KK-3 made it to the ATR, Jonathan still hadn't found Dr. Callington.The robot had learned his lesson about shooting things, and now he started to glow. 'What else could KK-3 do?' Jonathan couldn't remember. A hologram of a kangaroo tore away from the actual kangaroo. The same thing happened with a tiger. The holograms got closer and closer. Now Jonathan remembered. KK-3 could mix animals. The holograms collided, and left a new animal, body of a kangaroo, head of a tiger. The tigeroo kicked Jonathan until he was out cold, and then delivered the death bite. Dr. Callington had been killed, vaporized by the laser, so Jonathan could not find him.

Item_Response: My Robot Joe    I was in my room one day. When all the sudden I heard a tapping on the window. I looked out and there was a robot. I asked him what he wanted. He said he needed a place to hide from the FBI. I asked why. He said the people who created were going to shut him down, because they think he is trying to destroy all of man kind. He said he wasn't. That he had been framed by an enemy of the name X12-FTY.       So I let him in. After, he said he was really hungry so I went downstairs to get him a grilled cheese sandwich and a juice box. He thanked me for my hospitality. I said your welcome ( even though I didn't know what that meant ). After He asked me what I would do if the world was taken over by robots? I answered I would gang up and try to beat the robots. Our name would be The Resistance       Then he said somthing into his arm  like he was communicating with someone. Then he turned to me asked me if my name was Tyrone? I said yes. Out of no where here pulled this super big shooty laser. He said 'You must be terminated for you are the leader of the Resistance.' I tried to to block the laser with my plastic pirate sword. Lucky for me the lasers weakness is plastic. The laser rebounded of the sword and   melted the robot.

Item_Response: Rockey               It was just an ordinary day. No one thought robots where something of our time, however of the future. I'm an inventor and I've been fooling with parts ever since a kid. My long life dream.... to make a robot that comes alive.             I've done drawings  for weeks, looking for the right materials for days, and wondering where to start for years. In my garage this morning I decided to use one of the old blueprints I made yesterday, it was of a robot that was 3 feet tall, and was silver with black wheels to move it around. It was just a box robot.             I decided to go to the junkyard to find some materials. I see old refrigerators, tires, cabinets, stoves, and even some cars. None of it seemed right. Until I walked into a pile of mulch which had a metal box on it that was hollow and silvery. It looked perfect.                                                         1 Hour later               Well I'm back in the garage I snatched a bunch of materials and I've built the entire body so far. I need to put in some wiring and get some help too.   I  called up my brother he says he knows how to wire things well and thinks he can do it for the robot tomorrow.                  Well my brother is here in the same garage with a whole lot of wires that I don't know what thy do. He started stretching cutting and tying things. Sometimes he asked for the red or blue wire or simply grunted about something he was doing. After hours of work he said ' Should work now!' He flipped a switch and not anything.               He went to the store and came back with more wiring and a computer chip thing he placed it in did more wiring and programming turned the switch..... And   nothing. He said he'd come back tomorrow.             I woke up during the night hearing a loud bank of what seemed to be old tools.   Clank Clank! I walked in the garage and there he was the robot we put together.   This was the moment I had been waiting for all my life. I dashed into the house grabbed a phone and dialed my brother up to come over and see now!                He was here in minutes. He told me everything was working perfectly he could walk talk and even  learn new things. We knew we would be famous for the robot we named   Rockey.                                                                        THE END

Item_Response: shayla hurt       LA                                        The different kinds of robots                    robots come in different shape,size,color and can do different things.there are a lots of robots that help people for a lot of different purposes.These robots are here to help make peoples jobs easier  for them.There are five different robots that do very good things,but I'm only going to talk about four.       The Gemini-Scout was invented to work in under-ground mines and farms.the robot is small but is very strong.when they robot finds trapped miners it can use its two-way radio to talk with rescue teams.If someone gets hurt it will drag the person to safety ,and it can also carries food water and other supplies that you need it to carries thing .The Gemini-Scout is very good help it can help with a lot of different things.       The Dante 2 was invented to climb into volcanoes to gather information for scientist.It is  very good with high heat so it will survive.It looks for hole,vents,and craters, then it collects the information about gases that came out the vents.Now scientist can study volcanoes.       The Mr.Gower was invented to work in hospitals helping doctors and nurses bring medicine to patients.The body has a stack of locked drawers for stored medicine.it rides on elevators and steers through the hallway to get what ever you need.Its so strong that it can pull 500 pounds at one time.It can also deliver medicine for twelve hours without stopping.           The Agribots is a robot that picks fruit.Its very good with farms.Its really not popular but the framers really like it .It now when a fruit is ripped,and when a plant is becoming dead it will water it and take care of it.It picks fruit up with its mechanical hands.           All of there robots are very useful we need to keep making them so they can do different things,and now scientist can keep doing there work

Item_Response: It was summer break,' Mom,' I yelled,' Can I have my friends come over?'        My mom replied,' Of course you can't Jordan,' (that was my name) This was the start of the reason of why I decided to build a robot (to have a friend all the time that always has time to play with me, since I don't have a sibling) and building a robot was easy to me because I studied all about it, but little did I now that trouble was awaiting me.        The next day, I went to the garage to find some parts because my dad was a mechanic. The second reason I looked in the garage was because the garage was a big room of junk and broken stuff which could go well for the robot. In the garage, I found batteries, the robots head, (which was from a broken toy robot) the robots body, (a not functional paper shredder because I had nothing to use) and the robots legs, (which were also from a broken robot) but no arms. I decided that I should look somewhere else because I couldn't find the arms so through the entire house and found nothing, but I still kept going and I didn't lose hope.        After a while,'That is it, I give up, I looked everywhere,' I thought. Then I remembered the time I got a bunch of claw grabbers as a prize, which was really convenient, but my mom kept it in a cabinet because it was to dangerous and she let nobody use it. That cabinet was in my mom and dad's room so I would have to sneak in and grab two for my robot. When I went in sneakily, I was really lucky that it wasn't locked so I opened the cabinet and I grabbed two cranes, but I was wondering why the cabinet wasn't locked even though the cabinet had a lock and why there were almost no more?        I started to assemble the robot, which I did in my room so no one would notice, which started with the legs. Second, I taped the paper shredder and the head together with the legs to make the robot. Lastly, I put the arms and I realized that the batteries were not needed because there was no where to put it.        Even though it didn't come alive I could imagine if it did, but one second later, it came alive! I couldn't believe my eyes when I saw it moving its arms and legs. It looked different than usual, but it didn't really matter. First, I thought that it was awesome how it could play with me, but I, then, stared panicking because I didn't know what would happen if my parents found out. I looked back at the robot, but to my surprise, the robot was gone!        I went down stairs to find the robot, but it did not take long to find the robot destroying everything! I realized that I should show it how to do stuff that is destructive so it won't destroy everything in my house. I started teaching the robot outside like how not to blast everything in sight and how he shouldn't run in the middle of the street, but the robot did anyway and was lucky that a car didn't come and run over the robot or if the robot pulverized it. after a long time of teaching, the robot learned nothing and I was at another hopeless situation.        Later that day, I saw an army van that stopped at our house and saw my robot. A man came down and asked,' Is that your robot because we are looking for a robot that looks just like that one.' I was worried because this guy looks like he is from the army and I think I am in trouble, but I tried to speak as calmly as I could.        ' This is my robot,' I replied.        ' Does this robot of yours destroy everything it sees?'        ' Yes, it does.'        ' That robot is ours which we trained to destroy everything.'        ' OK, I'll get him out right away sir.' After awhile, I came out with him and I gave him the robot and he said thank you and went away.        I went back home and I realized that the house was a wreck and I heard the garage open. I went up stairs and after a while I heard,' Jordan! Come down!'        'I knew I was going to be in trouble.' I thought.

Item_Response: The story starts the morning McKenzy woke up. She was tested on for week and has gotten a little bit of food and no sleep she was allowed 24 hours of sleep before she starts training.       McKenzy, wake up! Fear wound me up tight. My 'bot was ordering me and I had no choice but to follow its commands. I was on a metal table with a white cloth draped across my body; hooked at the ends. This is what they call a bed? I wondered. Let me getchya caught up on the amazing, wildly fun, and very intresting (aka the worst week of my life!) travels of McKenzy Zyban!       I turned 16 a week ago (yay!) Same week that I was abducted by the Starr minions (could it have waited? no.) Taken to Starr Inc. (would have been a dream come true if I wasn't covered with a black cloth and knocked unconcious) Experimented on (that's just sick!) Got a 'bot brain plungend into mine (yuck!) have been having hallucinations for the past 3 days (One of the mant treats you get when you are sharing a body with a robot) have not slept until now (which I have only 24 hours to do) I'm aching all over (ugh!)   The door to the room opened and a young male walked in with a tray of food and some clothes.        'I managed to snag some clothes and food for you Kenzy,' he said in a low voice. His name was Jalen, I remember that much. As soon as his name came up so did a flash of pictures my robot brain has saved. He had olive skin and dark eyes. He almost never smiles and he cares for me like he did to his little daughter, who abandoned him for Mr. Starr. He still had that depressed look in his eyes.        He unhooked the covers and handed me the clothes. I put on the white tanktop and the white sweatpants and the grey sweatshirt my mother gave to me on my birthday (they let ust keep one thing from home).        I stole a quick glance at Jalen and saw his hunched shoulders. There were tiny gray hairs mixed in with his rich black hair. When he turned to get some of the food I saw that his mouth was turned slightly down. Not that he smiles anyway.        'It will be okay,' I promised, although I don't even have control of my own destiny. I put my hand on his shoulder and gently jerked him around so he was facing me. I looked deep into his eyes like I was finding a portal into his mind. He gave me a small nod and went back to preparing the food.        I slid onto the table and got to work on my shoes. I unlaced the combat boots and frowned when they didn't fit. Would it be a suicide mission to get boots that fit!? I wondered. I slid them on and went to the makeshift bathroom. It had a sink and a mirror. There was a small latch on the wall for the door to the toilet. I went up to the sink and quickly washed last night off my face and watched it rid my face of impurities. I slung my dark brown hair into a slick, high ponytail. I stared at my reflection. just a week ago I was a regular girl with thin, dark brown hair and pale sea blue eyes. Now, my hair was longer and bigger and my eyes were multicolored. That's the sign of a robo brain. I covered my face with my hands and spoke to my robot.         Listen, robo brain, I- I began        It's not 'robo brain' its Marlene! She snapped        Sorry, Marlene, I apologized I just wanted to know if training was at 9 or at 10.        You have 5 minutes. Go! she replied. I looked down at my watch, 5 minutes till nine. 9 it is. I snatched a peice of toast from the tray Jalen prepped. He was sitting on the table with a plate of eggs. I did not have the time nor the energy to scold him on how that was supposed to be my food. I burst through the door and sprinted down the hallway.       <><><><><><><><><><>       McKenzy has been working for hours in the training studio and has master some self defense kicks and punches. She has become an exceptional Covert Operation learner and is mastering mental preparedness. She was conditioning with her trainer when she is called to Mr. Starr's office.               I walked into Mr. Starr's office and took a seet in the plush brown chair I looked intently at the white desk and traveled up to mr. Starr's eyes. When he needs to 'talk' to you, you don't really talk. He signaled a gaurd to come. He leaned in and told him something. The guard glanced my way and locked eyes with me. I guped. The gaurd gave a terse nod. He walked over to me and grabbed my arm. There was a slot there for chip implants. Mr. Starr took a chip out of his compuer and handed it to the guard. The gaurd shoved it in and I let a little yelp escape my mouth. I slupped into the chair with my eyes closed. I felt no jostle to wake me up. Suddenly I bolted up right and my arm fell to my side.        'Process complete' I said without thinking. It was in a monotonous voice. I shoved the chair back and exited without a word. I walked down the hallway.       <><><><><><><><><><>       It is the next and McKenzy is off to training. Last night she had a test to do and is sore and drained (they took 1/2 a pint of blood to see how the electricity is reacting to the blood). she was halfway there when she was intercepted by Dillan and Penelope, the youngest recrutes coming in at only 5 years-old. They took McKenzy to a room at the back side f the facilility. McKenzy kept telling them to let her go and tell her where they were taking. Their reply was alway no. When they walked into the room They were joined by a tall girl and boy. She had ice blond hair and he had wind-blown dirty blond hair. They interogated her for an hour until they finally came to the conclusion that she would help them. Help them take down Mr. Starr.             'So, I'm supposed to just waltz in there and steal the mainDrive?' I asked.        Tanner sighed and ran his hands through hi hair. 'No!' he exclaimed. ' We will distract him and you sneak in and get the mainDrive. you will then plug it into the computer and delete the robot brain funcion. themn meet us at the entry. Got it?' I nodded. 'Good. meet us back her in the morning, okay?' he asked as he surveyed the faces of the people in front of him. We all nodded. he nodded to and held out his fist. The tall girl, Ryder, stacked it on top. Dillan and penelope stacvkedtheres and I beckoned me to do the same. Tanner moved his ontop of mine and and Ryder ontop of his and so forth. When it was back to order they then tapped each other's wrists and left soundlessly. As walked the lpng hallway, Marlene spoke to me.        Its your mission. Do you choose to accept it        Do I?       <><><><><><><><><><>       That morning, McKenzy comes back to the room. she meets up with the others and they prep her on what she has to do. They warn her that there is a system that sendas a warning out if there is something dangerous. They then part and McKenzy is alone. She hides behind a wall and awaits for her comrades to set off the diversion. When it goes off she aces in to fing the drive. when she does she jams it into the computer and disables the brains. she races out just as the alarm sounds. Gaurds come at her from all sides and feels like giving up. She then musters up her strength and kicks the first guard. She grabs a pole above her and kicks the next 2 guards. She drops on the next one and punches the next two. When they are all down she races down the hall to get to the exit when she sees it someone grabs her and pulls her back. She struggles to break loose but is able to she kicks her attaker in the gut and doesn't even look to see who it was. She runs to the exit and sees ryder. All i have to do is cross the threshold and I'm free. she tells herself. 3 feet. She picks up th speed. 2 feet. She lets out a breath. 1 foot! She leaps out of the facitiy just as it erupts in flames. She's Finally free!!

Item_Response: One perfect afternoon in Stevenson Ranch, Jeff was riding his bike down the street when suddenly out of the corner of his eye, he saw some silver shining object sticking out of the the ground on the side of the road.Naturally his instinct was to go and investigate, so he did and what he saw made his heart stop... He saw a Gemini Scout robot, the last of its kind. This could be a great discovery if it turned on. So Jeff went home and the next day came back with battery's and put them into the slot on the robots arm.This was the moment of truth, will it turn on or will he be disappointed, and what he saw shocked him...IT TURNED ON! This was a great moment but the question was what was he going to do with it. How was he going to persuade his parents to let him keep him if he wanted to keep him, so that led him to his next question, does he talk.'Hello', Jeff said to the big pile of rusted metal,(only his arm that was sticking out was shiny).And to his surprise a mumble came out of the robot. 'mmmm mmmm,' It was just a mumble, but can it get words out, he tried again,'hello,' said Jeff. And out of nowhere the robot replied,'hello'. Jeff thought that the battery's wont last long so they went home.         'IM HOME', shouted Jeff.The only thing on his mind was persuading his parents to keep the robot, so after hours of arguing and debating he finally got the yes from his parents.And even though that moment was exciting he still had two things on his mind, how do you care for a robot, and the ROBOT POLICE,They hunt down and lock up every robot they see because they think that there bad.         After the hours of researching how to care for a robot it was time to go to sleep, and as he was closing his eyes he heard the most terrifying thing he could hear, the robot police.He knew he couldn't just not answer so when he did they asked him the expected question,'have you seen a robot recently,'   'No', he replied   'Ok well have a good night then'   Jeff thought to himself that that could have gone very bad.         In the morning when Jeff woke up he knew that the robot police would be back soon and he would have to be more prepared. And out of nowhere when he least expects it they were there again and they looked like they had found something, (which they did.) When he went to answer the door scared out of his mind the robot police told him to give up his robot and when he went to go and get him they were shocked by the sight that they saw, they knew how rare it was and replied,'where did you find this robot,'   He replied,'just on the side of the road,'   The officer replied with,'this robot belongs in a museum.'   'why'? Jeff replied with   'this is one of the rarest robots in history'!   Jeff thought to himself, if he should let him go or keep him (not like it was his choice).   The office said,'we are going to take him and put him in a museum'.   So Jeff just went with it and said,'Ok.'   And from that day forward he remembered that he had found one of the best historical finds in his time.

Item_Response: Alive?!!!   'Let's Go, Mom, we're going to be late!', I yelled. It was my 12th birthday and we were going to Jump 51-50. I invited 6 girls from school, including my very best friend, Taylor. When we reached Jump 51-50 I leaped out of the car and greeted everyone there waiting. They all handed me my presents and I was so excited. We all went in and played for 2 and a half hours. Everybodies parents picked them up except for Taylor's, she was coming back to the house with me, to open up all of the presents.       When we walked into the house, having to make 2 trips for the presents we went up into my room. Taylor wanted me to open up her present last. First, I opened up Julia's present, it was a nail polish set. The 5th present was from Emily, it was an itunes giftcard.       'Now the moment we've all been waiting for', Taylor announced. I quickly ripped  up the wrapping and stared at the gift plainly. It was a metal robot.       I didn' t want to make Taylor feel bad so I said 'Thank you'.   'I know you don't like it', Taylor replied.   'I do, I really do', I exclaimed.       'Well, that's not really my gift', Taylor said, 'this is'. I   unwrapped the gift as fast as a cheetah.       'O, MY GOSH!', I screamed. It was 5 tickets to 1 Direction.   I couldn't help my self but squeeze her.       'Ding, Dong', it was Taylor's mom ringing the doorbell. I picked up the robot and placed it on the floor of my closet. I followed Taylor down the stairs and said thank you to Mrs. Valdez, Taylor's mom. Taylor left, and it was already 8:30, so I decided to go to sleep, because it was a long day.    When I woke up I could smell waffles and bacon. It was the first day of summer vacation! When I opened my eyes I saw the robot I had put in my closet the night before.       'Mom', I immeditally yelled. NO ANSWER!!!   'Dad', I screamed. NOTHING AGAIN!!! I jumped out of my bed.       'Good morning, is everything okay'?, questioned the robot. Without answering I ran into Cassidy's bedroom, woke her up and explained what has happened. She hopped out of her bed and sprinted into my room.       'Hello, what do you want'?, Cassidy calmly asked the robot.       'What do you mean, I am Claire's best friend', the robot replied.       'How did you get out of that box?', I said pointing to the floor.       'Easy, I used my scissors', the robot exclaimed.       'What is your name?', Cassidy questioned.       'McKenzie', the robot answered. McKenzie, showed me and Cassidy everything she could do. She was awesome. We played for hours together, because she could make anything I   said appear and tranform into anything.       I ran to the phone, which was ringing, 'Hello mom, you'll never believe this, there is a robot named McKenzie that Taylor gave me for my birthday and it could talk and do everything I tell it to do.'   'Wow, I'll be home in 2 minutes', my mom said sarcastically. I told McKenzie that my mom would be home in a minute. I also told her my mom loved oatmeal raisin cookies, so she got a plate and put a bunch of oatmeal cookies on a plate. When my mom got home McKenzie handed her the plate. My mom wouldn't accept them. Cassidy came down and greeted my mom.   'Claire, may I speak to you in the kitchen?', my mom asked.   I obviously said yes.       'Claire, I want this robot to leave, who knows what it's planning?', my mom said.       'Mom, she is completly harmful, she is so sweet and she is not planning anything', I explained.       'Claire Bridget Johnson, you better listen to me and make this robot leave by next week!', my mom shouted. I stormed away and ran into my room. McKenzie joined me and calmed me down. She gave me some oreos. I told her everything my mom had said, and she understood. I also told her we needed to come up with a plan so my mom would let her stay.   I heard a knocking on my door and said 'Who is it?'       'Cassidy', Cassidy replied. 'Are you really upset', she asked.       'Yeah', I said. She explained to me mom just wants me to be safe. I already knew that. McKenzie left and went down to my mom, she came back in 2 hours and said that she was allowed to stay as long as she wanted to. I had no idea what she said but my mom came up and told me she was sorry. She said McKenzie was a great role model. I agreed with her and we had a group hug. McKenzie gave us all ice-cream.

Item_Response: I felt something behind me,staring at me as I turned I saw this big robot trying to attack me I tried to make a run for it but the robot was too fast, he was just about to grab me when I woke up to being drenched in sweat.It was just a dream from the horror movie I watched the night before,I glanced over at my alarm clock it was eight o'clock.......school!As I rushed out the door from the corner of my eye I thought I saw a shadow move I looked over,nothing.I walked into the office and got my late slip,but when I got into my classroom things got wierd.The sky became dark and the wind blowed like crazy,making the fall leaves go everywhere.Just then the lights began to flicker and the windows flew open my teacher walked over and closed them.My walk home was normal and the wind stopped blowing,But when I got home I found something unusual.After I finished my home work I decided to look around in the attic to find some old antics,but what I found was way better.As I moved some things around something shiny flashed my eyes, ow I said I walked toward the shiny antic. It was a ball, a big golden ball I was just about to put it back when it formed into a tiny robot but for some reason I knew he was good.He spoke and said;Hello my name is Steve.I greeted him back and said;Hello steve,my name is a.j.So where did you come from I asked,I don't know said Steve I got amnisia on the way in a strange transportation that landed in your backyard.IN MY BACKYARD! I hollered.I looked out the window of my room and saw a huge space ship,I've got to get rid of that ship before my parents get home I mumbled.Suprised that Steve heard me he said; don't worry along the way after I bumped my head I found this remote for the space ship, as I pressed the buttons they each did different things and one of them made it invisable.He pressed a button and the space ship was gone see Steve replied.Okay that problem is solved but what about you?What about me? Oh you mean if your parents will see me, that's easy I'll just stay up here in the attic.Will you be ok up here alone with no food or water.Well I can't have water because I'm made of electronic things, and I can't eat human food.Then what will you eat?he pulled out a bag from his pouch that he has to carry stuff, after my injury I found this it said ''Alien food ''on it.Okay but if you need anything just stomp once and I'll be there.Three weeks past not a stomp but a.j just figured he was sleeping so he didn't bug him.Finally he decided that he missed his friend and that he would wake him up.He walked normal up the stairs so his parents wouldn't be suspicious.When he opened the attic door he whispered;Steve,he said it a little louder ;Steve.Finally he opened the door all the way and he found a note. The note said;Dear a.j I'm so sorry but I've found my family and I'm now in outer space I didn't get my memory vack but I will always remember you,your friend Steve.THE END.

Item_Response: The Robot        One day scientist named Dr. Robert built a robot to have as a guard for his old tower which he had found when he ran away from his town to secretly do his work. He built the robot out of old armor he found in the tower which he had polished and some wire from is science lab. The robot was strong and carried a heavy ax and a heavy sword the scientist found in the tower. The scientist knew that the military would kill him if he found his location. He was an illeagal scientist who practiced illeagal sciences. that knight the scientist turned the robot on and it did something unexpected. He first threw the scientist against the wall and then stabbed him withe the sword. before the scientist could say anything he cut off his head with the ax. The military heard something and went to the tower. there they met the robot who killed all of them. the robot preceaded to the town which he killed many innocent people. Then finally a man came witha shotgun and a bayonette. It was a survivor from the army. he tried shooting the robot but failed. Then he saw the robots weak spot and took the bayonette, jumped on the robot and stabbed it in the back of neck. The soldire became a hero and was promoted general.

Item_Response: 'Brrriiiinnnnggg!' My alarm clock shouted at me. I quickly shut it off and groggily got out of my comfy twin sized bed. Today was the day. The day I got to work with my father.        'Honey! Go get ready!' My father shouts from downstairs. I lazily made my way to my bathroom and brushed my teeth.        'Circle, circle, circle.' I thought while I moved the brush in a circular motion over my teeth. 'Pancakes are circles. Man...I'm hungry. I want some pancakes.'        When I finished brushing my teeth I got dressed into my white, over the shoulder top, black tights, and my black and white vans. I grabbed my phone and headed downstairs.        'Good morning Roxy.' My mother said while handing me a plate filled with pancakes and some orange juice.        'Good morning mom.' I replied.        'Hurry up and eat because we have to get to my work at 9:00 sharp.' My father exclaimed, chewing on a pancake. I checked the time. '8:45' The clock said in big red letters.        When I was done eating my delicious pancakes, I picked up my phone and headed over to the car where my dad was waiting. He started the car and we drove off.        'So dad, where exactly is you're work? What do you even do?'        'I work across the street from the mall. I make robots and other new inventions.' He replied.        'Robots? You make robots?!' I nearly shouted at him.        'Indeed. They are actually very helpful. They help doctors, explore volcanoes, they can even play with you!'        As I thought about what he said, my mind started to think about the whole 'robot' invention. What do they even look like? I soon started to doze off.        'Roxy, wake up. We are here.' I heard my dad say in a sweet, angelic tone. I stepped out of the car.        'Whoa.' I said as I examined the gigantic building in front of my short, 13 year old body. As i walked closer, it was incredible. The silver tone, the amazing structure, the large glass dome on top. This place was unbelievable. My dads voice soon shot me out of awe.        'Honey, let's go.' He said a few steps ahead of me. As I walked inside a breeze of cold air gushed towards me, making me fall back a little. I gained backed my balanced and continued to walk down the, also, silver hall. We soon reached this large vault with a holographic keypad.         'Whoa.' I repeated. My dad entered the code and the vault door unlocked.        'You seem to be saying that a lot today.' He said with a grin on his face. We walked in to be greeted with chaos. People were running around holding different gismos and gadgets, there were people crowding around a small silver and,what seemed to be, blue figure.        'Mr. Smith we need you're help! Something is wrong!' A bald man shouted at my father.                                                                         My father ran over and started picking up all these tools. I stood there awkwardly and about 30 seconds after, my father finally looked up from his work and saw me.                                                       'Oh. I'm sorry Roxy. Just go to the gadget room and I'll be done in a second.' He pointed to a metal door. I started to walk over, but tripped on a dropped screwdriver.  While I was falling I hit a blue button. I don't think it will do any harm. I stood up and checked my knee. Great, I got a scrape. Oh, just jolly, it's bleeding too! Note the sarcasm. I limped over to the gadget room and saw what looked like a piece of metal. I examined it for about 10 seconds, but it suddenly started freaking out and moving around. I abruptly stepped back and watched it freak out. When it was calmed I walked back up and examined it.                                                                                                'Hello?' I said to it. A dash of fear is my voice.                                  'Hello Earthling. I am HTP-276. And you?' It replied in a robotic, Siri like, tone.                                                                                'Oh. Um. I'm Roxy.' I replied kind of freaked out. It wheeled over to me and observed my scrape.                                                           'I see you have a scrape. I will bandage it.' It bandaged my cut.        'Oh OK. Thanks.' I said.                                                                        'Do you like to shop? We shall go to the mall.' It said. I suddenly liked this robot a lot. I nodded my head in agreement and we went off to the mall.                                                                                                                               When we got back, I was sore. I can't believe my dad didn't notice I was gone. Sadly, it was time to go. I said my goodbyes to everyone and HTP-276. As soon as we got home, I ran to my bed and slept. Today was crazy, but I can't wait to go to my dads work again.

Item_Response: When you hear the word robot, you are probabaly refering to a bad robot. But not all the time, cause robots can be very helpful instead of evil. Here is a story on a robot that suddenly came to earth in the 1930's.       In exactly 1934 a robot named AGR, unexspectingly landed in Santa Clarita, CA. AGR standed for, Advanced Gaming Rover. Scientist toke this robot and studied it. This robot was put in a room with nothing for 3 years. And in 1937 a man named theodore went in that room with the robot and discoverd that it was a nice robot. But the man didnt know what it really did.       Next the man put this robot to work. The robot could realy do anything. It could fly, swim, and even clim up walls. This robot is four feet tall, and it could go as fast as a Bugatti. The robot could make alot of things, houses, cars, money, soda, and even a plane. As years went by theodore died. So the robot went to work for the fire department. One day a building fell. They put Rover to the test. After he was done he ended up saving seventy- six peoples lives. After that happend Rover was a prosperous robot. He was involed in every situation. Then in 1967, scientist wanted to know how he did all of the stuff he did. They did a quick research on rover. When it was over scientist discoverd magnificent things about rover. He has a special magnet in his body that tracks peoples iron in thier blood.They also figured out that he could build a nucular bomb, and he did.       Finaly Rover died in 1999, no one knows how he died. They ended up having a day named Rover in honnor for his bravery. Without rover the world will never be the same. Everyone hopes a new robot will come very soon.

Item_Response: The factory was a disaster, broken fragments of walls and glass all over the place. My anger escaped me as I glared furiously at a rouge robot that was slightly damaged. I channeled all my anger into one last blow to destroy the robot. As rose, laser in my hand, aiming at the robots main controlling system and fired when a large green orb appeared around the robot. The orb deflected my shot shooting it back with an astonishing force that hit me in the chest. I had controll of my conciousness for a second then blacked out hitting the floor with a sickening crack while the stealthy robot snuck in the shadows.                   The year was 2035 where robots did everything. A human, as the robots called them, didnt even have to get off the couch if they wanted to go to bed, a robot would just carry them with padded hands so not to disturb the person they were carrying. Everyone was this lazy except for me. I was 13 and did everything myself and worked out and ran around the neighborhood reguarly. I didnt want to become, for all he money in the world, a fat blubbering walrus like the rest of the people in the world. I wouldn't like not being able to get up on my own and have a robot help me because i wasn't capable. These are the kind of things im against and that is why every morning my robot would try to help me up and I would defy it and make it go away for a while. Not being able to disobey orders, the robot leaves my room in a routine process. Robots were useful for some things like refilling your water bottle if there was no water nearby and I was thirsty. Small reasons like this are the only reason I keep mine around. I don't know why but for some reason I don't trust the mechanical beings.            I stayed fit for years before finnaly deciding I needed a purpose in my life. I didnt need a job because robots could produce however much money ou wanted. I was disgusted by that because I wanted the expirence of having a job and responsibility's. I knew was smart enough. Walking around town one day i saw a peculiar shop that said 'first ever robot run shop' it was called Weapons and Excesories. Mildly curious I walked inside where a robot greeted me and said 'would you like to try the weapon of the day?' 'Sure' I replied since I had nothing better to do. He handed me a small lazer gun that I had never seen before. It fit perfectly in my hand! The robot then took me out to the back of the store where it had a shooting range set up. There were 3 targets: a fake squirell that was 20 yards away, a fake blujay that was 200 yards away and a fake raccoon that was 500 yards away. Before the robot left he handed me a sniper edition of the lazer gun so I could hit the targets that were far away. Taking aim through the scope I focused about a half a centimeter above the raccoons head and fired. I missed! I took aim again a little lower and fired again. I missed again as i watched the aqua blue lazer fly past the raccoons right ear. Out of frustration I took aim directly on he raccoon's head. When I pulled the trigger almost intantly the raccoon exploded into millions of pieces leaving the base were it was held in a fiery inferno. 'Oh.' I said dumbly as i realized that the lazer was so fast that all you had to do was aim right on your target and it would hit. Quickly I took aim with the pistol and destoed the squrriel in a similar way. The pistol fired red lazers that suprisingly hit the squirell and insead of blowing it up melting into a red pool of boiling liquid. I began to take intrest in the robots craftmenship as I suddenly felt a little tired.            Walking back inside the shop the robot asked me if I had liked the test shots. I replied with a weary 'Yes'. 'Ah, you must be a little tired' the robot continued 'what I didn't tell you wasthat the weapon takes as much energy that it does if you were destroying it yourself.'. 'Great' I replied slumping over on a workbench suddenly much more tired than before. 'So for instance, if you had a really piled up amount of anger, hate, resentment, or were just really rested that day you would have more energy to use it'.  he rattled on as I lay doubled over on the bench suddenly feeling sick. 'how many shots did you take' he queried. '4' I replied. I can't tell if robots have suprise in their voice but if there was this was definetly the time I noticed it because the robot 'O my, the most I have taken without running out of energy was 3!' He continued to mutter to himself and I caught little bits and pieces of what he was saying like 'To think that a human could be stronger than a robot!'. A couple seconds later he replied and said 'You should be heading home'. I stopped his attempted motions to push me out the door with a difiant 'Wait!', 'how much do you want for the weapons' I said. The robot turned and returned with the pistol and Sniper versions of the lazer gun and said 'You are the first to come to my store and purchase so I will not charge you in electrobytes. All I want you to do is go home rest and be safe with these extremely dangerous weapons.' 'Okay' I hastily replied as I let my robot carry me home. For once I wasa happy that I had the robot to carry me home and praised him the second I was in my bed and drifted off to sleep.            The next day when I woke I again defied my robot's assistance and climbed out of bed fingering the weapons on my dresser. When I got outside robots were roaming the streets. I jumped in surprise as one pointed a metal finger at me and said 'your doom is coming soon'. That sounded more like a prophecy than a statement and quickly closed the door saying in my room the rest of the day. The next day the robots were still patrolling the srteets and confused asked my robot wat was going on and after he declared that he didn't know I ordered him to get me the highest quality armor at the weapon store. looking through my window at the robots I began to see some of their eyes glowing red hot like embers in a fire. almost insantly my robot returned to my room with a metal chestplate, leggings and a helmet which I quickly slipped on. He also produced 5 half yellow half green bolts of some sort. 'The robot manager at the store said you might need these due to the robot infestation but he said only to use them in dire need.' 'What happened' I asked 'The Director of the RMC, robot manufacturing company, shut down the factory. All of these robots have gone rouge swearing revenge on him if they find him.' 'Thats great' I said loading my lazer sniper with the new bolts. going to the window I took aim at a rouge robot and fired.             At first I thought it did nothing then after a second a shock wave began to progress through the lines of the robots disabling them all one by one. All had been disabled except for one that looked at me. It was larger than the others and had lots of weapons. It fired a rocket while my robot put up a sheild to protect me but got knocked backward into my bedroom wall in the process. I was a little angry that the large robot had  damaged mine. I walked outside with my pistol in hand and turned toward it facing it like it was a quickdraw in the old west movies. I drew, fired and hit the robot in the chest catching it off gaurd and doing a little damage but not melting it. It fired at me slicing through my armor and grazing my arm.I fired again and again until I was low on ammunition. Deciding it was no use I crept back inside. I decided to go around the back of my house and take refuge in someone elses house so the 1 rouge robot would't find me. Creeping along at the pace of a snail I finally reached my destination. As soon as I went through the back door, which I dicovered that was open, my jaw dropped to the ground.            The house was in ruins; bookshelves, doors, clothes,walls to bedrooms, and couches flipped upside down and torn to shreds cluttered the ground. Exploring a little further by going up the ragged stairs I looked around for anything useful or any sign of a human that once lived here. After discovering nothing I went back downstairs to hear a dull 'Thump' 'Thump' in one of the closet doors. I walked up to it for a second drew my weapon and flung the door open. Out fell a lean man that was bound and gagged. Blood dripped across his face as he hit the floor with a cry. Untying him but still keeping my weapon at the ready I noticed a patch on his right shoulder. It read 'Manager of RMC'! Dumbsrtuck I realized that the Robots had attacked this man because he shut down the manufacturing company that was making more robots. Groggily the man began to sit up and mutter something uncomprehendable. About 5 minutes passed before began to make some sense. I heard small parts like 'robots!' and 'no!'. Curious I waited for the man to recover enough to share his story. But as soon as he saw me he jumped back in suprise and hit his head on a table leaving him unconcious again. Not deciding to waste time I went to the window and surveyed the area for the 1 large and actually quite terrifying robot. He was no where in sight until I strained my eyes to see the very corner of the street where he was disapearing around a corner. Eager to see where he was going I started to slip out of the house, but the man was beginning to stir on the floor. Trying one last time I shook his shoulder trying to wake him up and finally he opened his eyes and I held him in place as to not let him hurt himself again. 'Who are you!' he demanded in a deep voice. 'A friend,' I replied 'and all I would like to know is if you have any idea why the robots are attacking and any information on the larger one with glowing eyes.' Yeah' he said 'I know about the big one. He was my robot and friend until I closed the  factory. Actually he may be trying to work the factory himself right now! I had better get over there!'  'No' I responded in a harsh voice 'you are in no condition to be fighting robots right now. But do you know how to destroy him?' 'Just melt his controlling pannel' the man said in a shaky voice. Blood was streaming out of his arm in addition to the small cut he had on his head. Unwillng to leave him like this I searched arond the house until I found what once was a bathroom and looked inside the cabnets until I found a first aid kit with bandages and wrappings. Returning to the room where the man lay unconcious yet again but this time from loss of blood I wrapped up all of his wound until it stopped bleeding and his heart was pumping normally. I pursued the robot with pure fury filled within me for what these robots had done to this man. Finding the factory fairly easy I walked inside to see the one robot in command hunched over a large pannel of buttons looking for the right one to press. Almost as soon as I walked in, weapon drawn, the robot whirled around with frightening speed and fired multiple lazers. Jumping to the side and watching the lazers explode in a shower of sparks on the wall I got up and channeled all my fury into one last blow. Aiming at the robot's controll system I fired. Just before the lazer hit, the robot created a green orb around it that blocked my shot and sent it richocheting back and hit me in the chest. I had conciousness for one second as I saw the robot slink into the shadows and then I blacked out.            Waking some time later to find my body aching I realized that my armor had melted off due to the shot I took at the robot.  Walking was hard for me since the groung seemed to be spinning below my feet so I crawled to where the robot had been when I was knocked out. Finding no trace of him I searched the factory for more clues as to where he went. Around the third bend I came up sucessful as I peered at him. He was at another controll pannel and this time turning gears and pressing buttons which meaned he had figured out the code. From my hiding place I drew my pistol ever so discretly took aim at his controlling pannel and was about to fire when my shoe rubbed against the concrete making a screeching sound. This sent him whirling like a top as he searched the room for me. I realized that I couldn't fail because I had no armor to protect me now. As he circled a corner in the room his controll pannel came into sight. I had little strength left but took aim and fired not heeding the robot at the weapon store's warning about overexerting myself. The lazer found its target and the room exploded with sparks as I backed around the corner to safety where I suddenly felt as if my breath had been taken away and at the last second, when I was sure that I would sufficate, it came back to me. I passed out wanting to do nothing more than sleep. I must have been out for a couple days because when I woke it was raining outside and the streets were deserted.            I quicky ran to the house where I left the man laying on the floor and found him exactly as he was before I left. After contacting the ambulance immediatly, they took him away and said he was going to be fine.  Going home and waching the news revealed that people were begining to come back out of their homes because they were previously hiding from the robots. The news reporter also said 'A heroic kid that was about 13 years old had been seen following the robot that put this town into destruction and destroyed it but we don't know who this kid is or where he lives!'. Good I thought to myself very good I don't think we are going to have any more robot problems for quite some time.
