Item_Response: The Wonderful Robot              One day little Jane was just siting on her father Johns lap and her mother Sally was in the kitchen setting the table for their guests who were suppose to come later that evening. Than all the sudden they heard a really loud BONK! on the roof. John said 'what on earth was that?' 'I don't know hunny.' answered Sally 'daddy why don't you go and see what it was?' 'okay I will you guys stay in the house though. I'll be back as soon as I possibly can.'                            So John went to go see what the loud BONK! was that they all heard. He climbed up on the roof and saw a small object that looked very complicated and hard to figure out. he slowly made his way over to that area of the roof. and the object made a odd beeping sound.   John got a box and put the strange object in the box and went back down the ladder into the living room. 'Look what  I've found everyone!' yelled John.  'what is it dear?' asked Sally.                         'oh I don't really know actually, but  I'm sure someone could find out what it is.' said John. Than the odd thing made a barking sound. 'daddy you don't know what a dog is?' asked Jane. 'hunny it is definitely not a dog.' answered John. Sally said 'let me see it.'. 'okay. be careful.' said John. Sally looked in the box and saw a mechanical looking puppy. 'awww a puppy!' yelled Jane. Than the strange object jumped out of the box and barked and yelped all over the living room. John and sally were scared and didn't know what to do about this strange thing that was jumping around their living room. While little Jane just danced and played and chased the odd thing.                      'hunny, Jane get away from that thing!' yelled John 'I just wanna play with it though daddy.' 'you don't know what it could do.' said Sally. Than John got up and trapped the odd puppy under the box. He than ran to the kitchen and called the neighbors who were suppose to come over for dinner and said 'sorry but we are having troubles and we can't have you over tonight we are going to have to rescheule for another time, sorry.'                     'we are going to have to do something with that thing.' said Sally. 'do we have to get rid of it?' asked little Jane. 'if you think we are going to keep that thing you are crazy!' said John. 'but daddy I wanna keep him he's my friend, he said his name was Barber zox lee.' said little Jane. 'are you talking to him?Is he talking to you?' asked John 'he's nice daddy.' said little Jane. 'how do you know?' asked Sally. 'he told me himself. Just let him out he could tell you too but you won't listen well enough!' whined little Jane.                       'That's obsurd!' said John. 'He looks like a robot pet.' said Sally. 'Ya thats what he is, he told me that too. He said he was from planet THE FUTURE, and he was here because his parents or owners kicked him out. He said he was just out exploring one day and than he fell off of there planet.' said little Jane. 'How is it possible to fall of of a planet?' asked John. 'He said his planet is a cube and it has no gravity. okay?' 'okay answered Sally and John.' 'So can't you just let him out he just got a little exited and you dont even have to worry about letting him out to got to the bathroom.' said little Jane. 'I guess we can try him out for a week or so, but if he does anything that he's not suppose to, he's outta here!' said John 'Okay daddy.' said little Jane.                            Then after a while the family had a wanderful time playing with there new puppy nut they continued to call him Strange as his name. They went  on walks in the park, played fetch, and even slept together. Theonly thing was that Strange was meant to last forever and little Jane grew up to be big Jane and went to colledge with her little Strange. Than when Jane became an adult she still had her little Strange. One night when Jane was sleeping she heared a really loud crash her and her husband Jack got out of bed and went to see what it was. there two kids May and Charlie got out of there beds too to see what was going on.                      Jack told his family to stay in the house. Jack went outside and in the snowey fluff layed a small mechanical device that was in the shape of a cat.

Item_Response: Monday morning I was with my brother and he was getting the mail from the driveway.  He came in and we started watching things on a channel that was all about robots.  After a while I got up to get a snack,  I reached into the fridge to get some left over spaghetti all of the sudden when I put it into the microwave there was a large 'BOOM'.                                                     The boom knocked me down on my feet, so I got up and the microwave was beeping.  When I opened the door to get my spaghetti a small baby liked thing did the robot walking out of the microwave.  I screamed and ran into the living room,  I told my brother there was a baby doing the robot in our kitchen.                                                        He told me I was crazy and turned the volume on the television  up.  Walking into the kitchen I was scared to death, so I closed my eyes and went to the counter.  A baby robot was in my kitchen taking pictures of all my appliances.  It looked at me straight in the eye and drove behind the trash can.                                                        When I took a look behind the trash can I sall a small but rusty little robot.  I asked it where it was from and how it got here.  It said 'My master Steve Jobs from my home planet Apple sent me here to look for some of his stolen products'.  He found out that my house has no stolen stuff from his planet and toke off through our chimney to his planet.

Item_Response: The Robot in The Mine                One day Bob was getting ready for work in the mines. He was already in a t-shirt, old pair of jeans, black boots and hard helmet and gloves in his hands. Bob was waiting for is buddy Jeff. Bob and Jeff always went to work together since they were neighbors. When Jeff finally got there they both got in Bobs truck and headed for the mines.                  When  they got there they both got right to work because they new if they didn't start now it would be dark before they made it home. A couple hours into the job Jeff found what  he thought was an old robot.'Bob come here think I found a robot!' Jeff explained.Bob quickly ran over to him. 'We should take it to the mechanic so he can fix it,'Bob says.                  The next morning Bob took it to the mechanic on the far side of town.'I've what appears to be a robot here,'says Bob.'You sure do,Bob. This robot was used to save you miners when you were trapped, and would check the air for any gases, and would help lifting coals.  If you want I can repair and it would be ready in two days.' the mechanic replies.'That would be great'says Bob.                   The next two days went by slowly,  but when the day finally came Jeff, Bob and all the other minners were exited. Bob quikly rushed over to the mechanic to pick up the robot.  When Bob and the robot got to the mine they quikly got to work. Life in the mines became much easier all the miners didn't have to stay late to finish up, infact on good days they went home earlier.                                          The End

'Wheres my screw driver' 'Wheres the hand' Jake would constantly be talking to him self.   He is a nervous wreck. Jake is a 26 year old scientist. He always dreamed about robots. Always make little toy robots. Until he grew up and went to college. Now he has a better idea. A bigger idea. A world changing idea. It was to make a robot, not just a small little toy robot. but a big robot. A robot that would do anything you controlled it to do.          'Just one more part. Wheres my controller?' Jake asked him self.          'Ahh here it is.' He bluetoothed the controller to the robot. Sucess. Now he just had to turn it on. It all comes down to this part right here.          ' Come on, work for me.' Jake was having no such luck. He would turn the controller on and off. No luck. He would take parts off, clean them and put them back in. Still no luck. Jake just couldnt find the problem. Jake kept trying more and more things un till all of the sudden it was 12:30. He figuared he would go to his small appartmant fit just for him with one bedroom, one bathroom, with a small kitchen and living room, and try again tomorrow. 'RING RING RING RING' snooze.          '6:45 already? I have to get a closer job dont ya thing Pappi?' Pappi was Jakes little black and which collie mix dog. He would sleep with Jake every day and new what the alarm clock met. whever it would go off pappi would start barking saying get up and let me to outside. Jake put on his plain black shirt and soem bage pants and some dressy schools. Jake really doesnt need to dress up the week becuase hes been working on the robot and getting dirty, but he still wants to obey his works dress code. So he gets in his car and drives to work.           ' Hey jake!' 'Hey cody!' 'Heyyy Jaksterr. Heres your morning coffe!' ' Jessica! Your my girl!' This would go back and forth like this when Jake enters work. This science lab was hugeeee! Jake had to pass about 5 halls all full of offices to get to the back of the lab where his robot was. Right away Jake a sip of his coffe took off his coat set them on his desk and went to the back of the room by the robot and immedialy started looking for his problem. Everyone just starting clapping with amazment with a big smile on your face. This gets plastered all over the internet, the newspaper, anything you can imagine you would hear about it. He made the path so that firefighters could make there way though and rescue them all. The robot passed the test.

Item_Response: The Human Robot                                                                          Ryan is a 10 year old boy who is autistic. He has a very BIG imagination. But he is struggling in school. He has to take special classes in school. His parents transfer him to an autismn school in Virginia Beach, Virginia. That means that he has to move from Bruce, Wisconsin to Virginia Beach, Virginia. He is going to miss his old school, from all the nice friends that he has had to new friends that know what he is feeling.               The next day he has to say good bye to all of his friends at his school and get ready for tommorow to hop on a plane and move to Virginia to meet new friends. His parents know that he doesn't want to leave this great school from missing his friends. His friends have be treating him like anyother persin in the school.                The next day he is on the plane heading for Virginia, it is at least a 2 day trip there. he doesn't know what the kids at the autismn school are going to think of him. His parents didn't even tell him what the autismn school is called? So Ryan speaks up and says 'What is the new school's name?' His mother replies 'Miranda's Autismn School.' 'Oook then?' Ryan said confused? His father replies 'You are going to so much fun!'                They are finally at their new house, which is located right across from his new school. That he will be going to soon in the morning. Ryan doesn't even know what classes he is going to take. That was the main thing that he was thinking about.               That morning. 'Ryan please get up for breakfast please.' Ryan does as he was told to do. He gets up, heads for the bathroom and gets ready, and finally goes down stairs for breakfast. 'Are you ready for a new day at a new school son?' Ryan's father asks. ' Umm, sure I guess?' 'Ryan you don't sound that interested, what's the matter sweety?' Ryan didn't respond. He just sat their and at his breakfast. They got ready to leave and Ryan didn't even want to go but he had know chose. They walked out the door and walked into the school doors and walked to the office from ome help from a teacher.        They walked into the office and met everyne in the office. The pricipal gave Ryan his schedual and his parents and him walked down to the class room following the pricipal. They stopped, and the pricipal walked into the class room and his parents kissed him on his fourhead and left. the principal introduced his to the class and they all welcomed him with delight. He as well felt delighted. His class was called 'Inventing,' he liked the sound of that name cause when he was 4-5 he used to build himself and his mother and father random things, and the still kept them today.             Ryan sat right in front where he loved to sit. The new project that they were going to start to day was building a robot any kind that they wanted. Ryan drew a picture of his robot just like the others in his class. All the parts that they needed were on the back table. Ryan was the 4th one done drawing, so he quietly got up from his desk and walked to the back table to grad all the parts that he needed, and the teacher, Mrs. Quill said that the tricky part was getting it to work. Mrs. Quill asked one of the other students named Jacob but everyone calls him Jake for short, to show him around the school after class.              Ryan was almost done with his robot which was small but looked like a human. Ryan forgot to program it to speak to others including himself and his parents. Ryan just got done working on his robot. He could speak to the robot and tell him whatever he wanted him to do, Mrs.Quill asked what Ryan was going to name him and he said 'Reggie.' After school he got to take him home and show his parents, Mrs.Quill said that he has to bring it back cause they are going to have a 'Robot Race!' Ryan was really excited. So he went to bed.             The next morning he got up, got dressed, went down stairs to eat breakfast, and then headed out the door for school. When he got to school he went to class and won 1st place in the 'Robot Race.' After he was congradulated he got a trophy. and took it home after school to his parents. And later in the school year He had a lot of friends.                                                                         THE END

Item_Response: Finn       Hi. I'm Isabelle. And here's my story about my robot named Finn.   It was in the middle of summer vacation, and I was really bored. I had done all of the things on my Summer Vacation To-Do List. I had already gone fishing, camping, hiking, swimming, I've slept in, went to bed a little later, watched almost all of the funniest videos on the Internet, played with my dog, cleaned my room, and much more. I have checked off every single thing on my list. but as I came down to the bottom of it, there was one thing left.   Make a robot.   And that is what I was going to do.   So then, I had asked my mother if I could go on an 'adventure.'   She then laughed and said, 'Be back before supper.'   Which was of course, 5 hours away. I had plenty of time to find robot parts. So I then grabbed my backpack off of the hook, grabbed my sweatshirt, my hat, and grabbed my bike from the garage. I then put my sweatshirt, my hat, and my backpack on, and I hopped on the bike and pedaled down the hill.   By the time I was at the junkyard, it was only 12:07. I have plenty of time to grab some stuff here, and then go to the store to go get more supplies.   I said hi to the gatekeeper, Rusty, and then pedaled past those creepy chain-link fences. they were all rusty, with barbed wire at the top. That always gives me the creeps. And then there is always the junkyard dogs, Spike and Lolly, but as they look scary, they're really sweet. They just are there to scare away the intruders who try to break in. But only by their looks and teeth bearing.   There were piles and piles of junk piled on top of each other, piling all the way up to the sky. But I don't think I'll need to go that far up to find some parts.   Just then, I saw this beautiful, glittering silver cabinet that was big enough for the body of the robot. That part would be the refrigerator of the robot.   I put that in my pile of supplies that I would need.   I pedaled around some more piles of junk until I saw the best pile yet. It had a go-kart! That will be perfect for the feet!   So then I had Rusty help me pull it out from under the pile of junk. I tried to turn it on. it started making this weird noise, and it wouldn't turn on! I guess I had just gotten my hopes up. But then, as I tried turning it on for the last time, It vroomed to life! Yay! I got so happy that I jumped up and started dancing with joy with Rusty. We danced for a bit more, and then I got back to work and asked Rusty,   'Do you have any small refrigerators?'   'Why yes I do! I just got a load of them this morning.'   What luck I am in right now!   'Could you please show me where they are?' I asked politely.   'Well, sure! So, what are you making anyway?'   'A robot!' I said gleaming with pride.   'Cool!'   'Yeah!'   So he showed me around the junkyard, guiding me where I wanted to go and pick out some parts. I had so far the body of the robot, the head, the refrigeration unit, the feet, and the mechanical arms and hands. Now, all I need is the eyes, nose, and mouth. But I'll pick up some of those at the hardware store.   'Hey Isabelle, do you want me to drop this off at your house?'   'Sure, that would be great!' I said smiling. (And let me note, he is my cousin.)   'Okay.' he agreed.   'I just have to run to the hardware store and grab a few parts. So you can just load all of those things into the garage, okay?'   'Sure thing, Isabelle.'   So I thanked him and said goodbye, and pedaled to the next stop. The hardware store.   I looked down at my watch. 3:02. I better get going if I want to build this robot!   I rode my bike down Main Street, turned the corner, and there I was, at Billy's Hardware Store.   I love it there. It's my favorite place to go to, besides the zoo.   I pushed the door open, and a bell rang overhead.   'Hey Billy.'   'Hey Isabelle. What are you up to today?'   'I'm building a robot!' I gleamed with pride.   'Cool! So what can I get for you?'   'Can I get two small white training wheel cover caps, a small plastic cutter, and a small gear?'   'Sure! Coming right up!' He walked around the counter, and into the small, cluttered back room. He came out with a small brown bag.   'Thanks Billy!'   'You're welcome Isabelle!'   So I stuffed that in my backpack and rode off onto Main Street.   I looked down at my watch. 3:30. Yikes. I have to start building my robot!   I rode into the driveway, and parked my bike into the garage. I found all of my supplies on the garage floor.   It had been chilly all week, but now it was getting hot out. I pulled off my sweatshirt, and grabbed a Popsicle from the freezer. Yummy, it was grape. My favorite.   I had then finished my Popsicle, and grabbed some supplies.   I was going to do a stack and glue method. I grabbed the go-kart, and set that on the floor. I put blocks of wood beside the wheels so it would not roll away. I then put Super Super Glue on the rim of the go-kart, then lifted the cabinet on top of it. Perfect fit! I then got the big pink and zebra striped jewelry box and put glue on the bottom of it, and stuck the box on the cabinet. Then I opened up the cabinet, put glue all around on the inside, and stuck the refrigerator in it. Then I glued the arms on, and made the face by putting the caps on the box for the eyes, the gear for the nose, and I carved out a smile on it's face. It was finally done. I went inside and went to show Mom.   'That is really cool! What is it's name?'   'Hmm. Oh, I know! Finn!'   'What a wonderful name!'   I then made her turn around, and then I pressed his ON switch. She asked what I was doing, and I said, 'Just wait.' And then, the arms of the robot started moving. It was giving her a massage! She thought that was a marvelous idea, and that she would have to use it more often!   She thanked me, hugged me and then we started stocking Finn's refrigerator with apple juice, oranges, apples, kiwis, and much more. I then checked off Make a robot on my list.

Item_Response: A long time ago lived a scientist named Dr.Olson.  He has been working on a top secret invention.  The first ever robot to come alive.  He thought, 'Yes!  I just need one more part!  I best go now, so that the store doesn't close!' Dr.Olson then threw on his coat and headed out the door.          A little while after Dr.Olson arrived in Ladysmith, he was by the hardware store.  He quickly ran up to the door and looked at the sign.  It said 'CLOSED'.  Dr.Olson was very disipointed.  He knew that another store didn't have what he was seeking for.  So, Dr.Olson sadly walked to his car.          'Why?!  This robot would of been so cool!  It could of gone up to 100 mph, talk, steer all by its self, gather information, go into places people couldn't, and either fold up really small or grow really big!  Such a disipointment.' he yelled to himself.  Off Dr.Olson went, all the way back to Bruce.  He walked into his house and hung up his coat and threw off his shoes.  He slowly, but surely, walked down to his lab.  He screwed everything back onto the robot that he unscrewed and sat down right next to it, in his chair.  All of a sudden, Dr.Olson started to hear sparks.          'Hello master.  What can I do for you today?' his robot (chucky) said, in a robotic voice.          'He's alive!  He's really alive!' Dr.Olson said, jumping up and down.  He laughed in excitment and screamed, 'Ya, who!!!' Dr.Olson ran all the way to the news station and told them all about it.          'A robot, you say?' the news man questioned.          'Yes!  He can go up to 100 mph, talk, steer all by him self, gather information, go into places we cant go, and fold and grow into surprizing sizes.  He's amaizing!' Dr.Olson exclaimed.          'Ok!  Lets make it tomorrows news, yes?' the news man said in such excitement.          'Yes!  That will work just fine.  But first, do you want to see it?' Dr.Olson offered.          'Sure.  I would like to see it... I'm looking forward to it.' the news man happily said.  Away Dr.Olson went, running into his lab.                                                        THE NEXT DAY              Dr.Olson got a call from the news man saying that he can't make it, but will report it in his news.  Dr.Olson was a bit glum, but he was still happy about his creation!  Eventually he was famious for his robot, and more and more invetors started to create more robots, such as R2D2.                                                                   THE END

Item_Response: Nuts, Volts, and Apples       The job of an Agribot is simple and straight forward: harvest the crop when ripe. No sooner. No later. Any robot who doesn't meet this requirement gets transported back to the Institute to be reprogrammed or disassembled. Mistakes are unheard of. Accidents never happen.   That is, until the robots came to life.       It was an ordinary at the ABC Farm, and Farmer Pick A. Lot was taking roll call of all his Agribots. 'Agribot 1a? Ah, there you are. 2b? Check. 3c? Splendid, splendid.'   So it went until he intoned, 'Now Agribots, you know what to do. You need to harvest the first half of the apple orchard. Now I don't want a single wormy apple in a bushel. ABC Farm stands for top quality fruit. Nothing but the best will do, understand?'  Always forgetting that the Agribots didn't talk, he rolled his eyes and huffed. 'Well, don't just stand there! Get a move on it!'       The Agribots rumbled off and started picking the fruit at an incredibly fast rate. They had almost finished the first half, and started to work on the second, when ominously dark storm clouds started to roll in. Thunder boomed, and the wind blew in, making the trees sway and bend under the stress. Rain lashed the trees and pounded madly against the roof of his house. Lightning crackled across the velvety black sky, and it illuminated the entire sky for a split second. Farmed Pick frantically started bellowing to his Agribots to get inside quickly, but his voice was lost in the wind. Without warning, a searing hot rope of lightning arched down and struck the robots with a terrific bang, showering them with sparks and frying the fruit held in the baskets. Farmer Pick yelled in anger and surprise and sprinted to his robots. The fragrant smell of baked apples filled the air, spoiled with a odor of burned rubber. He shouted over the wind, 'Agritbots, are you all right? Oh, what am I saying, they can't talk.' Then the Agribots started to move weakly, and a voice issued from it. 'What happened? Why am I all wet. Who are you?'  Farmer Pick gawked at it. This was impossible, but there it was. So with a whimper and a thump, Farmer Pick keeled over in a dead faint.       So for the next few days, Farmer Pick tried to keep the harvest on schedule. He took roll call, told the robots what to do, and watched them roll off. 'I must be getting old. Robots can't come to life.' But how wrong he was.   First the robots started picking the wrong apples. When he yelled at them to get the job done right, the robots complained, 'No good deed goes unpunished.'   Then when they actually picked the ripe fruit, they started to try to eat it. This resulted in much shouting and upbraiding on the farmer's part, and the Agribots just shuffled around and promised they'd never do it again.   Next they started to play hide and seek in the apple orchard, and Farmer pick had to look for two hours before he actually found them. He turned beetroot red and shrieked, 'That's the last straw! You are the worst robots I have ever had. I quit!' He threw his hat on the ground, stormed off, and drove off in his car to take a lifelong vacation from farming and robots.       Afterwards, the robots successfully ran the farm and prospered with their new job, and remained life long friends with each other. Farmer Pick A. Lot tried to explain what happened to authorities, but gave up after numerous suggestion to get some rest. But he always wondered what had happened to those three rogue robots who came to life.

Item_Response: Hi my name is Taylor and I'm going to tell you about the day i got a robot that i didn't even know was real......            So, one day i was just walking home casually from school, and I walk into my house and my dad is in the kitchen. And he hears the door shut and he says 'Taylor is that you', I said yes it's me. then, he tells me he has something for me. 'OK?' i said.       Mean while i walk into the kitchen....Look its a robot my dad says. Whoa! i say. Its all yours.           I take the robot upstairs to my room and start to mess around with it. i used the remote dad gave to me. after a while I started understanding the remote control a little bit more. Dad called me downstairs to the kitchen to eat dinner.....            After I finished eating i went back upstairs, and the robot was gone! The remote was still on the bed where I put it before going downstairs.I heard something coming from the laundry room. I slowly opened the door, and guess what was sitting on the laundry room floor...THE ROBOT!       Two months later:   The robot actually became one of my best friends. I named him Joe. Do every thing together. He helps me with my homework, he helps me clean the house.       I'm really glad my dad got me a robot. :)

Item_Response: This is the story, of a robot that became a boys best friend. It all began when Hurricane Andrew rolled in. The citizens of Charleston were all tying to evacuate. Little Jon, a twelve year-old boy, went to the junk yard for some boards. As Jon searched, lightning streaked across the sky, and rouge lightning bolt hit just behind Jon!   'AH' cried Jon. I could have died! Just as Jon thought. A small whimper came through the junk pile. 'Hello?' Jon said nervously as he approached the sound. Just then a puppy robot that looked just like a lab on the outside jumped on Jon.       Jon walked home with his little robot puppy. 'I hope Ma lets me keep you.' Through the puppy's real skin, a glow peeked through his eyes.   'Hey did you get a new puppy?' Asked Jon's friend Holland   'He's a robot puppy!'   'Really?' Replied Holland 'what can he do?' Jon told the puppy to fly as a joke, and rockets sprang out of its feet!   'What is this!?' Cried Jon, and they flew off! Holland desperatly chased them, but lost them in the rain of Andrew. Jon and the puppy landed on their homes doorstep.   'Good boy!' said Jon. Jon's mother allowed Jon to keep the puppy. Jon named the puppy Baxter. Baxter wagged his tail.       It was raining like crazy. The radio was playing 'Ridin' Out the Storm.' With the company of Baxter And Jon's mother, it wasn't so bad!

Item_Response: I was in my room, then all of a sudden, this toy robot that I have, comes to life! I was very excited, yet confused. I mean, why would my robot come to life for no reason? I didn't question it though. Well, she was a girl robot. I decided to name her Kaitlyn. Kaitlyn was sky blue, about two and a half feet tall, was strong, had all terrain wheels, and had light purple wings. She was the coolest thing I have ever seen!              After I stopped gushing about how cool she was, I asked her what she could do.Well, lucky me, my robot could talk! She could do my chores, clean my room, do my homework, cook, speak many languages, and even fix my hair! It was the coolest thing EVER. The best part about her was that she could fly!              She and I did everything together. We went to the park, the mall, my friend's houses, but unfortunatly I couldn't take her to school. They said that even though she was cool, it was against school rules. While I was at school, she played with my dog. It was the most fun I'd had in a long time.               'Whoa! That was a really weird dream!' I said. I looked over at my robot and said, 'You're the best friend a girl could have.' Right after I said that, I could've sworn she winked at me.

Item_Response: In the year 2134 the U.S. economy boomed with robots.  Everyone had one. At the age of 13 you got one and it would practicly serve you. The goverment even started takeing soldiers out of the army and useing robots. When you were old enough to get one, you went downtown to the closest town hall, and you would get a back ground check then it got to the fun part.             Next you got to design the robot. You would first choose a color. Then you designed the base, or the body of the robot. After, you got to choose four out of millions of attachments. You could choose extra arms, sticky pads on their fingers so they could pick things up, or you could just put on a storage section. last you got a romote and a chip. The chip was used to put in the robots head to turn it on and so it could think. The romote was used for may reasons like turning off the robot and turning it on. It also has an emergency shut down.             After that long process the robot would show up at your door the next morning. It would only resond to your comands and it was also ment to protect you. That stoped a lot of crime. The robot served you all of your life, when you died the metal would be recycled and it would be sent to town hal to start the process all over again. The special parts also were recycled. The remote was thrown away and the chip was saved for history.

Item_Response: Willy the Great Robot       One day long ago there was a teenager named Calub Armore.  He was always working on new projects. Armore has always been fascinated in robots as a child and always wanted to bulid one and be a scientist, but was sure he couldn't. His mother and family always said 'you cant do it never, ever, ever do that''. Armore always wanted to prove them wrong.             Every night he worked and worked but all of his creations failed, until one night it was late and everyone was a sleep. Armore worked then finally his robot awakened! Armore danced around, and was so proud of himself he thought at once he would start to train it. Armore worked all night and got the robot to dance, clean, and play with children and animals. He could not wait to tell his family 'I told you so'.            He ran down stairs the next morning and showed his parents they said 'son you are way to old to be playing with robots, you are almost 17'' Armore just said in his head at least I built one he grabbed his robot and went back upstairs. He was said about his parents reply.            That night he could not sleep thinking about the great things his robot could do for the world. Then he remembered that he still needed to name the robot he felt the need to name is after his grandfather who was also a scientist. He named it willy.            Willy, and Calub hung out everyday and tried to stay away from his parents. Then Armore had to go off to college and had to leave Willy behind. It was a sad day he ordered his younger brother Luis to take care of Willy. Willy missed Calub, but Willy and Luis had fun.

Item_Response: Robots, I always stood on end just hearing the word that was the one thing that made the curiosity that I had unfold. Just down the road where I live is a factory that makes robots! I was always curious to know how robots exactly worked. So when it was the darkest of night I sneaked into the factory and made sure nobody was around for my great discovery of how robots worked. Once I sneaked in there was a big, metal, door that supposedly was the impenetrable. What was I thinking I knew it wasn't just as easy as a walk in the park. But since I already got  out of bed. I couldn't leave my hungry stomach unsatisfied without any adventure. So once again I devised a strategy that was the biggest, baddest idea Ive ever had. I got out my robot that I always kept with me. It was a portable cube that could turn into a 6 ft robot with a golden aluminum body with stain less steel eyes that glow a bright neon green. It was the coolest invention yet except there was one minor flaw it didn't work at all. My goal for the year was to make it work except I tried everything but it still wouldn't work. The door that was impenetrable was starting to open with a series of clinking sounds that took out the locks. What just happened? I didn't do anything but let my robot transform nothing else? BOOM! The earth shook like never before with ear screeching sirens and megaphones announcing Intruder alert Intruder alert. Oh why did I have to get in this mess. All around me there were robots just like mine except with evil glares and menacing red beams coming from there obnoxiously big eyes. I will protect you from these imposters said my robot with a robotic/cold voice. Now that was just to much for me to handle first my robot comes alive and tries to defend me even though its meant for singing and dancing just like the HRP-4C. I guess it can protect me with some of his awesome Michael Jackson moves but I think that's about it. Wait a minute if that's what my robot can do so can the other imposter robots can do. They are gonna have a dance competition. Hit it Ben! Bum Bum Bum clash ting one robot down 2 more to go. Etc. It came down to the final robot Bum Bum clash ting both robots came tumbling down. No how could this be, my robot was the impossible to desroy but now it came down just as easy as a block of lego tumbling down. I was smiling but my heart was broken inside if he didnt protect me I would have been a pile of robot bolts or more like human remains.

Item_Response: Ideas-   * Testing out a new robot. Things go horribly wrong.   *Testing out a new robot, the one I said I'd invent if     *Robot being moody about doing whatever people want it to.   *Little bit of both?   Start (paragraphs 1 and 2)- It was the moment I'd been waiting for. After being stuck in the lab for months, I would finally be free! (Intro, explain that the narrator is a robot.)   Paragraph 3- Does job (photographing underwater stuff, rainforests, arctic, desert)   paragraph 4- Meets other robots.   Conclusion?   More paragraphs then the outline formed above might be nessesary.         It was the moment I'd been waiting for. Finally, I would be getting out of the lab and tested. After months of assembling, recallibration, and dozens of examinations and battery changes, I was going to actually do something. My name is Photo Falcon. I was recently programed in a little lab in a place called California. What the place called Earth that's outside the lab is like, I'm not sure. All I know is it's a lot bigger.      I knew it was time when one of the scientists, Maria Crystal, picked up the metal box I've spent a bit too much time in, opened it, and slipped the film into the slot in my side that's supposed to hold film. If not for the fact that nobody had flipped my power switch, I would've been flying all over the place from exicitment. Richard and Bob, two other scientists, grabbed their iPads, two very important electronics plus a metal box like mine and they walked into the glossy silver lab van. Tests outside the lab were always exciting to hear about, but this would be even better because I was with them!     I was about to be tested in a clearing, whatever that is, about five miles away. The ride was short, but very interesting. Many vans, most of which were much smaller then the lab van and of many different colors, drove along the roads with the van, their metal surfaces glittering in the midday sun. Through the window, I saw a large body of water. It was huge! The 'ocean' seemed to go on forever. Sunlight sparkled off the waves. A few weeks ago, I'd been put in a pool to make sure that my clear coat of waterproof plastic actually worked. At the time that had seemed huge, but now that pool looked dinky.     When the van came to a stop, I was lifted out of the trunk and removed from the box. Richard flipped my switch, so  I started my propeller and zoomed into the azure sky. The meadow I was being tested in looked tiny from above, the blanket of grass no bigger then a child's fist. I went swooped down easily, due to my torpedo shape. There was no way I could take any good pictures from this altitude and do what I was supposed to do.     Maria walked over to the second box and I felt my cameras going off. What was she thinking?! She knew any motion would set those off! I was only supposed to use my film on objects that were interesting, not the scientists that I saw every single day.     The lid was pulled off of the box and out hopped a rabbit. Its glossy, cinder colored coat reflected the sky and it leaped forward, ears flopping like a flag on a windy day. Snap! Snap! Snap! I twirled in a circle to allow all eight of my cameras to capture the image. For about half an hour, the rabbit hopped about the meadow and I caught every movement on tape.     When the trio of scientists had gotten a good enough assetment of how I worked (I certainly hope I passed the test! I didn't want to end up a non-functional robot who got set aside or worse, used for scrap metal), Bob pulled out my remote that would make me return to the ground. I descended and they turned off my switch, forcing me to remain immobile while they checked my pictures. Based on the pleased look on their faces, I guessed that they liked the pictures. The rabbit stood motionless now and up close I realized it too was a robot! On the return trip, Maria, Bob, and Richard talked up a storm. Apparently they were testing me and the rabbit and so they were extremly pleased to have gotten double sucess.      The next few months were a blur. I was sent all across the world to photograph all kinds of enviornment, including the warm and wet Great Barrier Reef, the Amazon River (also warm and wet), and a forest somewhere in Europe. Very soon I became so popular replicas of me were made. They all looked identicle to me; sleek, clear torpedo shape. Mini cameras (also clear) on the sides and wings. Airplane wings that could tuck into their sides. Propellers mounted to the back to make it possible to go through air or water.      I met other robots when traveling to other places. Sometimes Maria, Richard, and Bob would bring me with them when they compared robots with other scientists. In Iowa I met a robotic cat named Trixie who was the first of a line of pets for people who wanted a cat but were allergic to them or didn't want to feed them. Down in Florida, I photographed an Agribot, a robot who picks vegtables and fruits, busily plucking ripe oranges. I may not be a living thing, but I have to say that life is pretty good.

Item_Response: This is about a creative writing club that meets at the school library once a week.This a story about how robots save lives people and they work in many different stuffs.Robots do many jobs today.They work in mines and on farms.They help doctors and save lives.They even explore volcanoes.Here are some robots that are hard at work.            Gemini-Scout is a remote-controlled robot that does search-and-rescue work in mines under the ground.The robot is less than two feet tall and has wheels.Gemini-Scout carries food, water, and other supplies.It can even drag hurt people to safety.The robot also has a thermal camera to help it find miners.A thermal camera uses heat sensors to find living things.When the robot finds the trapped miners, the miners can use its two-way radio to talk with the rescue team.           Dante 2 is a robot with an interesting job, it climbs into volcanoes to gather information for scientists.It is also built to survive very high heat.Dante 2 looks for vents, or holes, in the crater.Now scientists can study a volcano up close while they remain safe in their laboratories.           Mr.Gower is a robot that works in hospitals, helping doctors and nurses bring medicine to patients.The robot is so strong that it can pull 500 pounds.The robot can deliver medicine for twelve hours without stopping.          An agribot is a robot that picks fruit.Agribots are not yet widely used, but farmers are interested in what these robots can do.In Japon, there is a strawberrypicking robot that can sense the color of the berries.This helps the robot know when each berry is ripe.

Item_Response: Hello, my name is Dr. Montgomery Fortz and I am going to tell you about my true story of the Forzbot that I created myself.     At first, the Forzbot was ment to work in schools as a secretery, but he turned out to be much, much more. It all started on the 29th of October, and I was about to give up on my new invention. But then I had an idea. You see, the problem was that the gears kept on getting stuck together, and no matter how many things I tried- Malsceno, Mandy Handy, the Unstuck. All of those are my inventions- the gears just refused to budge. Then I thought to myself, 'Maybe you should be more practical. If you were not a scientist, what would you use, Montgomery?' and it came to me. Vasteline! How could I have not thought of it before?! So I took out a bottle and slathered it all on it and- wouldn't you know!- the gears start turning and the pullies start pulling and the Fortzbot was more than just a fantacy! But the final resault was beyond astronomical, because next thing you know, he starts talking to me, just like that! I think his actual words were,'Hello sir, how do you do? I am verry sorry to disturb you, but I am new to this town and my car broke down. I need a place to stay for the night. I would hate to impose but...' The Fortzbot- my own invention!- was alive! Not only was he alive, but he thought himself a real person! Of course, I let him stay overnight, and by morning my cheekes hurt from smiling for hours.     And there was even more. The Fortzbot- who called himself Minho- knew everything from cooking to cleaning to working in the lumberyard. As thanks to letting him staying overnight, Minho did all of those things for me and was on his way.     Today, Minho works as a science teacher in Stanford, and has made many things of his own, including a non-toxic toothpaste, published a book: How to Convert to the Metric System for Kids, and read over 3,500 books, almost all on mathematics and engineering.     I know that most of you will not believe my story now, or next year, or ever, but the truth is the truth and will always remail so, whatever you might think.

Item_Response: The Robots          One day a little boy named Mario decided to build a robot so he got to work. The next day after school he went to the store across the street from his house to get the materials he needed. He got scrap metal, screws, and, many tools. When he got home he ran into his room threw his backpack down and got started. His mom had went to go check on him to see if there was something wrong. When she walked in she had noticed what he was doing and was fascinated. Mario found it odd how she didn't ask why he was making the robot. Later that night his mom walked in  and found him asleep.                           The next day he had finally finished his robot. He was so excited to start it up to see if it worked he was almost positive it would start. When the time finally came for him to start it he got a little nervous. When he tried to turn it on he noticed that the switch to the robot didn't work. Mario was really upset he wanted to cry but he didn't he wanted to try again. Mario had took apart the old robot and started over. This time it took him a week to Mario a week to finish building the second robot.       Mario had finally got ready to start it up once again. He had told himself that if it doesn't work he is going to give up. When he flipped the switch on the robot it immediately began to work. He was so happy and for the rest of the day he was playing with his new robot. It would walk around the carpet sing,and dance.       Later that night the robot came to life! It had began to start walking! The robot had left the house and ran outside. The next morning Mario and his parents noticed how the front door was open and Mario's robot was gone. When they had walked outside they had noticed how the whole neighborhood was sparkling clean but the robot was gone Mario was upset but he decided that maybe it was good thing that he was gone.

Item_Response: I was staring at a box I had gotten in the mail.It was very tall, wide, and long. It was probably about 13 feet each way. It was incredibly heavy, and I had no means of moving it. So I went into my garage, grabbed a ladder, and went into my office, got some scissors, and opened it up.         The object inside the box looked as though it were maid out of titanium and iron. I noticed the back part was opened up. There was a window in the front, on about a 70 degree angle. The sides were at about 45 degrees, and the bottom was flat. It had what appeared to be arms. Through the window, I could see what appeared to be controls. I climbed in the back and pressed a little green button. The thing stood up abruptly. On the ceiling, there was a helmet sort of thing. It lowered to the point where I could put it on.          Once I put the helmet on, I could not only control the robot, but I could also see things I wouldn't have, had I been using my eyes. The robot jumped into the air. When it landed again, something caught my eye. It was red. It moved like a snake. It was huge. And fast. Fast and huge. Something else appeared on the screen. It was a radar. Apparently, this robot also had weapons. My right... well, the robot's right hand had a knife in it. I asked myself, 'how do you miss a giant knife in the hand of a robot?,'          Just then, a voice answered my question. It must have been the robot's voice, because last time I checked, humans don't read minds. The robot answered, <You did not see the knife because you were busy wondering why a robot was in your yard. Hello Jake, we have been watching you for a couple years now, and we have decided you are ready>  'For what?! What's going on here?! And who are you?!,'  <You are ready to help us defeat Kalaar, the snake like creature you saw moments ago. As for who am I... I am KK8, or Kill Kalaar Eight.>          A jolt hit the robot, and it stopped speaking.

Item_Response: It was a warm summer day.  My dad explained to me he wanted the garage cleaned out.  I told him we have to much valuable stuff, and shouldn't get rid of it.  He said 'If you can find something to do with it, we won't have to throw it out'.  I thought for a while and eventually came up with the idea of making a robot.  My dad wished me luck and went inside.  I spent the rest of the day building a robot in the garage.           I took some old bikes completely apart, piece by piece.  The wheels were used as the robots feet, and the handlebars were the two hands.  Next I tore apart the old dirt bike we never used.  I constructed the motor and gears into the mechanism to make the robot move.  Soon after this hard job was done, I reconstructed my electric scooter into the arms and legs. A lawn mower was used for the head and the motor and gears went along with the dirt bike parts.  I took apart a few pairs of roller blades and those were used for looks.              The end product was amazing.  I destroyed two bikes, an electric scooter, a dirt bike, a few pairs of roller blades, and a lawn mower.  It was worth it.  At first I honestly didn't think it would do anything.  I was wrong.  My robot, Scirt Lade, does more than you can  ever imagine.  It plays sports, it cleans, it serves you, it can even cook anything you want.  It does pretty much everything.   I guess my dad wishing me luck did a lot more than I thought.

Item_Response: AI-363            AI-363 can be ready for anything that comes my way. He protects me all day and night. But how AI-363 came alive is a whole different story.           It all started on my birthday, April 29 in the year 2013. My mom and dad where planing on giving me some new stuff but when I saw them walking outside in the thunder and lightning. CRACK!!!! The lightning made all the power in the neighborhood go out! I was worried my mom or dad got hit but luckily they didn't They got back inside quickly and said. After everything stopped I became 73 degrees with no chance of storms or any bad weather. I saw something in the corner of the house, something that looks small.                  To took a few steps the thing, it turns out it is a robot that was somehow it came thought he must of. He had a Allen Iverson jersey on with some Jordan's. He looked awesome!!!            After I met him we started playing basketball, soccer and all these other sports that we liked. Surprising thing is he can dunk on a regulation hoop. I forgot to mention that he has dreads. Me and AI got together every day for the past to years but, something bad happened for me at least. He got drafted to the NBA. He was a first round pick for the 76er's. At least I could watch him on the TV. He turned out to be the best player in the NBA, he even led the team to championship ring.       I never saw him in real life ever again. I will always remember that birthday for me. Just only for that peculiar reaso....           AI!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!! You are back. I thought I was never going to see you ever again. The first thing he did was dunk over me on our hoop. AI is so funny. This was the best day of my life. At noon AI and me went to the park and played one-one of course he won. We kept playing for 5 hours straight.       A big storm came again in January 3, 2015. All of the sudden I heard a....... CRACK!!!!!!!!!! He was gone. I did not know what to do except cry. I will always remember that birthday for me. Just only for one peculiar reason. AI-363

Item_Response: THE PLANE THAT CHANGED EVERYTHING                        The scenery could not have been better, scarlet purple rays beat down softly on the crowded streets, rich aromas of blooming Daffodils and Tulips sweetened the air, and the sweet low whistle of the morning breeze joined by the constant chirping of the morning birds set the stage for an innovation to take place.                        This, was Kentwood. A town that has been standing under the shadows of its boastly neighbor Grand Rapids for over thirty years. The only thing that keeps the town standing on its feet is the importance it carries as the housing space for the local airport. Gerald R. Ford International Airport. But the town is very inexperienced at innovating, unlike Grand Rapids, the town does not even have a product that bears the phrase 'Invented and made in Kentwood,' but that was all going to change.                        So what was the innovation that had Kentwood's name entombed in the extremely exclusive club of innovative cities? Well, the answer lies at the local airport, where Kevin Roy has worked there for two years on a solar-powered airplane, only thing is, it's not an airplane, its a robot! You don't need a pilot to fly it. All you have to do is communicate with the Air Traffic Control and give the plane verbal intructions. The plane then does the rest.                       It was Monday, a day that most citizens of the area hate. People go back to work, buisness travelers fly out, kids start a new week in school, it is all mayhem on Mondays. But today, Kevin and his new innovation, called 'Innovation one' would take flight to launch a new push for pollution control.                      So now we jourmney into the cockpit of  Innovation one, Kevin is making his final pre-flight checks before take off. He climbs into the cockpit and says 'Engine one start, Engine one generator and battery on.' The plane responds and in a matter of seconds the engine on the left wing is gently humming in the morning breeze and Kevin can see that electricity is clearly flowing from the battery to the electric motor in the engine. He then says 'Engine two start, Engine two generator and battery on.' Again the plane responds as planned as soon both engines were humming gently while Kevin awaited commands from the Air Traffic Control.                     'Nero one five five niner Mike increase speed to zero two zero knots and proceed to runway two six left.' the controller chimes over the radio, with a rather urgent tone. Kevin repeats the directions to the plane and the plane gently starts rolling forward, takes a left, and rolls down the taxiway to runway two six left. While rolling, Kevin instructs, 'Solar Panels on Engines one and two report active.' The plane responds by switching the power fromt the batteries to the solar panels mounted on the wings. By the time he reaches two six left, his anxiety of if the plane will fly puzzles his mind, and he almost misses the controller saying, 'Nero one five five niner Mike cleared to line up runway two six left.' Kevin repeats the directions as said and the plane lines up on the runway.                        Kevin's urgency to take off is on the brink when the controller says, 'Nero one five five niner Mike wind two six zero at five knots runway two six left, cleared for take off.' With some enthusiasm but urgency. Kevin repeats the directions as stated and the plane starts to roll down the runway at ever increasing speed. All this while, Kevin is leaning back in his seat, staring at the runway before him, when the speed indicator reaches one one zero knots, the speed he wants, he says, 'Rotate and climb to three thousand feet.' The plane lifts up and...

Item_Response: Finding the Robots            I'd been sitting around all day with nothing to do. At my job   at the market downtown. It was an old place but always filled with people including myself. I sat at a red table when suddenly my boss came over to me.         He stood over me waiting for me to say a word but i said nothing. 'So are you actually going to do do something or just sit around all day and stare into space.' 'I'm ready for anything sir.' I replied. 'Well then why don't who go and grab me the boxes that were just delivered and bring them over to me when you are done.'         As I skit-ted across the market to the back door. There seemed to be mysterious creatures with the delivery man. I reached for one of the boxes but the creature stacked one box right on my hand.         'Oww.' I screeched. The creature that had dropped the box on my hand I noticed he was made out of metal that rolled away whereas the other one I had saw earlier had large arms that were good for grabbing stuff on and off the truck. 'What are these things?' I said to the delivery man. 'They are robots, You know they are actually very useful they are all around us.' 'Really?' I replied. 'Yes, I use them for loading my truck and carrying my boxes to the businesses.' 'Wow I never knew how much they can help!' 'Robots aren't just for this job though some help guide people and find out info some of our scientist can't. Mine are the Agribot and the Mr. Gower. This isn't the only job my robots can do, they can do many more!'         'Well me and my robots have got to get going, nice meeting you!' 'You too.' I said as I watched the two robot scoot up the ramp and up into the darkness of the truck.

Item_Response: Romeo and Juliet           Many years ago lived a young  robot named 'juliet'!Juliet was a loving, caring, funny, kind person. Who always put others before herself . Well one day Juliet woke up to a beautiful rising yellow sun with the smell of beautiful yellow roses with a note. This note said 'Dear Juliet, i know you don't know me but i secretly know you . As soon as i saw your beautiful face i instantly fell in love with you. Your white smile could light up Akers. But behind these beautiful insides Juliet worked at a hospital with lots of other robots. She climbed up mountains and went under ground to help find hurt people. She always said that even though she is a robot that she can do anything she wanted to she just had to dream.But Romeo didnt care if she was or wasn't a robot, he still loved her. One night romeo and juliet had dinner at juliets house, and she played piano so she played a romantic song that she wrote just for romeo... Romeo got just a little teary and when the song was over gave Juliet a BIG hug and said ' i knew that we were meant for eachother.' Romeo and juliets dinner was supposed to end at 7 but they ended it at 6 because, Juliet had a very difficult, hard day at work. Even though Juliet was a robot she could still talk, play, climb,protect, and help others!Juliet has the same feelings for romeo as he does for her but, she just cant....

Agribots           Agribots pick fruit, or vegtibles.               Pet Robots?           Robots? Playing like animals?   How strange! Your Not Driving           Nevada finalized some new rules that   it's LEGAL to drive in a robotic car your not acually driving!       The new Google product is a car that drives itself! Item_Response: The Cookerama       Many, many years ago there lived a man named Richard Hast. Richard was a very intelligent man, who loved to invent things. When Richard was just a little boy he always told everyone he knew that one day he would become an inventor. As he got older his love for inventing got stronger. When he was only 12 years old, Richard designed a robot rocket called the Shooter 9000. Sadly Richards robot rocket failed. But, did Richard give up, No. When Richard turned 14 his parents got him a whole set of robot parts that his dad had found at the dump. Richard was so excited that that night he decided to go down to the basement(where his lab was) and started to design a robot called Mr. Gower. Mr. Gower was designed to work in hospitals all around the world. This robot looked like a small cabinet on wheels that was used to store medicines locked up in the cabinet. Mr. Gower was a great idea, but something went wrong. Richard's dog Leroy found the robot on his desk one day. Leroy pushed the robot off of his desk with his tail, and the robot fell faster then a meteor coming towards earth. When Richard found the shattered pieces of not only his robot, but his heart. He began to cry. He cried and moaned until there was no more tears left inside of him. He thought he should give up. So, he put all of his inventions in the garbage. Then one day when his dad was getting ready to get in his car, he saw all of the robot parts in the trash. He grabbed all of the parts and headed towards Richards lab. When he got down in the basement he put all of the parts on Richard desk and wrote Richard a thoughtful note. it said, ' Richard, good things don't just come. You have to work hard and all the pieces will come together.' Underneath that it said, ' You can do anything you set your mind to.' Love Dad. The next day Richard went down to his lab. He saw the parts and the note. He smiled. I will make the best invention this world has ever seen! He yelled. For days and days he worked on his next invention, when finally after one whole month Richard proudly said, 'It's done!'Richard had designed a robot with the latest technology. It was called, The Cookerama. The Cookerama had a tall steel made body with long hair as yellow as the sun. It had spatulas for hands and an apron as blue as the sea. The Cookerama was designed to cook any meal you asked it to in under ten minutes. The Cookerama used the latest technology to prepare the most delicious meals ever! Richard decided to take his amazing invention to The House of Inventions. While he was in the car he could feel his heart beating. He could not believe that his dream was about to come true.When he got to the House of Inventions, he was automatically entered in the best invention contest. The winner of the contest would get five hundred dollars and a picture of themselves and there invention in the hall of inventions! Richard was very nervous because he was worried about his competition. The judges were deciding who would be the winner. He could feel the sweat dripping down his face. Then the announcer was going up to the podium to announce the winner. Richard was shaking. 'We are so lucky to have such amazing inventors this year. All of your inventions are brilliant, but remember, we can only choose one.' Richard now was shaking because his journey into inventoring was about to begin or end. ' The winner of the competition, Worlds best inventor, is... Richard Hast! ' Oh my gosh!' Richard said. 'I don't know what to say!' Everyone screamed in the audience. But, the scream that was the loudest of all, was his dads. 'I knew you could do it Richard!' He was a world sensation! He even got to be on the news! 'Is there anything you would like to say Richard?' The reporter said. No, nothing much just one thing. Thank you Dad! I couldn't have done it without you!

Item_Response: The Green Tomato Robot                   One day I way out side getting some tomato to see if my robot would respond to them. When i got back to my station he was not there instead there was a colossal mess of wires. I went out to my garden and there he was. he had a tomato like face and his arms legs and body where cherry tomatoes.           I went to go pick him up and bring him inside when i realized that he ate all of my tomatoes. There was one thing wrong because I didn't finish him he was green. When I pic him up he was crying so I got him inside and when he saw my tomatoes he stopped crying and ran right towards them I caught him be for he made another tornado- wish mess again.           We dis sided to go to the store to get some more tomatoes when I realized he didn't have a name so I sat and thought sense he's green and he's a tomato and a robot I'll name him Ro-to. I took him outside to play and he did exactly that.When it became  dark out we went inside. Then I saw that the man was falling over and i saw purple liquid and then I knew that he was shooting poison at him and then I Know that I had a multi per pis robot in my house and i didn't have to be scared anymore.

Item_Response: One day my dad asked me to wake up at 5:00 in the morning so we could go get our new dog and the dog was from Tenessee.  The dog was sent to Manchester but we had to get there around 6:00 to get the dog. When we got we ended up waiting until like 3:00 because the dog wasn't in the first van. Item_Response: Once there was a boy who was an only child. The boy was named Steven. And though he didn't have siblings, he had his only friend Rusty, Stevens dog, who he played with every day. Rusty was Stevens best and dearest friend he had ever had. But one day, Steven and Rusty were outside playing ball. Steven had over thrown the ball and Rusty did an amazing leap for it, but the ball rolled into the street. Rusty didn't see it coming, but Steven did. A speeding car came out of no where when Rusty had came out into the street to get the ball. Steven came running to save his dog, when he tripped over a tree root and couldn't get up.                  'It all happened so quickly,' Steven told his mom at the vet. 'I know son, but you have to stay strong for Rusty. Okay?' Stevens mom told him. 'Okay, Steven replied. Soon after, the vet came and talked to Steven. 'Rusty is very lucky. If he didn't glance over to where the car was, he would have been killed.' 'If he could have been killed and is luck and is safe how come I can't take him home?' Steven said angrily. 'Because he is still in bed shape and he will have to stay here a while,' the vet answered softly. 'But I-,' Steven tried to say. 'Then when can we take him home?' Stevens mom asked quickly before her son could say anything more. 'I don't know yet. He might have to stay here for a while or-,' the doctor said before looking at Steven. 'May I speak to you separately Miss Jenkins?' 'Of course,' she replied quickly. ' Rusty might have to be put down if he isn't responding well to the treatment,' 'Oh no!' Miss Jenkins said. They walked back to Steven who couldn't here the conversation. 'Thank You for giving us the low down on Rusty,' Miss Jenkins said. 'You're welcome. Please come back to check up on him anytime.' the doctor said. 'Thank You. We will,' Miss Jenkins said as her and Steven left.                  The ride home wasn't pleasent. Seven couldn't keep his emotions down. He cried the whole way home.                  A few weeks later, Steven and Ms Jenkins were at the vet saying their good-byes to Rusty. 'I'm sorry we have to put him down, but you know it wouldn't be right to let him live in pain any more,' Ms. Jenkins said. 'I know,' Steven said softly. While leaving the vet, Steven said, 'I wish we were in the future and I could get a robot so he would never die.' 'I know son,' Ms. Jenkins said.                  The next morning, Steven woke up to a big surprise. 'Here is your new robot!' Ms. Jenkins yelled. 'You actually found one!' they were both yelling now. 'Yes I no how said you were yesterday and I didn't like it, so here it is!' Ms. Jenkins said. 'Lets open it!' Steven said.                  The rest of Stevens day was a totally bust. The robot was just a toy a didn't talk or any thing.'I'm so sorry Steven,' it's okay mom. You didn't know the robot was just a piece of junk,' Steven went to bed that night and wished the robot was a real robot.                  The next morning, Steven woke up to his robot cooking breakfast with his mom. 'What in the world!' Steven screamed. 'Your wish came true Steven!' 'I know! I finally have the last thing I wanted before my childhood ends!'                  Steven went on with his life with his robot who had come to life. Sadly, Stevens robot grew to old to fix when Steven was an adult, but Steven didn't become sad like he did with his Rusty. He began his new life with a family.

Item_Response: THE MOST AMAZING ROBOT IN THE WORLD                          Another boring Monday at my house doing nothing but playing Black Ops 2. The only reason I'm at home is because it is a snow day. And usually I go down to where my mom works, so I usually go down there to eat breakfast. So I get off of my couch where I was dominating people on Black Ops 2. As I'm walking down to the restaurant I see something called the 'Robot Adoption Center.' So I go in there and all of the sudden all I see a ton of robots just sitting there waiting for someone to bring them home. As I walk out of the (RAC) I start sprint at super speed as if I'm a jet and when I get in the restaurant I go straight to my mom and I scream 'you got to come see this!' So I dragged her out of the restaurant and drag her to the (RAC) she says 'where are we going.'         'We are going to the awesomeness place in the world,' I reply. When I get there I ask her if I can get one and she said          'Let's look at them first.'          'Come on look at this one.' The one I was looking at was in the shape of a dog. And since my mom is allergenic to dog we couldn't get one, but this one didn't have fur. That means that we could get it because she isn't allergenic to metal. I said 'hey mom can I get this one.' I asked.           'Sure buddy.' she replied. When I got home I played with him, but I played with him for like 2 hours and the only one tierd out was me. Cause I forgot that he was a robot.           After I got tierd I started to playing Black Ops 2. When I did that all of the sudden he starts playing to. And he was better than me, and that is weird when a dog is better than yourself in a game. But I understood why he was better than me, because he was a robot, but I still treated him like he was a real dog. When my dad got home my dog started barking at him. And my dad was so scared that he screamed. My dogs name was Master. So he went upstairs and greeted my dad. My dad was like 'where did you get a dog?'           'At the (RAC).' I said           'What is that?' he asked           'The 'Robot Adoption Center' Dur,' I said like everyone knew about it.           'So what can he do?'           'Everything pretty much.'           'Let's bring him up to the cabin.' When we went to the cabin all of the sudden he started to play in the leaves like a real dog hopping around. Then we usually we stay there for 2 days but this time we stayed for the week playing with Master.            One day though he ran off into the woods. And my dad just whistled a hour later and he came straight to him. And Master was pretty useful around the cabin he could track down deer, he could play my games for me and he could do the most awesome thing in the world. He could do the Harlem Shake dance!                                                                THE END!

Item_Response: One day a boy called Bob Hamillton was watching t.v. He saw an ad about a live robot but he could se it was obviously fake. The commercial suddenley gave Bob an idea, he would create his own actuall living robot! He as a genius of science thought that surely he could acomplish this. He set out to collect various pieces of scrap metal, for he had no money.            First he visited the nearby junkyard for a circut board or mother board.   He thinks he will find theese in a discarded computer or t.v. Affter hours he find what he's looking for all of it though would have to be upgraded if he wants a real self working robot with high quallity A.I. Searching and more searching lead to no progress for the quantaum particle node XL or the screwdriver he needs. Though all be it by pure luck, he finds them while leaving the smelly old junkyard right under screwdriver and a wrench also as a bounus someXL MK 3 hype batteries next to it. He picks up all the scrap metal in the yard and proceeds to leave.        He starts working tiresly on his project. For two day and nights he works on his record breaking robot. Finally his robots is finished crome shell titanium lining the most complex serurity anyone has ever seen with their eyes, it was marvalous. But then by freak aciddent lightning struck his robot then nucular waste started raing down and a minature atom bomb struck on the robots face. Surelly Bob thought his robot was destroyed, but no! It came alive with power then greeted his master and promissed his loyalty. Then they marrily went on having fun and adventures helping people out until one day the robot saw a toaster, married it, and ran away. Then just like that Bobs adventure with his beloved robot, was over.

Item_Response: One day in midwestern Wyoming, there was a 8th grade boy named Roman McLane. Roman wasn't an ordinary 8th grader, but he was a stright A student. He has a really strong skill in technology and engineering. Roman was having trouble with math though. He always got 70's on his homework and quizes. He got so stressed out.       On a bright and warm Sunday afternoon, while his little sister, Victoria and his little brother, William were outside playing tag, Roman was studying for a test the next day. By 5:30 that night, Roman feel asleep. The next morning, he put a different t-shirt and grabbed his bag and headed out for school. he has never felt so nervous. He started quivering. He felt sick to his stomache.       When Roman arrived at his school, he took a big gulp of air, hoping to keep it. After lunch was math class. At lunch, Roman barely ate. He was to frightened. The time came. Roman left the cafeteria, feeling a knot in his stomache. It took nearly an hour to finish his test. Then finally, his teacher was handing out the tests he graded. Roman was sweating and hoping Mr. Grungler would forget him. Mr. Grungler handed Roman his test upside down.' See me after school,' Mr. Grungler said softly. Roman turned over his paper, he had a sharp look on his face when he saw the big, red 100 on his paper.       Roman walked in and sat on a chair.

Item_Response: Grand Rapids, MI   April 7th, 2043                  I had lived in Grand Rapids my entire life, I was familiar with the area, but comparing my childhood and now, it is so different. When I was just eleven, robots seemed so distant, everything was so different,but they were so much closer than my friends and I thought.              Now robots take up more than half of labor jobs, probably more, they can do farm work, factory work, anything really. The only jobs that humans still have is basically government, overlooking robots, or heads of corporations. This doesn't help the unemployment rate and now people mostly live in the city in run down apartment buildings and on the streets, begging for food and living off of garbage or welfare, or both. The government is in huge debt because they don't have anybody to tax anymore, most people have fled for Canada or Europe, where there are more jobs for people. I try to help the homeless and work as the overseer of the overseers of robots. I try to give them good pay but times are tough and ever since WW3 jobs have been plummeting.                  I  am lucky to live near to where I grew up, and my sister lives close by to me and my parents still live where I grew up. People that live on my street don't really own the buildings, but the government doesn't really care, they don't have any money to give the government. They can't catch them either because for one there are too many of them to catch. The second reason is  that there aren't many police officers to catch them. Robots do almost everything now, but they can't take us anywhere to catch them because they can't feed them in jail, so they usually just let them go, the soil in almost all of America is all out of nutrients so dust storms occur a lot. This doesn't really affect many people because very few people live in rural areas. Basically only robots and overseers.            War has been  on and off since North Korea bombed the White House, the president and  Congress have had to live in bunkers and haven't made speeches in months.  they don't have much control over the people anyways. Not many people live in Washington D.C. now in fear of being bombed again, the White House in ruins and so are the national monuments. Europe, most of them allies or independent, have been fighting on and off as well, but it is not as bad there as it is here.                After all these years humans tried to make it easier on themselves to do things, but now we need to help ourselves and become self supportive without these robots.This is my final log before my family and I will move to Europe and try to live like it was before the robot age.                                          10 years later....                      After Jake and his family moved to Europe an all robot Civil war began in America, the people couldn't defend themselves because the robots did it for them. Now the robots are now really alive and are trying to take over the world, government leaders are working together to try and stop this epidemic. People in Europe are scared that the robots will soon turn on them too. But they  will be more  prepared, Jake  Domagalski now roams Europe giving safety tips and has a best selling book on how to survive robots if needed. He is now the  Head of Defense for TUNEA, The United Nations of Europe and Asia. Hopefully they will be able to stop the epidemic before it's too late.                    May 11th, 2053                    The robots are now bombing TUNEA, and we are now developing a destabilizing device that you can throw at robots like a grenade and they will shut down. But we will need soldiers to do that, and we are NOT going to use any robots, I now have started recruiting men to fight in the TUNEA army, navy, and marines. I am worried we will lose this war because of one of my mistakes. We are trying to  fight for Hawaii and the Caribbean, but it will be a hard battle.              December 26th, 2056                 After 3 years of  fighting, we are now developing robots made from the remains of robots we have killed to be suicide bombers. Our  men are few and morale is down, we have been prioritizing to save as many people as we can, we have regained Washington D.C. But the robots just keep on coming and our men can't fight forever, they can, this will be an uphill battle.                 June 17th, 2060             After we had made our robots, they killed  hundreds of robots  per battle with only 2 or 3 of our robots. This war is finally in our advantage, but it isn't over yet. This is the head of defense for TUNEA, signing out.
