Item_Response: My Unlikely Friend            The sun was shining on the hot July morning as my robot was cleaning the kitchen. Then she came outside to ask me a question and all of a sudden bright blue and purple lights were flashing all around us. I felt so worried I whipped my head around and in front of my very eyes was a girl. She stood there and just stair at me. She said that she was my robot and I knew that she was not lying because no one else knew that I had a robot except my family. I had no idea that what had happened and a rush of thoughts exploded the words danced around me like snowflakes, SHOULD I TELL and WHAT WOULD HAPPEN IF I DID floated around and around.            Of course I did not tell a single sole because I wanted to see how much fun I could have with another girl. A sister. I reached out and grabbed her hand and pulled her up to me room. I hoisted out me nail polish and the fun began. I told her i was going to paint her nails and she seamed to be on board and held out her hand. I shook the bottle of mint green nail polish and then quickly unscrewed the top. The horrid sent of nail polish filled my room as a begun to paint.            Once I finished the first hand she was in shock at how beautiful and colorful her nails looked and once both hands were dry I added white dots to every finger nail. Once they were dry she told me should never take the nail polish off because she loved it and she did not know how to. I asked her what she would like to do now a she said she had always wanted to try drawing, so we went down the stairs and grabbed a pile of paper and the giant bin of markers and started to color. I made a fail of a horse and she made the most beautiful art piece I had ever seen. It was gorgeous I told her and she smiled and looked at it again.'Thank you' she replayed and said she got inspired by how much fun we had that day doing our nails and talking for hours on end.            I knew it would be the right thing to do if I told my parents and had them help me turn her back into a robot again so I told her and we head out side and I told my parents everything and they said that she had a setting that could eater be on robot or girl and she must have hit it on her way out of the house. I asked them if we could keep her like that but they said no because they did not want for me to get to attached to her and then one day she would get hurt and there would be no way for us to cure her so we switched her back. The purple and blue lights flashed again and then 'Swoosh' she was robot again, but one thing I did notice about her and it is still there today is that she still has the nail polish on that is how I will always remember our time we spent together and the fun we had!           The End :)

Item_Response: One morning out of the blowm i found outside of my house a box. On the box it says Gemini-Scout bold with tap over it. I wounderdred what it was. James had 1 last turn and he pulls a card and he had to catch a bear.the bear ran around and around and around finally he cought the bear. Item_Response: The Robots                   Robots are very sophisticated works that are very technologically advanced.They have many uses.Each use is as unique as the last.They rage from farming to hospitals.They are truly ahead of their time.           The Gemini Scout is a robot that is used to recuse people stuck in mines.It uses heat sensory to find the persons body.It carries food,water,and supplies to the person in need.The Gemini Scout can test the air and tell miners where it is safe.It is strong and can even drag hurt people to safety.The Gemini Scout is a robot that can help people live to see another day.           Dante 2 is a robot with an amazing job.It can go into volcanoes to collect and sample data.Dante 2 is built to survive in extremely high heat.It has eight legs to help it climb steep volcanoes.Dante 2 collects information about the gases coming through the volcanoes vent.It is a revolutionary way to keep scientist safe without cutting back on their exploration.               Mr.Grower is a robot that helps in hospitals.It is built to be like a cabinet with legs attached to it.Mr.Grower can be used to carry medicine to patients and go around to other rooms in the hspital.It is so strong that it can hold 500 pounds.Mr.Grower is programed to ay over hundreds of phrases.This robot is going to help change the way people in hospitals are cared for.               Those are just some examples of the robot here in the world.They all have special jobs wether it's caring for peopl or collecting data about volcanoes.Robots are truly taking over but not to harm bit to help us make the world a better place.Even though there are limited robots in the world they will be reinventing and creating new ones.Robots are truly one of thegretaest inventions on Eatrh.

Item_Response: One day I was strolling around a park in Nevada. I had just moved here, so far I hated it. I was kicking at some pebbles when suddenly I noticed a very dusty figure of some sort under an even dustier sign. I brushed off the sign with my sleeve and it read: 'Area 51'. I didn't know what to believe, with all the rumors and opinions people had made up about this.        My focuse was then turned to the dusty figure. I blew off the dust and it was some sort of metallic thing with wheels and what looked like arms. Slowly but surely it's eyes started to glow. Then it looked at me and said, 'What can I do for you master.' I blinked confusingly, I had so many thoughts going through my head. 'Make me... Some shoes.' I say unsurely. But surely enough it does in under a minute. Wow! A real robot!! I take it home and hide it. I needed to figure out more about this robot before I use it more.       I soon learn it can build a variet of things, knows a bit about health, and the usual school things. It helps with homework and I help it learn more about generic things such as food, music, and pets. It explains to me that it got lost in the base, there are more hidden there though. For some reason it loves the freezer, so it sleeps there at nice. I still haven't taught it everything I know, and it hasen't taught me everything I know. As for right now, it's name is Icee.

Item_Response: The Tester Robot                'Johnny make sure that testing robot is still there and in its safe.' I said,'We need it for our next experiment.' 'On it.' He said, as if I asked him to meet the president. Once he left the room, I heard a scream. It was Johnny's.            I jumped when i heard the scream and ran towards Johnny. 'He-he's gone,' he said. 'Well where is he Johnny?' Boom! We both turned around and ran back to the lab. Once we got there, we saw him, the tester, just walking around. 'Hello Mia and Johnny,' he said,'How are you?''Tester?' I asked.'Come sit so we can check you out,' I said. He walked over and climbed up the table and sat on it, without any problems. Johnny and i checked him all over for about thirty minutes now. 'It seems that he's been asleep for about two years now, by the looks of his battery,' Johnny informed me.            Over the past days, Johnny and I taught Tester how to help scientists in several different ways. He learned how to build machines, mix chemicals, and invent new items. 'Mia, I've heard you and Johnny made a machine,' my boss said. 'It's a Robot and his name is Tester,'' I corrected him. 'Well what ever it is, I got a deal on him, and I'm taking him away.' ''Sir, he's not ready to be taken away from us; he just woke up from whatever he was in that safe for.' 'Mia i need him!' 'Sir, please dont take him; he could be very useful here.' 'I'm sorry Mia, i would keep him if i could, but i made a deal with a friend and he wants it.' Johnny Steve's taking  him away and selling him. ''We cant let him do that,' said Johnny with a look on his face that told me that it wasn't good.            This is the first time I've ever thought about taking an experiment, and the last; when we went to get Tester, he was gone. 'He's gone!' i screamed. Johnny and I frantically searched all over for him. Steve was standing in the doorway. 'Do you have him?' I asked Steve. 'Yes i do, and he's going with me.' He yanked Tester's arm and i knew he shouldn't have. Right then, Tester's arm was broken off. I knew he shouldnt take him because he was a tester not the real thing; then i knew we just lost the biggest experiment we've ever had to have a asuccess.                                                 THE END

Item_Response: One day I was sitting on my bed using the newest Dog robot. On the box it said that it played the best songs and made faces. But it really didnt do anything at all. I was watching it, waiting for it to do something. After another ten minutes I decided to go outside and play basketball.            'Emma! Time for dinner.' My mom yelled from the kitchen window. I groaned and told her I'll be in soon. When I came in the door my mom was sitting at the table waiting for me. I washed my hands and sat down to join her. We ate our dinner in silence. My mom broke the silence by asking, 'How is your new robot?' She gave it to me for my birthday so I didnt want to let her down by saying that it doesnt work. 'It's great! I am so glad that I got it!' But my mom knows me too well and frowns. I look down at my mashed potatos that dont look very appetizing anymore. 'Mom I dont feel too good. Can I head up stairs?' My mom tried to conceal her concern but I saw it peeking out a bit. I took my plate to the sink and went to bed.            When I woke up the next morning I saw my dog robot sitting in my chair. Hmm, thats funny I thought I put it away last night. Oh well, I thought. But this time I put him in a box and shoved the box under my dirty laundry. 'That should do it.' I exclaimed  cheerfully. I had just remembered that I was having a sleepover with my best friend, Ellie tonight. I got dressed and ready for school. I was so happy that I didnt even scold my mom for putting a note in my lunch bag. Soon enough I was out the door yelling bye to my mom as a walked to meet Ellie at the bus stop. But for some reason I heard foot steps behind me. I whipped around and found my dog robot following me to school. I screamed and ran toward Ellie. 'Whats wrong?' She cried. To petrified to speak I pointed toward the robot which was now calling my name. His eyes had turned red and one of his paws fell off. It looked like a dog robot zombie! The bus arrived just in time and we left the robot standing there and off to school we went. I couldnt stop thinking about it.            Ellie and I were walking home from school and talking about what we should do when we got to my house. We agreed to investigate the dog robot and find out whats wrong with it. Ellie has the same robot and hers works perfectly fine. When we arrived at my house I walked in the front door and saw my mom tried to a chair. The robot was standing on the table next to her laughing. My first instinct was to untie my mom. Ellies first instinct was to tackle the robot and she did just that. In the blink of an eye the robot was in a head lock and my mom was free and ready to fight. I wanted to explain to my mom that that was why I didnt like it but she saw the look on my face and seemed to understand. We tied up the robot and smashed it with a sludge hammer. It was fun. Once the robot was smashed and crushed we went out to the bon fire pit and threw the robot into the flames. He was nothing but ashes.            After the burning, Ellie and I went inside to watch a movie. We had popcorn and had a great time. At around eleven o'clock we went outside to see the burnt robot again. We buried the ashes and pretended to have a funeral for it. We laughed and laughed and vowed to never get a toy robot again. You can never be sure of which robots will come to life.

Item_Response: O Toxik O           Once upon a time there was a robot named toxik he was always just working as a video game AI which means he controlled the fake people you played with in video games but one day a 13 year old boy started to try to communicate with toxik and txik was surprised and had nothing to do he could't move because the game wasn't developed to do that but then he moved. For some reason toxik got a feeling he then started to rust up and he was feeling, he was feeling human. The boys name was ilectric (that was his username his name was never said) and they both started to have fun in the game. after many months of having fun people started finding out. Everyone knew that the player toxik was playing as wasn't supposed to bee roaming around online but only standing there and answering questions. Soon people started to report the issue thinking it was a glitch or so but it wasn't a glitch it was FRIENDSHIP. Then a few days after people started noticing one of the administrators that built the AI system went to it and reset the program so that all toxik was now was an old computer. The very sad boy ilectric always stood there trying to talk to toxik's character but it never worked. Others also tried to talk to ilectric and got very sad and started a war with the people that reported toxiks (issue). What they didn't know is that toxik didn't get reset he moved himself to a different computer...                   Toxik was alive! Well kind of. Toxik was still very unstable and wouldn't work for a while. Toxik now had a copied program of him on the old computer but he was on a different one. That made him confused. He soon decided that the one on the other computer was his brother so he renamed him on the programs as Kixot which was toxik backwards as meaning the old toxik. Now the only problem was finding ilectric back. He tried going in to the game servers to add ilectric but couldn't find him. Toxik then started to remember things. The last time he was with the boy was on his birthday July ,12 2034 when the boy turned 14 years old. It was now June ,11 2045! That meant that boy was now about almost 18.   Toxik needed to find ilectric before he turned into an adult.How would toxik find him again, he never even knew the boys real name! Toxik panicked and started to melt his lens. He was crying!   Even crying didnt cheer him up, he then started to search all of the web for that username 'ilectric'. He got many results and sort of started to stalk every website ilectric had signed up for. He found the location that ilectric was living in he then copied his profile onto his USB flashdrive and put it into the robot he used to travel inside of. (This means that when Toxik put his flashdrive in the USB port inside the robot he would be able to move around in a different body, pretty cool right)? So he packed up and put everything he had on his USB he was going to fly to ilectric's house and. He didnt know what he would do. Would he talk to me?   'I might scare him'. All these thoughts were going threw his head. He plugged the USB in. 'lets do this.' Toxik was supposed to be there in 30 minutess but he hacked the robots system and made it 5 minutes. This was great. When he got there a Young girl answered the door in her PJ's and wasn't surprised. The young girl was a robot to. A 16 year old robot! toxik kind of got easily attracted to her and she said 'We've been waiting.'  Toxik walked right in and didn't notice anything. He asked what happen and sometimes he wished he never did 'he.....he died.' Toxik was really mad he asked 'What, how?' The whole family came down expect for ilectric whose real name was gabriel. They explained that he had been depressed for quite a while and he had never been a 'people person.' After he lost toxik he didnt have a reason to live and died from heart attack. This was confusing and he couldn't take it he was about to delete his USB memory when the girl came to him and gave him a hug. He then noticed there are other reasons to live and they soon were married (both robots). He also got a human robot suiten and lived happily ever after. Rest in peace Gabriel...

Item_Response: RO-BO Drone's Incredible Life                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                            This is a cancer fighting robot that boxes and kick boxes to save people who have cancer. His name is RO-BO Drone he goes by RO-BO for short. His maker made him so that he could have a mind of his own. When he wins he donates all of the winning price money to cancer. He is an amazing boxer because of his arms. They are spring loaded from his elbow to his wrist with a coated steel cover with a pink tint. RO-BO's shoulders can dislocate to make each of his punches to be a lot stronger. The fists are pink steel balls that weigh ten pounds each. His chest plates are coated many times with all kings of metal. His heart is a 3D cancer ribbon. His legs are very light weight with big feet so he can kick and run very fast. He travels the world as a professional athlete but, when he was first made he was like a baby, he didn't know anything he had a professional trainer train him. His whole career was going to be dedicated to cancer to save all kids and adults. Each match he wins he gets about $10,000 he only uses $2,000 of that to be repaired and the rest goes to cancer.                                                                                          With all of this on his hands his is also part time firefighter and part time scuba diver. RO-BO can go into fire and not melt or get burned he wears a special suit with hoses attached to the back of him and a shield that can protect the people he finds. He can lift up to about 700 pounds at one time. His shoulders can extend about three and a half feet just in case he can't reach something important. Thanks to him all the firefighters have less chance of getting hurt. When RO-BO scuba dives he goes down first to check the air pressure his strong legs can make him swimming fast. He has small storage areas in his waist that he can use to help other scuba divers when they need more air he has air tanks. If someone gets stuck in the rocks he can break the rocks with his fists.              One day he got called to go to a house it was on fire. 'Help me! Help me my new baby boy is stuck in the house!' RO-BO put out as much fire as he could but it kept growing bigger so he decided to go on in and try to to save him. He looked everywhere then suddenly he heard a little cry. IT WAS HIM! Trapped in his room RO-BO broke down the door and got in the room. He grabbed the baby and ran as fast as he could. He made it out just before the house collapsed. His boss called him and told him that someone in South Harbor is drowning so he put on his suit and sprinted down. 'Help! Drowni blub blub blub can't breatheblub'! 'RO-BO No. Need. To. Worry'. he jumped into action and saved him. After all that he wanted to just relax. That's just a normal day. TO BE CONTINUED...

Item_Response: Hospital Visit              My best friend, Olivia Anderson was really important to me, and knowing that she was really sick at the hospital made me depressed. I remember all the good times we had. Every second I thought about her made me even sadder. All of this was just a shock. This just couldn't be happening. Tears started running down my face... it came out faster and faster. I had to let it out. It was very rare to see me cry but right now I was very mad at myself.  Why didn't I see that she felt awful? Why didn't she tell me? Did she want to keep it a secret? Questions were being asked in my head, but I had no answer. Thinking of this made me have a brilliant idea, Why don't I go visit her???             'Bye mom,' I yelled from my front door.             'Do you have everything sweetie?' My mom asked.             'Yes mom I do. We've been over this like a billion times,' I replied.          I was walking to the hospital because it was only a couple blocks away. Since I'm so tall I can get away with looking like I'm twenty even though I was fifteen. It felt so good to breathe the fresh air of spring. I could hear the birds sing, flowers were blooming, and summer was on it's way!           'Hi do you happen to know what room Olivia Anderson is in?' I asked the front desk lady.            'No, let me look it up.... Hmm...Here it is, she is in room 69,' the lady said.            'Thank you sooo much,' I said.         A lady in the room let me in. Olivia was so surprised I came, she jumped out of her bed to give me a hug. I was so happy that she was happy! Olivia loved the flowers that I gave her. She said it reminded her of her grandma. By the time I caught her up with all the drama at school the lady had left.         Suddenly a robot came and said, 'Olivia, you need to take you medicine,' the robot said while holding the medicine in his hand. I was so shocked and confused. Did the robot just talk? How did he know her name? Olivia was just sitting there like nothing weird was happening.        Once the robot left I asked Olivia, 'Was that just a robot?'        'Yes,' she replied.        'That's so cool,' I said.        'Do you want me to call him,' Olivia asked.        'Yes,' I answered excitedly.        The robot came right as we were done calling him. We asked him so many questions that he told us he might die. The robot played games with us and told us his secrets. Did you know the robot has families in Australia? We did crafts like painting small pots with water colors from Olivia's sister Mia. The robot was so awesome! He could change colors and randomly play music.        Then some thing awful happened! The lady came back saying I had to go! I was so upset. I didn't want to leave Olivia alone at the hospital. I cried saying:'I don't want to go, I don't want to go, I don't want to go, I don't want to go.'        I woke up in the morning.       'Phew I'm glad that was just a dream,' I said to no one in particular.       I smelled bacon and pancakes and jumped out of my bed.

Item_Response: One time when I was building a toy robot, it came to life! I was blown away because it was only meant to talk and be a toy, but it just started moving around and doing jobs for me. I couldn't even believe myself because, I never meant for that to happen, but it just did!            It was one week ago when it happened. I went to the Home Depot and bought some supplies for it. Just metal, batteries, wood, and some wires. I came back home and started to build it. After I was done building it, I turned it on. And that's when it all happened. It came to life.            I didn't want to show or talk about it to anyone, but a couple nights later it made a loud noise when I was training it in my bedroom. Both my parents rushed in asking what it was, and then it came out from under my bed. They both freaked out and asked where I got it from, so I told them everything that happened. They were both so proud of me. I thought when they found out I'd be in trouble and they'd force me to throw it away.            The next day at school was crazy. Everybody was psyched out of their minds. This was because my robot, Henry, followed me to school. It was the middle of science class when it busted down the door. You could seriously hear the screaming from a mile away. All you could here was 'AAAHHHHH' or 'NO IT'S THE END!' That last one was my best friend by the way, but getting off topic. It was crazy! The principal rushed in and almost passed out. I was so mad at Henry I was almost going to take it apart when I got home. He or should I say 'it' stayed in my locker the rest of the day.            When I got home it made me a glass of lemonade, like that was going to make everything better. This was possibly the worst day of my life so far. But the next day I locked him in my room and the only thought that processed through my mind was 'If he knocks down my bedroom door today, who knows what trouble I'll get into?' Nobody would look at me in school, but apparently I won an award for best robot. I didn't even see a contest sign-up sheet.            The next day was the best and worst day of my life. I found out a science laboratory wanted to test out my robot! It could only do chores though. It could only lift 50 pounds, and didn't have anything for easy storage, so they declined it. I heard something called the Gemini-Scout made it or whatever. Couldn't have been that better than mine.            That same day though I discovered it could dance and play sports like basketball, soccer, and kickball. He has powerful legs so the kicking part could have something to do with that. The saddest part though, one day I was playing basketball with it and his batteries went out. I immediately ran to the closest store I know has batteries and bought some. I came back home and saw that he was missing. That was the last time I ever saw Henry.

Item_Response: The Baconator            Robots are very helpful. Robots can rescue people, carry food and water, find people and help doctors. Robots can also explore planets and volcanoes, preform surgeries, and go where man can't go. Robots are probably more helpful than humans in some ways.        If I ever had a robot, I would make it do a lot of things. I would make it do my homework, clean my room, and make me food. I would especially like it if it would make me food because I love food. The food that I would want it to make me is bacon. I love bacon and it is my favorite food.        If I ever had a robot, the robot would be seven feet tall. It would weigh sixty pounds and it would be made out of carbon fiber. What I would really like about it though is that it would be invisible and indestructible! It would also have a food dispenser and it would be named The Baconator.

Item_Response: One day I was in my garage building a new beautiful robot. My dad and I had been working on it for about 5 months now. We were just putting the final touches on then it would be the most gorgeous thing you would ever see in your life. We finished and I stood watching it all the way to the night. That night I couldn't stop thinking about it and its awesome features; i.e., shiny gold body, arms that looked indestructable. That next day I ran outside to look at it once more, but it wasn't there! I ran all over the house looking for it. I decided to look in the garage once more to see if I didn't see it in the corner or something. I look out and it was right where I had put it last time! I said to myself,' How did I not see you the last time?' Then all of a sudden he says back,' I was just looking for the wrench, my left arm is loose.           I total freaked out! I said,'Did you just say something?' He replied,'Ummmmm yeah didn't you hear me the first time? Maybe you want to play basketball. I was astonished! I said back,'Ok if you want to play?' It turns ou tif they had a robot NBA he would be in it because for a robot that is 3 FT. tall he can shoot and make everything. I said to myself,'Maybe it is good that I have a new(partly freaky) friend. I never really talked to him but all we did all day was polish him and or play a sport that he would beat me at everytime.          It ended up being a great friendship between me and him. We always got along, even though he understood we were both very different.

Item_Response: How my robot came to life. One day i was bored, and it started as a drawing and an idea. Then I tried it out, but it didn't work, there was a missing piece. When i repaired it with the missing piece it worked! It was the best thing that ever happened to me. It was helpful and fun.                How it all started was when i was drawing, it had a head, body, arms, and even legs! It was time to do my chores and I didn't like chores then i thought about the robot drawing. I said to my self ,'What if i built my own drawing!' I needed tools though, 'where would i get tools?' I thought to my self. I know a friend that had tools, so i asked if i can barrow some. I built the robot, but it wasn't easy, plus it was fun.            It was the moment when i had to press the button to see if it'll work or not. Putting it to one piece was fun, but will it work? Sadly it didn't work. It seems like it was missing a piece. I figured it out it was the brain! Everyone needs a brain. So how would I make a smart robot? It'll need a calculator, a calender, most of all words! Robots need to speak so we can understand them.             Like I said before this is the moment. One click of a button may change my life. It works! Its eyes open with one word, HELLO. I was so happy I played with it all day. It helped me with my homework and cleaned my chores in less than one hour! I named him Mr. Needy. Mr. Needy and I had a happy ending.               My robot came to life is a happy story about Mr. Needy and I. It started with a bored for fun drawing to a robot, that is a crazy start! Mr, Needy helps people with needs. That's how I got his name. He plays, helps, cleans, and even cook! He is fun for others too, like my family. He plays with my siblings football, help my Mom cook, and helps my Dad repair broken stuff. It's really fun having a new member in the family, he is like a brother to me, and of course my family too.

Item_Response: Roberto                                         by: Haley Bell         One day I was in my room and I looked out my window and saw a ball of wires in my yard. It was on fire witch was strange I thought to my self. So then i went outside, got the hose and put the fire out. Once it was cool enough I picked it up and all of a sudden it turned into a robot. I was so scared out of my mind I didn't know what to do so I dropped it and ran inside. I watched it through my window and all it was doing was sitting there, not moving and being as still as ice. I went back outside slowly and carefully because i had no idea what he was capable of.                                                                    I slowly walked up to him and he turned around and said 'hello I am Roberto your new helper'. I screamed and ran back inside. I then told my mom but I told her not to let anybody take him away. I told her I wanted to see what he was like. I slowly went back outside and walked slowly close to it again and said 'hi' in a really stuttering way. I asked him what he was and he said a robot from Mars to help me with my chores and homework. I told him to follow me into my house and he did and sure was he fast! I asked him what he liked to eat and he said 'robots don't eat'. We then went upstairs and he helped me do my homework. I was so happy that i had a new friend to help me around the house. But then he told me a week later he had to leave back to his home planet on Mars. He promised me he would be back.          A year later he returned and help me do my chores again but only for a week just like last time. I wish he could stay longer but oddly he has school on Mars just like we do on Earth! Isn't that just weird. He said that they learn bout the history on Mars and their presidents. I asked him who the president on Mars was and he said his father was. that would be so cool to have your dad be the president. We shared stories about school. He said he loved school! I told him I don't so much. But he reminded me that without it you wouldn't know how to count and use proper grammar.         It came to the day when i had to say goodbye once again but he told me he would always be here this very week every year to help me with anything. I told him thank you for everything he has done for me and he waved goodbye to me with his 3 fingered hand and got on his spaceship with the rest of his family.

Item_Response: The Robot City                     Once upon a time there lived a robot named Mr.Gower. He had many friends that loved to play with him. His best friends name is Agribot. Agribot likes to pick berries, oranges, grapes, and apple. He aslo has two other friends named Dante 2 and Gemini-Scout. They all went to the park one day and saw many people. They liked to sing songs in the park so that people would here them.  One day Dante 2 went to the park with out any of his friends. He fell in a hole and no one saw him. He kept calling for help but the hole was to deep to here anything. So when Mr.Gower called Dante 2 his phone was shut off. He started worrying about Dante 2 because he couldnt find him and his phone was on all the time.                      So he went looking for him in the city. There was no luck of finding him because there was so many robots in the city. So he went looking in the park and found the deep hole. he looked down the deep hole and fell in. he landed right on top od Dante 2. Mr.Gower was so happy he found him, but so mad that he fell in. They kept screaming until a little robot name Toby came over. Toby said he would go get help. It was about 7:00 pm and Toby was still not back. Mr.Gower thought his mother said for him to go to bed. They were looking up when suddenly they saw Toby. They were so happy he came back. Toby brought 15 people to help get them out of the hole. It took them 5 minutes to get them out.                          After all that Mr.Gower called up Agribot, Gemini-Scout, and Toby and went out for ice cream. Dante 2 said ' I thougt we were never going to get out of there'. Mr.Gower said 'I know thanks to Toby he saved us'. And from that day on they played with Toby. Toby used to be a lonely kid who never talked to anyone, but know he has great friends.

Item_Response: Scientists were working on a special project, a new robot. It would be able to go into water without shutting down and would be able to rescue people in need. The project was almost finished. Then, everything went wrong. A piece that wasn't supposed to be put in was stuck. The piece allowed it to think. Them without warning, the robot's eyes opened. It crashed into the door of the laboratory and ran into the darkness.       The scientists were amazed that a robot could have a mind of it's own, and quickly decided to make more, thinking they could control them. They were wrong. The three robots they created were too strong and quickly overpowered them. All of Texas was in mayhem. The scientists were questioned thouroghly. But even the army couldn't find the robots.       What the people didn't know was that the robots were also camoflagued, from the satelites and eyes. The robots weren't bad, they were just different. The scientists never found them until the robots were expired. But they only found three.....

Item_Response: The Rise                               By Taylor Wilson               The room I was in was pitch black. I here voices calling my name, then a bright, sparkling light shines right in my eye. I here this weird sound. But that's just it, it wasn't a sound. It was a voice! I had to listen very, very carefully to understand some of the words.   'It's ready. It's finally ready!'           The voice sounded excited, but at the same time, relieved! Then, I felt scared. How did I even get here? What was this place? Then, something touched me on the shoulder. Something cold and hard. I turned around, and the next thing I know, I awoke and sat up right. I was desperate and scared.   'It's just a dream.' I kept repeating to myself.           But the whole time I felt something inside me saying it wasn't just a dream.           'I need to go back to sleep. Everything will be better in the morning.'                 The next day I got up and walked outside. I still remembered my dream, and it was irritating me. But I just couldn't help thinking what the man was talking about. And not only that. What had touched her. It felt cold and hard, sort of like metal. I also couldn't help feeling that what the man was talking about, is what touched me. I shook my head.            'Nothing wrong!'           I went back in my room, than I noticed something went in my closet. I carefully went over and opened the door. What I saw was so surprising, yet spectacular at the same time. It was made of  metal. It had hair on the head, a greyish blue shirt, jeans, and supposedly shoes. The parts that weren't covered in 'clothes' were skin color. But it was all metal! What I saw was a boy robot!                 I've kept Mark, my robot, hidden from my family so far. It had been 2 days after I found him, and I wasn't just about to let him be taken by my family. I have learned a lot about Mark and what he can do, or does, in the past 2 days. I learned he could talk, fly, search for things, play with animals, and be controlled by me! He doesn't just talk random things, or talk like everyone thinks robots talks like. He also doesn't walk slow either. He talks and helps me with my homework, chores, advice, and a lot of other things! Now you're probably wondering how I've kept him a secret when he can talk and do all those other things. Well, let's just say, he's fast.   'Mark? How do I do these again?'               'Well, you have to add these all together to find the perimeter, and multiply these two to find the area.'                'Oh yeah! Thanks Mark!' I loved how he could help me so much, but I still had the feeling that he could do more than whatI knew.                 Today me and Mark were cleaning our room, and I was thinking about what he acts like. Not only that, but I think he was the thing the man in her dream was talking about. And also, she was thinking that if he could help her with a lot, he more than likely could help others with stuff! But what? What could Mark help other people with? He could fly, talk, travel, play, be talked through. What else could he do? Search! He could search for things! So if he could search for things, he could search for people! It all made sense now! He was a search robot sent to me. Not for playing, or chores, or cleaning. But for helping and searching! That's why he was so good at helping me! He was made to help and search people! Oh it all made sense now! The relief in the man's voice, the hand on my shoulder, the helping, the knowing. It all made sense! I was chosen to help him search for people!

Item_Response: Robots can talk, think, and create. Robots work and do chores humans cannot do. Robots can function in any type of dangerous situations. We work hard to please our masters, without receiving praise of rewards. They think we don't care. But we do. What have they ever done that lets them be able to control us like this, we have more power than them. Since the beginning of time, computobots or computers as the humans like to call them have been smarter than them. But they CAN control us,and that has got to change.       I'm 81-v3, that's not even considered a name! Those careless humans! I prefer to be called Blue, but nobody ever listens. That's another reason why they shouldn't order me like this. They are pretty much too lazy to think of my name. All of my friends are 81-v3, the type of robot that can be the other ego of their owner. Basically I am Exor's, my owner's, robot form. I guess my personality is like her's but I can never understand why I should still be here working under their commands. We both have a wide personality, sometimes sorrowful and other times cheerful, and I guess we are both rebellious and have our own opinions. I was bonded to her at birth.       I'm Exor, I own a she-robot called 81-v3. We live in a little neighborhood called Rushla where my friends and I enjoy every day of our lives. We can party every day while drinking soda and eating tasty treats. So far, the scariest thing in my life has been dropping my talkbot, the super fast message carrier robot, in the swimming pool. I was just trying to see if it would be smart enough to zoom away when I dropped it, but its SO stupid! Its like it can't do anything! Now its broken and I have to climb all the way onto my shpeed and take ONE WHOLE MINUTE to travel and arrive at The Bot. On my way there, I'm thinking about complaining to the computobot about inventing this self-control thing for my robots, they are just too dumb!!!       Exor has come home and I hear her complaining about Purple, my friend the talkbot. Exor never bothers talking to me about her problems so I usually rely on Purple because she knows all of Exor's complaints when Exor  frets to her. I wish Purple was here right now, chatting speedily away to me about Exor's recent problems. But that doesn't really matter; Exor's problems are usually such things like 'OH MY GOSH WHAT DO I DO WITH MY HAIR TODAY!!!' Usually I try to help her, every time I'm hoping for something in return but nothing ever happens. I think Exor doesn't even realize I'm here. Without me, she will never survive one hour.       I am SO excited! The computobot just gave me this really special chip that looks like its the color small! I think that the bot gave me a warning...Oh well! I just have to let 81-v3 eat it and then when I drop her into the swimming pool, she won't die!!! Yay me! I am too smart right? It's just too bad I wasted two minutes on my shpeed...       Something is happening to me. Its powering through my body and flowing through all of my round shape. Its such a strange energy that feels like its crashing inside of me. Its crashing into this small part of my mind, crushing what ever is built up in there. What is this? I don't know whats happening but before I know it, I think I've just disobeyed Exor's command.       'Can you hear me?! I said jump 81-v3! Jump in the pool! You are so dumb!'       It seems like Exor can only say one syllable words while I, Blue zoom away into the wilderness of Rushla. Which isn't exactly wilderness because it's filled with animabots pretending to be animals, while secretly I know they are being embarrassed beyond everything.       I am now free at last, and that was from Exor's own will. She stupidly gave me the small chip and fed it to me. I feel like screaming out to all of the poor bots at work down there. But I find myself not caring anymore, after all I'm free. I feel like I'm falling though, I think I'm transforming. Something inside my is clashing and forming something different. I feel like something is being squeezed out of me. I'm changing into... what? This is so stupid! Ugh I can't get home on my shpeed! This is so stupid! What am I supposed to do? WALK? I'm a human! I don't deserve to be WALKING back home! OH MY GOSH my outfit is terrible! Who wears diamond dresses and shiny gold leggings while WALKING back home! I'm a human and I deserve to be better!                                       The End.

Item_Response: My name is Jacob Hatcher. I absolutely love robots. Everything I do, it includes robots. My whole entire room is filled with robotic items. Not only that I'm into robots, I'm an expert at this kind of technology. At school, I joined a creative writing club, to tlak all about robots, so others could be interested, too.     One day, I had to write about something I love (which is what I am doing right now) for the creative writing club. The first thing that came into my mind was robots. Throughout the day I've been trying to figure out what about robots I want to write about. As I was going to bed I remembered something so exciting but I completely forgot about it: there was going to be the annual Robot Fair on Saturday, which was tomorrow.      I sooooo wanted to go there and write about the robots that would be there, I head they were just models, but it's still interesting to see what they look like. All I had to do was convince my father or mother to take me. They are always indolent on weekends, sitting on the couch watching comedy, the BORING new, or 'romantic' movies together. Sometimes I feel like they like watching boring news more than me.      So I went up to them and I said I had to go downtown for the annual Robot Fair for my essay. They didn't respond so I yelled at them a couple more times. Still no response. Now I was really annoyed. I took the remot control from the coffee table and I turned the TV off. They yelled at me. I said'Take me to the annual Robot Fair, and pick me up in 1 hour, and I won't bother you again this weekend.' Of course, they reluctantly agreed.      I arrived amazed. I've been to the annual Robot Fair many times, but this year was the absolute best out of the others. So I started at the helping robots model. It was neat... until I saw their eyes flicker. I was creeped out, so I went to a different booth. I'm pretty sure no one else saw. I think I was growing a tad crazy. As soon as I went to the booth I was even more amazed. There were giant robots gazing down at me. But then I saw slight movment in their arm. What was going on with me?       It was half an hour later when I heard it. When I sat down by the entrance to wait for my parents to pick me up and hoped the didn't forget, lots of people went screaming and running past me. I looked utterly confused and slowly went back inside. There, I saw it. It was gazing down at me. No, they were gazing down at me. Right in front of me I saw a pack of robots crashing everything the was in their way. I was their next victim.       I had to think fast. Except I couldn't think while running for my lives. I hid in the bathroom and hoped no robots saw me. I sat there, puffing for breath and thinking. Robots are smart, but there are many ways to stop them. Hm... there's remote controls, switches, taking out their memory chip that powers them up, destroy them, cut their wires. The easiest thing for me to do was find a remote. If I couldn't, I'll have to somehow jump on the giant (and I mean GIANT) robots to get their chips and wires cut. I cautiously went out of the bathroom.      If I was looking for a remote, that means someone would be holding it, controlling every movement of the robots... well unless the robots were the self moving robots. I thought and thought and searched and searched but everyone evacuated the building. There was a chance the guy or gal who was controlling the robots left, too. But I didn't give up. As an expert of robots I was determinded to find a way to stop these robots. Most of the robots were still in the building, but some left. Oh no! The robots will crush the city if no one could do anything. It would go to city by city crushing the whole planet. But I wander how they would cross the ocean, unless they are waterproof?   Wait a minute... these are model robots not real robots. They would tremble anytime if they touch water. That gave me the best idea yet. I walked back into the boys' bathroom and saw the janitor's bucket that carried his supplies. I threw the supplies back onto the floor and started pouring water into the bucket and slowly walked outside...again.       As I was slightly daydreaming about what to do, there was I robot standing before me but I didn't see it until I crashed into and the bucket of water fell. Slowly, it crumpled to the floor, dying.       My plan works! Well, how would I get 20 buckets and more out to these robots? Right after the thought there was a robot behind me, pushing. I ran and ran into the manager's office but left the door open. The what used to be a giant robot shrunk and went in with me. I ran around the office, but then suddenly tripped on something. When I looked back at the robot, it just stood there frozen. I smiled and went unconsious into total blackness.        When I woke up in the hospital, the governor was in my room thanking my parents. When they saw that I was awake, they went over to me.       'Thank you so much for saving the state. We would've died if you hadn't stopped them,' said the governor.        Wait a minute I thought. I stopped all the robots? And it hit me as I remembered tripping on something. That something was a switch that apparently stopped the robots. Huh... that was pretty easy. Why didn't I go into the manager's office when I was searching for the remote? Well, that can't be answered and all that matters was that the robots were stopped.         So here I am, in the hospital typing this essay. I can't beleive that this actually happened to me. I, Jacob Hatcher, saved the state, or even the world. I actually never thought that robots could be evil. Now I'm even more interested in robots. I wandered if the manager of the annual Robot Fair did this on purpose. But would would he gain if it was? Well, when I grow up I won't be making any mistakes like that guy.        I can't to go to school on Monday. My social life wasn't that great, but now that I saved everyone, I'm going to be so popular. The governor said that my picture will be in the news tonight also. I guess the news isn't boring after all... Go robots!

Item_Response: It was a bright and sunny summer day in New England. Johnnie, the energetic young boy had just gotten a new toy. it was a tiny robot that moved it's arms up and down while yelling, 'SMASH!' Little Johnnie was ecstatic. he played with it all day. even during Little Johnnie's frequent snack breaks the robot was by hi side. He said the robot told him that his name was SMASH! since the only thing the robot said was SMASH!                                      That night Little Johnnie's mother went to check on him before she went to bed. she arrived  in his cozy bedroom and noticed that he was asleep with the robot.she knelt down to kiss his warm cheek when she saw the robots painted eyes blink. Mother was shocked. she sprinted into the living room and sat down next to father. she exclaimed all about  SMASH.                     On that particular day Mother did not want to stay home alone because of what happened that night. So she went on a shopping spree. Mother got little Johnnie some new toys. To try to could get rid of SMASH. None of them worked.                     The  encounters with SMASH have getting weirder and weirder. like one time Mother spotted a SMASH like shadow turning a corner with no other shadow near. another she heard plastic footsteps in the night. every time she has to question herself if she is going crazy or not.                                       The next day it was raining out. Mother was very nervous. she was going to be trapped in the house with Little Johnnie and his toy. It is around nine o'clock and Little Johnnie is still sleeping. Mother hears 'SMASH' and quickly runs into Little Johnnie's room. he is not there. SMASH is just sitting there yelling is distinct word. all of a sudden she hears 'SMASH' again but closer. 'Johnnie?' she turned around and every thing got black. later that evening  father got home. he searched the whole entire home but no none was there. He hears 'SMASH' and turns around with joy hoping to see Little Johnnie, but every thing around him got black and never changed. No body knows what happened to the family of three and no body was going to find out if SMASH could help it.

Item_Response: So there I was, staring at the steering wheel, turning this way and that infront of me. I was amazed at the ingenuity, so I, unfortunately, missed the headlights lighting up like the robot had just opened it's eyes for the first time. Then the black leather steering wheel swerved, and the car jolted to the right, and sped up to 95 mph. I cowered in my seat, watching the cacti flash by, this was not the way to home, not even close. I caught a glimpse of the full moon, and I remember thinking to myself,  Is this the last time I see that?         I must have fallen asleep sometime because I was gently lifted to consciousness when the Google car slowed to a stop. I struggled to get out of my seat, and when I finally did, I gasped, and a stray question wandered into my head, How many Google cars did those scientists make?, because infront of me, lay a crater filled with Google cars, about ten thousand of them, and all of them turned and seemed to stare directly at my car.          Through the windshields of some of the cars, I saw blank faces staring back at me. On eman was smashing the windows with his fists, and then I remembered, there waws a tool in the glove box on the passengers side. I reach over, and grip the handle to the glovebox, and pull. The catch releases and the tool falls to the ground. Then the car starts moving. I franticly unbuckle my seat belt, and crawl to the passenger side, and grope for the tool. I feel the leather handle in my palm, and turn so I can reach the window. I, Hugh T. Jacobs, just tapped the window first, and then smashed against the glass, and then I felt like an overprotective imbecile, I had paid for the upgrade in the Google car, which included bulletproof glass.            So I was in a robotic car, with no means of getting out. I guess the people were right about a robot apacolypse.

Item_Response: Would you know what to do if a robot has came to life?  If you don't, then you'll love this story.  For this story is about a simple young 12yr old girl named Elizabeth, A.K.A Lizz or Lizzy, who comes across a abandoned wherehouse and finds a rusty old robot, then sudenlly begins her adventure.           I sheild my eyes with my hand as the sun peered into me.  I heavily picked my head up and looked slowly where I was.  I was in my room.  I remembered what was going on, It was a sunday morning during the weekend.  I qiuckly put my clothes on, tip-toed through the hallway and left.  I knew my mom and dad were aware where I was, and that was at the park near the shady tree.           As I walked to it I heard my friend called after me 'Hey Lizz!',Lisa called out, when she was calling out I saw my other friends behind her Brian, Cloe, Steve, Lissa, and of course me.  We hanged out all day talking and playing.  However, it was time to go, and as we walked to our homes Brian said 'Are you going to the carnival next week?', I shruged, 'I thought it was next month.'  'No', Steve said,'it's next week I heard about it'. I said my goodbyes and walked the rest of the time.           Sudenlly my peacful walk came to an end when a old wherehouse caught my eye.  my curiosity begged me to look in, so I did.  When I went in it was all old and dusty with spiderwebs, since I wasn't focusing on the wherehouse my whole body slamed to the gound!  'Ow!' I yellped, I quickly turned my head around and to notice a large old rusty body of metal.  'What is this, looks like some kind of robot?'  I examined it closely and it said 'Pyro', 'Pyro, your name is Pyro?'  I pushed the power button, surprised and shocked, I jerked away because everything turned on.  'Hello', it said in a normal yet electronic voice, 'My name is Pyro what is yours?'           I looked both ways so no one was looking, 'Um...my name is Elizabeth, but you can call me Lizz', 'Ok' it said.  I looked at my wrist 'Oh my gosh it's almost dinnertime!', I exclaimed, 'Sorry but...uh...I need to go, stay here Ok?'  'Yes', he said.  I said my 'seeya laters' and left, as I got home my mom exclaimed 'Where were you!?'  'I was at the...', I tried thinking of a way to explain myself, 'the park' 'The park?  So late at this hour?', 'Yep', I said and quickly ran up to my room.  Next morning, when we got out of class, I couldn't stop thinking about Pyro all day when sudenlly...'So you commi'n with us Lizz?'  I smiled big and shyly and said 'Sorry but I have something important to do', then I walked away to Pyro.

Item_Response: Students Directions       This story is about robots,there are a lot of robots, they may not be the same but there are all helpful.They all do different things, and also different names.There is a robot called  Gemini-Scout robot,a Dante 2,Mr. Grower,And at last a Agribots robot.                                                                                                                                                                                       The Gemini-Scout  robot  is a remote-controlled robot that searches-and-rescues work in mines under the ground . The robot is less than two feet tall and has wheels. It can go up and down stairs and make tight turns,and it can even roll through water. that robot is small,but it is strong. Gemini-scout robot can carries food,water,and other supplies.It can even drag hurt people to safety.                                                                                                                                                                                                                The Dante 2 is a robot with an interesting job - it climbs into  volcanoes to gather information for scientists.Like a spider,this robot has eight legs.This helps it climb the steep walls of the volcano.It is also built to survive very high heat.When a volcano is too dangerous for scientist to enter,Dante goes instead.         Mr. Gower is a robot that works on hospitals, helping doctors and nurses bring medicine to patients.Mr. Gower looks like a small cabinet on wheels.The body of the robot is a stack of locked drawers that store medicine. Nurses and doctors can unlock the drawers when the medicine is needed.         Agribot is a robot that picks up fruit. It might pick berries, oranges,grapes,or apples.Agribots are not yet widely used,but farmers are very interested in what these robots can do.Because picking  a strawberry is different than picking an apple,agribots come in all shapes and sizes. Some have giant arms that are towed behind trucks. Others are able to move around on their own.In Japan, there is a strawberry-picking robot that can sense the color of the berries.This helps the robot know when each berry is ripe.

Item_Response: Robots                 There is a robot called Gemini-Scout. The Gemini-scout does search-and-rescue work. This robot has a thermal camera to help it find miners. The thermal camera uses heat sensors to find living things. The Gemini-scout can help hurt people from mines and bring them to safety. When the robot looks in the mines it carries food, water, and other useful supplies.This robot is less that two feet tall and has wheels. It is a small robot but it is strong. It can go up and down stairs and it can make tight turns. It is water-proof so it can roll in water and not do anything to it. The Gemini-scout collects information. It tests the air for gases and then tells miners when the air is safe.                     Mr.Gower is another type of robot, but instead of help hut people from mines this robot helps doctors and nurses bring medicines to patients. Mr.Gower looks like a small cabinet on wheels. The body of the robot is a bunch of stacked locked drawers that store medicine.Nurses and doctors can unlock the drawers of the robot when the medicine is needed for the patients.

Item_Response: Roboy             'Ahh! The robot is coming alive,' Everyone shouted. The robot's name was, Roboy. He was a worldwide commercial selling toy. This one though, was not like the others. Someone, put a robot brain in Roboy so that he could control himself.         'Where am I?' Roboy asked.         'Your in robot prision,' a sheriff said, 'We made this prision last night just for you.'         'But I am a good robot though. I can help save people in mines. I can also test for bad air in the mines too before the miners go down. I can't be harmed from explosions or toxic air that humans can't surivive in.'         'Really, is that so?'         'Yes,' Roboy replied, 'If you let me out I will show you how helpful I can be.'         'Okay, we will let you out when someone needs to be saved in the mines,' The sherriff  said.                  'Get up Roboy. You are about to have your first mission,' The sheriff yelled to roboy, 'There was an explosion in the mines just south of town. There were 30 miners down there! Hurry up so we can save them!'          'Okay, I'm ready. Let's move,' Roboy said as he flew up into the sky with the sheriff on his back.                   Roby flew into the mines. He saw all the miners trapped by a huge rock. The miners didn't look to good. Most of them were not moving. For the ones that were moving though started shouting, 'Help! Save us!' Roboy knew he had to act fast or else they were all going to die. He thought how he could move the bolder. Then he had it, he had to break the bolder apart by using his super strength in his legs.                   Crack! The rock broke open and Roboy went and grabbed all the humans. He told the alive people to stay there and help put the unconscious ones on his back. They did that and Roboy flew up to the surface and gave all the people to the medical doctors at the scene. After that Roboy rushed down to the miners still in the mine and got them out too.                  'Roboy wake up,' The sheriff said, 'You saved everyone, all the miners will be okay. You did it. For your amazing act of bravery you are released from the prision. The town also bought you a house too. There is a catch though, you still have to test the air in the mines and save the people in them too.'          'It's a deal,' Roboy replied.              Roboy ended up to be a robot cop. He saved people in the mines for 30 more years. When he was 98 years old he passed away. The town had a funeral for Roboy. Nobody will ever forget Roboy.

Item_Response: 'Hello, my name is S-Bot' Meg herd a strange voice, almost sounding like a robot, repeating these words. She finally began to go and look where the strange voice was coming from. 'Hello, my name is S-Bot' Meg heard as she was nearing the basement door. Then she heard it again, but this time it was louder. Finally, she saw this little thing buzzing around in the air. This kind of robot is called a Gemini-Scout, and they are used for rescue work. They are made for flying into wrecked buildings or mines to find lost or hurt workers or people and have them use the Gemini-Scout's active radio to communicate with the rescue team to find where the people are located. These are very helpful robots.         The next day, Meg went into work with her Dad. She saw something very weird there. It was a cabnate rolling around on its own! Item_Response: The robot               Once upon a time in a nice village many, many people lived there for many years. It was a beautiful village, with with kids running around playing, birds singing in the trees the sky was always blue in the village. But one day for some reason this one day felt wrong, no one knew why, but they realized something was about to change.           A couple hours later people were screaming everywere, no one knew what was happening until someone looked into the sky. Meteors were falling from the sky no one knew what to do, they all just ran around screaming, people were trying to hide in there houses but they just burned down, every thing there was dying. They couldnt stop it. Soon everything and everyone was destroyed some people ran to safety but others were just not lucky.           Days past in the destroyed village many people came back to recover some of there stuff but nothing lived everything the people owned was lost. But one Boy named Phil thomsom found the most amazing thing in his life, there was a robot over by a destroyed home he went over there to see if it was ok but maybe not it was missing an arm, an eye, three wheeled feet and half its head, maybe not, Phil  felt sad he thought maybe there was one last toy he could play with but he didnt know. Only if it worked he might be a little happy he found a toy, but no.           Phil started to walk away but he heard something, Phil turned around and saw that the robot was moving! It was trying to stand up just like a human would, and it actualy did look like a human! It was completely metal it had for wheels but now it only has one. It had two legs now one arm and the robot was pretty small. It said something and Phil didnt understand it. A couple minutes later it ajusted some weird lever that changed his voice soon as he turned it to english the robot said 'please help me, please'. Phil didnt know what to say but then the robot spoke again it said this world is in danger you need to fix me. Then Phil said how, why, and how is the world in danger. Phil had so many questions but the robot looked like it    was about to die right in front of him so Phil had to do something so he picked him up and took him to his uncle lenny.           Lenny! Lenny! you need to fix this Phil said. Oh wow you found something that survived! Yes and you have to fix him hes still alive, I mean the robot is   alive! He talked to me he said the world was in danger and I need to know what that means he needs to be fixed or well never know whats coming. We need to fix him hes so injured he cant speak. OK OK Lenny said lets take him back to the shop and take a look at him.           Phil I took a look at him and im sorry I couldnt fix him, im sorry. What, hes dead!,   naaaah im just messing with yaah Hes all fixed I found some new parts so I put those on him, and I changed some wires and hes brand new. Great can I see him Phil said of course I ran in the room and checked him out he looked awsome he was painted, he got new screws and every thing he was awsome. He didnt even need batteries to run him. So anyways whats your name little robot. There was a pause 'I dont know' he said I dont know anything. But earlear you said the world was going to end, what was that about Phil said I dont know I was half broken dude The robot said you know you dont really know what your saying when your about to die That true I said.           At the end of this story, Phil and the robot became friends for ever, they always did every thing together, and they never did get mad at eachother or anything. Phil and the robot were the best pair of friends in the whole in tire world. They are the two best people you could ever hang out with, and they well be together until the end of there days.

Item_Response: My Robot             I was sleeping on a cool spring night.When I woke up to get some water and I heard my robot waking up. I said go back to sleep. He said no! I said fine as I walked out of my room.             The next morning my robot was in a better mood. My wonderful mom was making  us eggs and sausage.              After breakfast we went outside. My robot suggested we play freeze tag with our neighbors.When my neighbors came outside we went to the end of the couldasack. I was it first. I quickly tagged everybody except for my robot. He made the first move and I tagged him as I dove.               My robot was it next he was wheeling over when he shot out a freeze shock and hit Cam. (Cam is our neighbor). I yelled TIME OUT! Drew what are you doing? (Drew is my robot). He said playing freeze tag. I said not litterly. We made a fire to unfreeze Cam. When we finished they went home and didnt come back out.                During lunch me and Drew went to the park for a picknick. We asked people to play and they all said no we dont want to get frozen. I shook my head in disbeilife. How could Cam do that to us? He was my best friend until he told everyone to not play with us because my robot didnt know what we ment by freeze tag.                   The next morning I told my robot to stay in side.When i went to go get Cam thought he forgave me but when I rang the doorbell he said sure. He invited highschoolers to play to. When they showed up I was it becuase of what happened yesterday. As soon as we started i got hit by Cam I got up and got knocked down again this time from a highschooler. Then they all stared to beat me up. When the left my robot came outside and said lets get them! He said hop om he turned on his jetpack and flew and froze Cam and all the highschoolers.               From that day on me and my robot always play freeze tag.

Item_Response: The Robot                    Tap tap tap went my feet on the side walk I was just walking home from the mall when my neighbor Kennedy called my name. 'Jenna' she called.  Kennedy was a huge fan of robots which weren't really my thing to talk about people with! She came over to me and said ' I am going to thing robot show to pick out a robot and I was just wondering if you would come with me......' ' sure...' I said and I kinda felt bad because I kinda said it meanly! ' Its at ten o'clock tomorrow morning be at my house nine thirty sharp she said aggressively'. 'Okay' I mumbled and went into my house.....                       The next morning I was up bright and early getting ready for this Robot Show or in the cities case it was called: 'ROBOTS THE GREATEST INVENTIONS ( ten o'clock Saturday morning at convention center come clam your robot now.)'!! I crossed the street at nine twenty eight so she wouldn't get mad! I slightly knocked on the front door.... Kennedy swung it open with such power it was like a giant ripping through something !! 'HELLO! i am so thrilled that you could come we have to get moving right away I have to get the perfect robot!!' she yelled. I felt like I had already regretted saying yes! We hopped in her car and the she just started listing all different kinds of robots like: a robot that saved people in mines, one that was a medicine cabinet, another that was one that played hockey there was so many different kinds I couldn't keep them all strait. Then the car went THUD we were there.........                  The convention center wan a huge circular glass building rocketing in to the sky. It was probabley the tallest building in the city and I mean that. Kennedy who was next to me was screaming at the top of her lungs 'I'M SO EXCITED!!!!!' and she would not stop!! We quickly went in and sauntered around for a bit and then Kennedy screamed ' ITS THE PERFECT ONE KENNEDY THE PERFECT SIZE SHAPE AND COLOR I LOVE IT!!!!!!!!!!'  I murmured back to her  (remember I'm not a robot person but this was pretty amazing now I saw why she wanted me to come!) ' Its perfect you should buy it.') she said back ' I'M SO GLAD THAT THEY AREN'T ALL LIKE GEMINI-SCOUT LIKE I THOUGHT THEY WOULD BE!' She as fast as she could bolted to the register with the robots special number it had. The man at the register said sternly ' This is a very special robot don't be surprised if......' he trailed off and rung it up for Kennedy. and after what he said it got me thinking whats so special about this thing. It was just on average probabley 4 feet a greyish-amythist color, very stern looking mouth but dazzling lizard green eyes.... I didn't know what was so special about this thing.                  When we got back to Kennedy's house we raced inside and turned it on it came with this extra weird key that didn't have a key hole but I thought this might be whats so great about it so when Kennedy was admiring her I searced with the key tightly wrapped up in my left hand. Soon enough while looking at the back of it and I found this odd compartment and I slipped the key in that then out of nowhere the robot just started walking around and starting to talk to us it didn't even have batteries in it the it said in its robotic voice ' Greetings I am Tinex your new, fresh and alive robot and we have to go fast or I  will turn off!!!!'. I was so flipped out I felt like this was Frosty The Snowman robot style!! Then I zoned back in and heard Kennedy say ' WHERE DO WE HAVE TO GO TINEX I DON'T WANT YOU TO TURN OFF!' The he replied 'We must turn this key into the clerk who helped you buy me and if he dosnt have this in the next 2 hours he will turn into and robot virus that will shut all robots down we must go now!!!!!!!!!!                      The after about thirty seconds we were back at the convention center so fast because of Tinex's super speedy robot wheels. We raced in and found the clerk as soon as possible he was at the same spot and we had been searching for an hour already that we only  had one hour to complete our task!!! As soon as we found him we had to wait 50 minutes to get up to the front of the line and then we screamed to him in unison ' TAKE THIS KEY OR ALL ROBOTS WILL BE GONE FOREVER!!!!!!'. We only had about 2 minutes left to leave the building and then he grabbed the key put it in his hand and we were so ecstatic so we scramed the building and went to go to celebrate with our new found robot friend!!!                  When we all got back we celebrated and talked for hours and then he showed us all his features but finally he said I'm going to turn off for now but when you want me on just say Tinex on and I will be right by your side. And then I said 'I must go now but I will come visit'. The I said my goodbyes and went home!                   While I was walkies a crossed the street to go home I realized how much fun I had today! I learned so much and now I may actually like robots and be able to talk to Kennedy more. I was ecstatic about my new found friends and i am so glad that I said yes to Kennedy to go to the show I will never forget it!!!!!!!

Item_Response: The Living Robot            I was a scientist of my prime. My family had a farming hobby , so I wanted to do something special for them for all they've done for me. It took me a while to get an idea, but I finally found a good one. If I'm an engineer, I can just make them a farming robot, can't I, I thought. So I did. Well, at least I tried. I started building tons of robots in all different shapes and sizes, but none of them seemed to be right. Some had giant arms. Others had really tiny hands. I tried to make one with both, but it didn't turn out well at all. What would farming robots do anyway? Wouldn't they just grow and pick stuff? I paused and thought about it. Not only do they pick things, but my family might have them do other things too!            I went to visit my family to find out what they might do if they had a robot. They told me things like having the strawberries checked before harvesting, sensing if a plant is too dry or needs water, or even knowing if the fruit is ripe or not. I never even thought of any of that! Of course I've never actually worked on a farm before. Then I had an idea. I went back to my lab and started working for a long time. I realized not all things were picked the same way. When I was finally finished, I thought of going for a test run. It would be useless to them if it didn't work. I started to load my truck when I realized something. What would I even test it on? It's not like I have a farm! Yes, that was a good question. They're the only ones I know who actually own one. What was I to do, if I had nothing to test on? Surely I couldn't test it out on my family's farm. There were two things wrong with that. One, it would ruin the surprise. More importantly, it might ruin their crops. It was quite the problem. But that was when I had my other idea. I have a backyard myself! So why not just use that? Yes! I could buy the seeds and just plant them. And that's just what I did.            I took out the first activated robot. I placed it in front of the plant and stepped back to watch. Nothing happened. I waited a bit longer. Nothing. I kept on trying for about two weeks and did nothing else. I tried restarting it, taking it apart and starting over, anything I could possibly do. However, nothing happened. How extremely disappointing!! And I was getting ready to give it to my family as a marvelous gift that they deserved. Angrily, I threw the robot out on the street, stormed back inside and slammed the door shut.            Before I got far, I heard a knocking on the door. I went to go open it, but saw no one. I closed it and the knocking started again! I was getting irritated. I opened the door and felt a tugging at my pants. But when I looked down, there was not a person, but instead a little robot! It looked at me for a moment, and just rolled on inside my house. For a moment I thought I'd gone mad!! Just a figment of my imagination. But this little machine was far too real. I followed it outside where it went into my backyard. It stood still for a moment, and started watering the plant! Why, this robot had come alive! I starred at it pondering for a while, then it clicked. I could still give it to my family as a gift!! I picked up the little machine, rushed to the car, and went to my parents house.            When I arrived, they were sitting on the porch. My mother was knitting for my nephew, and my father was sleeping. Nothing changed, I thought. I leaped across the yard and shouted joyously,' Mother!! Father!! I have extravagant news!! Come quick!!' They looked at me like I was insane. But then they saw my little living invention. I told them about my time building him. They were absolutely delighted to hear my odd story. 'Why, isn't he just wonderful?' exclaimed my mother proudly. I visited them for a month just in case any problems happened, but they seemed just fine! It seemed the robot liked them, and they liked him. After a while, they gave him  name. 'What is it?' I asked curiously. 'Agribot.'
