Item_Response: Birthday Dissapiontment                                      By: Sadie Horne           Excited , nervous , and scared I sat down at our table ready to open my birthday presents . Grandma , aunt Allie , and all my cousins had gathered at my house for my 10 birthday celebration . Turning 10 was going to be great , all my friends had their parties months ago and now it was my time to shine . 'Alright now lets open presents !' My mother exclaimed in excitement .      First present was from grandma , it was the secret diary I had been begging for for months ! I was so excited because now my brothers couldn't get into it , it had a lock ! Next present was from aunt Allie , I slowly tore open the yellow package it was hidden in . It was a dress with pink and purple sparkles ! I jumped out of my seat and ran to give her a gigantic hug ! My cousin handed me a purple box from all my crazy cousins . I ripped it open and found that it was shoes to match my beautiful dress ! ' You guys all know me to well, !'I told them in excitement . the last present was from my mom and dad , it was wrapped in yellow wrapping paper with a perfect pink bow ! I anxiously tore open the paper , the tape was sticking to my hand ! Finally the moment I had patiently been waiting for . It was a robot that could talk , sing , dance , clean  , work , and all it needed was 10 tripple a batteries ! ' Oh mom , thank you so much , I love it !'       I ripped all the unnecessasary wrapping it was smuthered in off , and ran upstairs to grap the batteries ! When i got downstairs Lucy my robot was sitting on the counter just waiting to be played with . I handed the batteries to mom and she carefully put them in . Grandma , auntie , and all the cousins had to go but now i got to play with my new toy ! I set the robot on the ground and pressed on ,  nothing was happening . ' Go Lucy , run ! ' She didn't move one bit , ' listen to me Lucy , go ! ' Mom and dad tried to figure out what was wrong , but nothing was . ' It must be broken !' Dad told me in dissapointment . I ran upstairs and hopped on my bed very frustrated that my birthday present wasn't even working. Well I was just going to have to deal with it , atleast I had a dress , shoes , and a diary ! Dad set Lucy under my bed just in case she was going to work again .        At school i had nothing cool to show all my friends fro my birthday . 'What did you get for your birthday ?' My bestfriend Sally asked . 'Well my mom and dad bought me a robot that can do so many really cool things , but it doesn't work ! ' Everybody at school thought I wasn't cool now because I didn't have that stupid robot . I cried all the way home and ran up to my bed and weeped into my pillows . This was the worst birthday known to man ! Suddenly I heard a little sound coming from the ground . ' Mary had a little lamb , little lamb , little lamb , Mary had a little lamb and its fleece was white as snow ! ' I heard faintly from down there . I jumped of my bed to find that Lucy actually did work ! I yelled to my mom and dad ' Get up here Lucy actually works ! ' It was a miracle I finally got to play with Lucy ! I guess my 10th birthday wasn't so bad after all .

Item_Response: A hospital bed is not something you want to wake up in, especially in a post-apocalyptic world run by machines. This was all my fault. ever since Dante 2 and Gemini-Scout came out, I wanted to do something great. Not something that destroys half of the human race within a week. This is how it all began.      The year was 2017, I'm on my way to work at the lab, without a care in the world. I already had the blueprints for my creation. It was already half-built, I just needed to upgrade the wiring circuit. The robot's name was IPaCU, Inelegance Provider and Cooperation Unit. It was meant for human cooperation testing in the study of survival. This thing looked like a worm popping out of the ceiling with wires coming out of it and a main control core,it had back-up 'legs' in case of a malfunction where it needed to drop off the ceiling.       When I arrived, they had already started programing it with inelegance of survival.'So how far have we gotten?' I immediately ask.'Not far' a scientist replies. 'She hasn't woken up yet, we don't have enough power sources.' 'Any back-up sources?' I reply, 'No, none left.' 'Three weeks, we have been in this same spot for three weeks!' I'm starting to yell. 'Do you have any idea how frustrating this is!? I have been working on this for four years, four years! And Where are we? Nowhere!' I yell in frustration.        'If we do not have this thing powered up in one week, I'm shutting down the project' I say calmer, but still furious. I take time to cool off, and then rest. And at that moment, one little spark goes through the main wire of IPaCU, turning it on. Of course, I sleep through it. The only thing I wake up to is the sound of the emergency siren and the screams of scientists. This thing, the thing that was supposed to help humans, is killing them with toxic gas. Luckily, I grab a gas mask just in time to only be knocked out by it, not killed.        With me knocked out, the apocalypse begins. No one, nowhere, was safe from IPaCU. I was carried to the hospital by a surviving scientist, to this day I still don't know how he survived. But that explains the corpse on my floor. I'm sitting up now, I grab a weapon and exit the hospital. I've got to do what I've got to do, I started it, now I finish it.

Item_Response: My Robot and Me   One Friday I was sitting on a rocking chair in my backyard with nothing to do when all of the sudden came a BOOM in the house. I went inside to check what was happening. My dad had bought home a giant box home. He said it was a surprise. I opened the big box, and there was a giant robot. The robot was awesome, with a lot of things to do. It can also help me with my homework!       On the second day with my robot, on a Saturday, I never knew that the robot would become alive. In the morning, at 7:00 A.M., the robot stood next to me and called me to wake up. The robot's voice wasn't a regular robot's voice, but it was a human girl voice. Was I even dreaming? No, I wasn't. The robot had become alive! I decided to name the robot Chloe. After waking me up, Chloe went to the kitchen to help with breakfast. When I told my mom that the Chloe was alive, she screamed! Then she calmed down and let Chloe make breakfast.       That afternoon, it was a blast! I played tennis, wall ball, volleyball, and board games with Chloe. I decided to swim in the pool with her in my backyard to cool down. We swam, and dived all the way until dinner. Ever since my dad bought Chloe, my life was not filled with boredom anymore.

Now it is close to coming true , since today, robots can do all kinds of things of work. they assemble electronic gadgets, guide trains on tracks, and sort trash. today's robots can play as well as work-robots sings, dance, and even play music.                                                                  A Japanese robot can play the piano with its two mechanical hands. Another fobot,HRP-4c, can even dance and sing. Many playful robots are made to copy animals, too. Some robots play the way animals play while other robots play with animals.For example,moviemakers have designed huge robotic aoes and dinosaurs to be in movies.But these kinds of robots aren't made only for movies.                                       Robot animals can live with you. You can buy a life like pet, such as a dog, a seal, or even a dinosaur.                      These robot pets have a lot in common with real pets. They want your attention and you can teach them tricks.                There is even anew version of a robot pet that has fur so you can pet your robot just like you pet your dog or          cat.There is one difference, though---you don't need them outside or feed them!                                                                                        Other robots help people play with live animals. One company,I-Pet                                         Companion, has made a robot that lets people play with kittens, but from a distance. when you log on the internet,   you can control the robot from far away. the robot is put in a room full of kittens. it drags a piece of string for the kittens to chase. When it's your turn, you can control the robot to pull the string this way or that way.                                                           The kittens jump after the string as you push the controls. Some robots even play all by themself .        Collage students in oregon have created robots that can play hockey or shuffleboard on their own. all year, the students work hard to design the robots. The robots play the game without any instruction from the students . the robots grab the puck, turn, twist and compete to score. In the final test, the robots must push the puck to the goal      without being told what to do. There may never be a robot like Robbie since''I,Robot'' was a made -up story.                                                             Still, today's robots can offer hours of fun....

Item_Response: The Robot That Came Alive               In a robot club that I joined, my assignment was to build a robot to share out with the club. It took me a whole month to this assignment so I needed friends to help me, Jarrett, Rodger, and I. During this whole month we were all excited about how this robot was going to look like. We are going to build this robot in my garage. If you even mess one thing up the robot wont work. What we want the robot to do is, help us hold tools, deliver, and speak. It will also move by its self. This robot will have 4 legs. We shall be naming it Rojo. We were almost done with this project, now the only tricky part is, bring it to life.                      We tried plugging it in and it wasn't working. It took a long time to figure out what the problem was, we were just missing some parts. We plugged it in and it was lighting up! Rojo the red robot was finally alive! We were all proud of ourselves, because we got an A! That was story of making my robot come alive                                                                          By: Anthony George

Item_Response: Emily Bot                                           One day my friend Sarah and I needed to do a class project. Sarah and I decided to make a robot so we could be creative. We wanted to make a robot that can do special skills like dance,sing and talk. I invited Sarah over so we could start to make ideas.I heard the doorbell ring and I ran to the door. I opened the door and I didnt see Sarah I saw my little cousin Emily. Emily had brought all her toys and water paints. I said 'What are you doing here?' Emily replied 'I came to play here.' I said 'Well go play somewhere else Sarah is coming over because we need to do a project.' Emily walked right in the house and ran into the game room.             The doorbell had rang again and this time I knew it was Sarah. I ran to the door to answer it I opened the door and saw Sarah with a notebook and wires and much much more. I said 'Hey come on in.' Sarah said 'Okay why is there a bunch of trash on the floor?' I said annoyed 'Because my cousin is  here.' Sarah said 'Oh well she better not disturb us.' I nodded my head and walked to the kitchen leading Sarah. Sarah got all her things out and we started to bulid. Sarah and I walked upstairs to go grab some material for the robot. While we were gone Emily went into the kitchen and made the robot just like her. Sarah and I walked downstairs and saw the robot. Sarah got angry because all that effort we put into it and I did too. The robot was all covered in glitter and fleathers it looked horrible.              Sarah grabbed the robot and then it started to talk and move the robot said 'Put me down Sarah!' Sarah and I both looked at each other then screamed. We ran upstairs and Emily followed us. I said 'Why did you do that Emily?' Emily said 'Do what?' Sarah joined in and said 'You know what you did you made the robot talk and walk!' Emily said 'No I didnt I only put glitter on it and fleathers.' Sarah and I said 'Well then who did it!' Then we heard a noise like crashing and breaking things. We also saw something coming up the stairs. It was the robot the robot said 'I am coming.' We all got scared and painked because the robot was alive!

Item_Response: Rob                  The bell had just rung for us to get out of school, it was Friday! I was happy that now I had two whole days of no school, nothing but to relax. After I went to my locker and but all my books away I started to walk home. I was five minutes into walking home and all of a sudden I herd a sound... it was a sound that sounded like something hitting metal. I kept walking and three seconds later I heard it again. So I started to go back and look for what was making the noise.   Soon enough I looked in a big trashcan wondering if it was coming from there. I slowly lifted the lid up... but all I saw was an old toy looking robot and some trash that was thrown away. So I figured what ever was making the noise had gone away. I started to walk away and then I herd it again. It sounded like it was coming from the trashcan, but all I had saw was the old robot and some trash. I started to wonder if it could of been the robot... but it wasn't possible anyways it looked like the robot didn't work. Some how though I was curious and decided to go and look in the trashcan again. As I lift up the lid and picked up the robot.   He looked like he was a run down old toy that was thrown away. I looked at him and found an on and off button. I switched the button on to see if it worked and soon enough I saw the eyes light up, but that was it. So I decided to take it home and look at it some more.   It was nearly six o'clock when I got home and Mom had already made dinner and said it was time to eat. I sat down at the table and started to eat dinner. Mom asked me how my day was and I told her it was good but I did tell her that I found something interesting while I was walking home from school. She asked me what it was but I said it was just an old toy someone threw away. After I finished dinner and put my dishes in the sink I went up to my room and looked at the robot some more. I turned the on button on again and then his eyes lit up. I set him down wondering if that was all he did but then I heard something say hello. I turned over and looked at the robot and saw his arm make a slight movement.    Then he moved his head and said, ' Hello... my name is Rob, whats yours?' I couldn't believe he was talking to me. I responded saying, ' Hi, my name is Joey.' It was kind of strange at first, just the thought that I was having a conversation with a robot but then after we got into the conversation  a bit more it didn't feel so strange.   Mom knocked on the door asking who I was talking to and I said, 'Oh, I was just talking to a friend on the phone.' hoping she would believe me. She said, ' Ok, just don't be on the phone past nine.' I said,' sure... ' ' Wow! that was close Rob... she almost found out about you.' ' Ya, your right.' It was almost time to go to bed so I started brushing my teeth and geting my bed ready. Rob asked where he was going to sleep and I pulled out an old shoe box and put a blanket at the bottom with a pillow and then gave him another blanket to cover himself.   The next morning I woke up and looked at Rob's bed. He wasn't there! I thought ,' Ok where would I go if I were a robot.' I looked all over in my room and still couldn't find him. Then I ran down the stairs and asked Mom if she had been in my room and she said,' Ya, there was this old robot thing sitting on your bed.' I asked her ,'Well where did you put it.' Oh I put it in the trash.Why do you want it?I thought since it was sitting in an old shoe box I thought you wanted it to be thrown away.' I said,' No I found him yesterday in the trash and brought him home!'   So I ran outside and looked in the trash and got him out. He was still Ok and I decided that I could use a friend. So I took him inside and from that day he's still my friend. I'm now eighteen and those six years he's stayed with me by my side ever since. That's what a true friend is.

Item_Response: One stormy night Sammy was working in his room on his robot friend. Sammy did not have many friends so that is why he decided to make one. He has been working on his friend for four months now but there was no use he could not make it work. So he put on his rain coat and walked to the trash crying. He tossed him in the garbage and walked in the house to go to bed. When he was sleeping a tear stoke down his face and right when it hit his pillow lightning struck hitting his robot outside.                  The next morning when Sammy woke up everything he saw was blurry. He opened his eyes a crack and saw a face. He closed his eyes then opened them again, blinking multiple times. The figure was gone. Sammy got out of bed to brush his teeth. When he was smiling in the mirror making funny faces with toothpaste in his mouth. He heard a laughter but where from. He heard it again coming from his closet, very scared he opened his door there he saw his robot it was alive and shinier then ever. Hi he said remember me i am your robot that you designed. 'Why did u put me in the trash it was dreadful in there the smell was just awful.' said the robot. 'Sorry' Sammy said still confused.                 Sammy decided to give his new friend a name 'how about Franky?' 'Sounds great i cant wait to spend so much time with you'said Franky. 'Well we need to go eat breakfast and introduce you to the family.' Exclaimed Sammy. they both walked down. The whole family was up sitting at the table waiting for Sammy so they can start eating. When the family saw Franky there mouths dropped open wondering who it was. This is Franky everyone. he is my robot friend that I made. Franky this is my dad, mom, my sister Angela, and my dog Clover. Franky had great manors, he said hi and nice to meet you. Franky was not only did he have great manors but he was also kind.                  Franky suggested that they go outside and play soccer. Sammy agreed. They both walked outside using Angela's new pair of shiny black shoes as a goal. Sammy started with the ball kicking it as hard as he could. Franky stopped it, but now it was his turn to kick on Sammy he set it up striking it with his metal foot hitting it so hard that Sammy jumped out of the way so he wouldn't get hit. 'Wow that was a great kick Franky.' Exclaimed Sammy. Franky ran after the ball he was super fast he could run a marathon in less that two minutes. Sammy asked Franky if he wanted to join the soccer team but Franky said no he would rather play soccer with him.                  Sammy knew that there friendship would last for miles, they even came up with a cool handshake. Well even though it is time for them to go to bed, Sammy had never felt the feeling of a friend to hangout with and he was glad he found someone as special as Franky.

Item_Response: The Alien Robot            It all started one cold winter night in a lab on an island 4 miles off the coast of Maine.A group of 10 scientists were working on a mysterious robot that was 16 feet tall and 8 feet wide that appeared out of nowhere and looked of alien origins.It looked like a giant,blue Iron Man suit from the movie Iron Man.        They worked and worked on it for days with no luck at all.They tried replacing old parts, hitting it,and attacking it.Nothing seemed to work though.The problem was much more simple than that.The robot simly didn,t have any more power.Giving up,the scientists threw the robot into a junkyard with other items.Thats when it started.The day it started was a groomy day with a strong rainstorm.Suprisingly, The robot ran on water.This rainstorm filled the robot's power core up enough to start it up.First it was loading in data about its surroundings.This lead to it finding out it was on a planet called Earth,which was 206565492 lightyears away from its home world,Galvin Omega.It could fly there, but it didn't have its power core charged enough.It then scanned the area to find the closest area to get information about this 'Earth.'It then traveled the the closest building with a computer and absorbed its data.Scanning though the data it found out how to get enough power for the space flight home to Galvin Omega,a n area the primitave species of this world calles a 'dam.'The closest dam was 20 miles.This took the robot about 5 minutes to get there.This is where the problem really starts.Somehow, the army gets there thinking thai it is a threat.They fire on sight but were blasted away by the robot's plasma cannon.This then made the robot an Alfa Red Threat.This caused the army to send all their troops there.Quickly The robot had to escape before it lost too much power.        The robot seemed to be faster than most and dived into the deeper side of the dam.The army unable to do anything at that moment,dicided to wait till it came out where they would be waiting.Although the army was strong it wasn't able to stop the robot when it shot out of the water and flew through space to its home.

Item_Response: There was a young, yet so fragile girl by the age of 13 named Rosemary. Her parents spent their day working, leaving poor Rosemary all on her own in the house. One day she asked, 'Mummy, why must you go to work everyday and leave me alone in this lonely house?'   Her mother replied, 'Well, Rosemary, because we do it for your food, the clothes on your back, and this lonely house.'      Rosemary kept quiet after that response. Day after day she became more lonely. Her parents seemed like they didn't love her anymore. This was true. Her parents did not work ALL the time.  After they got of of work, they went to go partying or do something that does not involve Rosemary. Rosemary was a good student. She had no friends, no way of being social. Then, she discovered the internet. The 13 year old found a website where there were people just like her. They didn't sleep -just like her-. They all had problems -just like her- it was real nice. She used it a lot, but somehow she needed something else. A friend is what she needed.      Rosemary has never had a friend in her whole entire life. She does remember having one in 5th grade, but that friend let her go after a while.    One night while her parents were 'working', Rosemary was on that special website and found a page. It was not some regular page, it was a robot selling page.   'They're having a give-away!' Rosemary cried.    The prize was a robot. 'The I, Robot' she read.       After a few weeks later, she won the prize. When she opened it, her eyes were bursting tears of joy. Since Rosemary never had a childhood of her own, she decided to make one out of this robot.   'I'm going to call you Flossy.' giggled Rosemary.   'As you wish.' said Flossy.           Rosemary loved Floss very much. Somehow, Flossy adapted to Rosemary's personality. About 2 years later, Rosemary somehow had drifted apart from Flossy. She often thinks about him, she remembers how lucky she was winning that give-away. It practically saved her life. While she was looking out and about in her old house, she found Flossy. He was all dusty but still looking like Rosemary's late childhood. Rosemary quickly and quietly turned Flossy on.   'Good morning, Rosemary, what wonderful weather.' it said.     'Yes, what wonderful weather we are having.' she let a tear out while she was speaking.   'Do you know how long it has been since I've used you?'   '2 years a 3 days, ma'am.' Flossy said.   'You know, I've been always meaning to thank you.' Rosemary said.   'You're welcome, child.' Flossy replied.         Then, Rosemary's parents walked in and said,   'GET OUT, WE BE HAVING A PARTY OVER HERE!'      The night of that day, her parents were inside the house, being burned alive.                             The End (:

Item_Response: When Jack got home from school it was just any ordinary day, but little did he know his life would change forever. His cousin was coming over next week so he planned to build a fort in the woods. When he told his mother where he was going she just said' Be back by 7 o'clock.' While walking through the woods he started to day dream about how he would be a famous basketball star and married to a super model. He didn't know it but he been walking the wrong way for about 15 minutes.          That's when he came into the clearing. Jack was very confused, he'd never been to this part of the woods. Then something caught the corner of his eye. It was I a giant piece of metal sticking out of the ground, and it looked like a giant hand! As he got closer to it, it started to look more and more like a hand. When he got right up to the object he stuck his hand out to touch it. That's when it happened.          There was the sound of gears grinding. The whole ground rose up, and underneath was a giant metal man. A robot! When it stood to it's full height it was easily 12 feet tall. That's when it looked at Jack he took of has fast as he could, but the robot was faster. The robot's hand shot out and grabbed him. Jack thought for sure the robot was going to squish or something. But the robot just stared at him. 'What do want?' Jack cried out. The robot start to walk away with Jack.          When Jack tried to yank himself free the Robot said'Stop child. I am from a different galaxy.' Jack was speechless. He thought he was dreaming, but nope there was a real living robot in front of him. 'Why are you here?' asked Jack. 'To find my lost brother Dracou.' 'Well what's your name then?' 'Gizmo.' 'Oh, I thought would be some Russian name like Arnold or something.' They didn't talk until they came to a cave. 'This is where we sleep tonight.' When Gizmo set him down Jack saw a symbol that looked like a skull. When he asked Gizmo about it he said it was his family's symbol.         For 8 days they traveled across the country to find Dracou. Jack missed his mom,but knew this was a once in a lifetime experience. On the 9th day they came to a military base. Gizmo said it was where they kept his brother. They devised a plan and waited for night fall.           When the sun went down their plan was put to action. Gizmo fired a couple shots on the other side of the base. All the alarms went off and guards rushed over there. That's when they snuck around to the back entrance. When Jack saw the place all he could say was' Oh my gosh.' The place was way bigger than it looked and had a least 10 floors going down. Everything was white and all of the scientist were in these big radiation suits. They were all surrounding this big pile of metal. But when Jack looked closer he realized it was Dracou.          Now it was phase 2 of their plan. Jack seen the nearest fire alarm and pulled it. All of the scientist started sprinting to the nearest fire exit. When they were all gone Gizmo grabbed Jack and jumped off the main floor all the way to the bottom one. When they got to Dracou, Gizmo hit a button on his back, and he instantly woke up. Gizmo told him to situation and said they were going to have to blast their way out.              Gizmo and Dracou both fired they're guns at the roof and it came down. Gizmo grabbed Jack and flew out of the roof with him.When they got to Jack's house Gizmo set him down and said his good byes. Gizmo said' I never thought there were any good humans until I met you Jack.' 'Thank you for saving my life.' said Dracou.That's when they flew   off.

Item_Response: The rise of the Robots (PART ONE)   by Logan Magin          'Year: 2079 April 24th, twenty six years after the rebellion of robots,' repeated the loud speaker, previously the human race had created such intelligent artificial life that they began to think on their own. Robots no longer were devoted to risking themselves as experiments or battle technology. One, the first rebel and the leader of the robots had begun everything. He took over the factories, hacked us, out-smarted all of us, and got the other steel creatures to follow him. Soon enough we were slaves we were servants to them! We needed a new plan. One to free us all.          'What shall we do?!' this was our human resistance leader, we were divising a plan to save our race in a secret underground bunker. I had grown up dowwn here, almost never having a single ray of sun touch the surface of my skin. My name was mark, I think, my parents had been taken when I was just a little boy to work as servants for the 'Big guy' or the one robot that flipped the simple life of the past.   'Hey...' suggested on of the few elderly people that escaped 'Have you ever seen the movie terminator...?' We never had, of course, all of the movie theaters or entertainment departments had been destroyed because the robots didnt feel amused by them.'Robots took over in the movie, then went back in time to try and take out the human leader...' he whispered 'What if we flip that...' Everone went silent. The closest time machine available was in custody by the artificial intelligence.       'How will we get to it?' Suggested the rebel leader (he had never ever given us his name)       'Only a couple of turret drones guard that today,' I stated, 'and we still have several RPGs in our saved inventory.'       'That's right,' James (my best friend) shouted 'We could take those out, get the time macine, go back in time, and destroy the prototype of artificial intelligence used to create the 'Big guy.'       'Now then, Who agrees with the two... children?' Everyone began to mumble, shake thier heads up and down, and stick their thumbs up. Our leader seemed surprised by our quickly made plan, but had to go with the over all vote. We scheduled to leave the very next day to take back wha was ours. 'Wait,' He said, 'Who will be the one to go back in time to destroy that prototype?' Instanly everyone went quiet, and I saw how physically weak we all were. I was one of the only healthy people, 'I will,' I said.

Item_Response: Student Directions      Robots Narrative Performance Task       Task:           You have joined a creative writing club that meets at the school library once a week. The current assignment is to write a science fiction story for the group about any subject that interests you. For your story, you must include information from research that you have done. To prepare for your story, you have decided to research the topic of robots. Below are four sources you have uncovered in your research (two essays, an article, and an image).               After you have reviewed these sources, you will answer some questions about them. Briefly scan the sources and the three questions that follow. Then, go back and review the sources carefully to gain the information you will need to answer the questions and write a story.               In Part 2, you will write a story on a topic related to the sources.       Directions for beginning:           You will now examine several sources. You can re-examine any of the sources as often as you like.       Research Questions:           After examining the research sources, use the remaining time in Part 1 to answer three questions about them. Your answers to these questions will be scored. Also, your answers will help you think about the research sources you have read and viewed, which should help you write your story.               You may click on the appropriate buttons to refer to the sources when you think it would be helpful. You may also refer to your notes. Answer the questions in the spaces provided below them.       Part 1       Sources for Performance Task:       Source #1   This article about the kinds of jobs performed by robots is based on information in the following sources:   http://www.nbcnews.com/technology/futureoftech/rescue-robot-just-made-mine-disasters-121251   http://www.nytimes.com/1994/08/03/us/robot-completes-volcano-exploration.html   http://www.ri.cmu.edu/research_project_detail.html?project_id=163enu_id=261   http://www.umm.edu/news/releases/robot.htm;http://www.economist.com/node/15048711.       Meet the Robots   by Erin Bregman               If you think of robots as a thing of the future, think again. Robots do many jobs today. They work in mines and on farms. They help doctors and save lives. They even explore volcanoes. Here are some robots that are hard at work.       Gemini-Scout               Gemini-Scout is a remote-controlled robot that does search-and-rescue work in mines under the ground. The robot is less than two feet tall and has wheels. It can go up and down stairs and make tight turns, and it can even roll through water. The robot is small, but it is strong. Gemini-Scout carries food, water, and other supplies. It can even drag hurt people to safety.               Wherever it goes, Gemini-Scout collects information. For example, it tests the air for gases and then tells miners when the air is safe. The robot also has a thermal camera to help it find miners. A thermal camera uses heat sensors to find living things.               When the robot finds the trapped miners, the miners can use its two-way radio to talk with the rescue team.               This robot was built to be easy to use. Its remote control is the same one that is used for some video games. If you"ve ever played a video game, you may know how to use Gemini-Scout.       Dante 2               Dante 2 is a robot with an interesting job—it climbs into volcanoes to gather information for scientists. Like a spider, this robot has eight legs. This helps it climb the steep walls of the volcano. It is also built to survive very high heat. When a volcano is too dangerous for scientists to enter, Dante goes instead.               Dante 2 looks for vents, or holes, in the crater. Then the robot collects information about the gases that come out of the vents. In the past, scientists could not learn as much about volcanoes, but Dante 2 is changing that. Now scientists can study a volcano up close while they remain safe in their laboratories.       Mr. Gower               Mr. Gower is a robot that works in hospitals, helping doctors and nurses bring medicine to patients. Mr. Gower looks like a small cabinet on wheels. The body of the robot is a stack of locked drawers that store medicine. Nurses and doctors can unlock the drawers when the medicine is needed.               Mr. Gower can go anywhere in the hospital. It can ride elevators, steer through hallways, and move around things that get in the way. The robot is so strong that it can pull 500 pounds. Mr. Gower runs on batteries. After charging for two hours, the robot can deliver medicine for twelve hours without stopping.               Not only does it work long days, but Mr. Gower can talk. It has been programmed to say hundreds of phrases. For example, it can say, “Calling elevator” or “Your delivery is here.” Mr. Gower does work that doctors, pharmacists, and nurses used to do. This allows them to focus on other important tasks.       Agribots               An agribot is a robot that picks fruit. It might pick berries, oranges, grapes, or apples. Agribots are not yet widely used, but farmers are very interested in what these robots can do. Because picking a strawberry is different than picking an apple, agribots come in all shapes and sizes. Some have giant arms that are towed behind trucks. Others are able to move around on their own. In Japan, there is a strawberry-picking robot that can sense the color of the berries. This helps the robot know when each berry is ripe.               At the Massachusetts Institute of Technology (MIT), scientists are working to grow cherry tomatoes with no human help at all! They have created a greenhouse full of plants that are cared for by small agribots. The agribots are like robot farmers. Every plant has sensors that tell the robots what the plant needs. If a plant is too dry, a robot will water it. When a robot senses that a tomato is ripe, it uses a mechanical arm to pick the tomato. Agribots may seem unusual now, but one day they may be common on farms. Source #3   This article about  interacting with robots is based on information in the following sources: http://www.theatlantic.com/infocus/2011/04/robots-at-work-and-play/100052/#img06; http://www.upenn.edu/pennnews/current/2012-01-26/latest-news/robotic-hockey-teams-faceoff-penn-engineering   http://www.gazettetimes.com/news/local/article_be8aab10-90dd-11e0-9473-001cc4c002e0.html   http://www.ipetcompanion.com/;http://news.cnet.com/8301-17938_105-20020139-1.html   http://techcrunch.com/tag/hrp-4c/;http://io9.com/5090047/10-robotic-pets-that-deserve-to-live-in-the-white-house   http://www.ubergizmo.com/2012/03/smart-fur-robo-bunny/.       Robots that Play Well With Others   by Kascha Semonovitch               About fifty years ago, the author Isaac Asimov wrote a story called “I, Robot.” The story is set in the future, when robots take care of children. The main character loves her robot babysitter, Robbie. Unlike the child"s parents, Robbie always has time to play. Robbie and the child have adventures together. Robbie is an endless source of fun!               When the story was written, it was a fantasy. Now it is close to coming true, since today, robots can do all kinds of work. They assemble electronic gadgets, guide trains on tracks, and sort trash. Today"s robots can play as well as work—robots sing, dance, and even play music. A Japanese robot can play the piano with its two mechanical hands. Another robot, HRP-4c, can even dance and sing.               Many playful robots are made to copy animals, too. Some robots play the way animals play while other robots play with animals. For example, moviemakers have designed huge robotic apes and dinosaurs to be in movies. But these kinds of robots aren"t made only for movies. Robot animals can live with you. You can buy a lifelike pet, such as a dog, a seal, or even a dinosaur. These robot pets have a lot in common with real pets. They want your attention and you can teach them tricks. There is even a new version of a robot pet that has fur so you can pet your robot just like you pet your dog or cat. There is one difference, though—you don"t need to take them outside or feed them!               Other robots help people play with live animals. One company, I-Pet Companion, has made a robot that lets people play with kittens, but from a distance. When you log on to the Internet, you can control the robot from far away. The robot is put in a room full of kittens. It drags a piece of string for the kittens to chase. When it"s your turn, you can control the robot to pull the string this way or that way. The kittens jump after the string as you push the controls.               Some robots even play all by themselves. College students in Oregon have created robots that can play hockey or shuffleboard on their own. All year, the students work hard to design the robots. The robots play the game without any instructions from the students. The robots grab the puck, turn, twist and compete to score. In the final test, the robots must push the puck to the goal without being told what to do.               There may never be a robot like Robbie since “I, Robot” was a made-up story. Still, today"s robots can offer hours of fun.       Source #4   Here is an article on self-driving cars, from NPR.com, February 17, 2012.   http://www.npr.org/blogs/alltechconsidered/2012/02/17/147006012/when-the-car-is-the-driver       When the Car Is the Driver   by Steve Henn               This week the state of Nevada finalized new rules that will make it possible for robotic self-driving cars to receive their own special driving permits. It's not quite driver's licenses for robots—but it's close.               The other day I went for a spin in a robotic car. This car has an $80,000 cone-shaped laser mounted on its roof. There are radars on the front, back and sides. Detailed maps help it navigate.               Do people notice it's a self-driving car and gawk?               'We get a lot of thumbs up,' says Anthony Levandowski, one of the leaders of Google's self-driving car project. 'People drive by and then they wave. I wish they would keep their eyes on the road.'               Levandowski is in the passenger seat with a laptop showing him what the car can see. Chris Urmson is behind the wheel. But his hands are in his lap and the steering wheel is gently turning back and forth, tracing the contours of California's busy Highway 85.               'And it can adjust the speed. If there is a particularly tight corner, it will slow down for that,' Urmson says. 'It adjusts speed to stay out of blind spots of other vehicles. It tries to match speed with traffic.'               Urmson has been working on this technology for close to a decade. His first car managed to travel just 11 miles on a dusty road. Google's vehicle is a giant leap forward.               'When we got this on the freeway and it was doing 70 miles an hour and just smoothly driving along the road, you could taste it—the technology,' Urmson says. 'You could really feel the impact and how it's going to change people's lives. It was just amazing.'               While he was talking, a motorcycle cut us off. The car saw the move coming, and we hardly even noticed.               Google's fleet of robotic cars has driven more than 200,000 miles over highways and city streets in California and Nevada. Google did this testing in kind of a legal limbo. These cars aren't forbidden, but, 'There was no permission granted for any of that to happen by anybody,' says Steve Jurvetson, a venture capitalist and robotic car enthusiast.               'It's essential that there be a place to do tests,' he says. 'There's two ways to do it—the seek-forgiveness strategy and the seek-permission strategy. Frankly, the 200,000 hours I think that have been driven here in California—that's a seek-forgiveness strategy. Right?'               If anything went wrong, Google would have had a huge amount of explaining to do. So last year, the company hired a lobbyist in Nevada. 'The state of Nevada is close, it's a lot easier to pass laws there than it is in California,' Levandowski says.               He says Google convinced the state Legislature to pass a law making robotic cars explicitly legal. But the Legislature went further than just creating a place to test these cars—it ordered the Department of Motor Vehicles to create basically a driver's license for these robot cars.               'I thought it was great,' says Bruce Breslow, director of the Nevada DMV. 'My grandfather took me to the 1964 World's Fair in New York City many times. And they were promising me the car of the future as an 8-year-old, and I thought to myself, this finally could be it.'               Starting March 1, companies will be able to apply to test self-driving cars on Nevada roads.               'The test vehicles will be Nevada's first red license plate since the 1940s,' Breslow says. Think of it like a learner's permit—those bright red plates will let everyone know there's a student robot driver behind the wheel.               'And eventually when these vehicles are sold, it will be the first ever neon green license plate that the state of Nevada will ever issue—green meaning go, and the future's arrived,' Breslow says.               Google says it will probably be years before cars like this go on sale. But Jurvetson, the venture capitalist, says he's convinced this technology could save thousands of lives 'today, already, right now.'               Robots are never distracted. They don't text or drink or get tired. They see things no human can.               'That front radar catches bounces off the ground,' Jurvetson says. 'We were driving behind an 18-wheeler, and we saw the vehicles in front of the 18-wheeler—vehicles we could not see with our eye—because the signal bounced off the pavement . . . at a glancing angle underneath the 18-wheeler. And so no human will ever have the amount of information that these cars have when they are driving.'               While Nevada may be the first state to create a licensing system for self-driving cars, it won't be the last; Hawaii, Florida and Oklahoma are already following suit. And Jurvetson says one day we may be asking ourselves if humans should still be allowed to drive.

Item_Response: I was walking home from my baseball game with my friends.We were passing the old run down house were the Jensen's lived.My brother told me that the Jensen's didn't move they were disinigrated by their evil robot.But I think he was just trying to scare me.Some of my friends wanted to go in so I did to.At first it wasn't bad until we got to the back door.We saw the shed.The shed that the robot is in.It was a descent sized shed,but it's secrets were bigger.I wanted to go in if my friends went in first.Everyone chicken out,but I went in,ALONE.I tried to scare my friends by pretending the robot grabbed me and took me in.That got them good.It was really dusty and sheets were over everything.There were some spiders and mice that made me jump,but they were no match for what I saw next.It had a sheet on it that was really dirty.I pulled it of and there it was,the robot.It was tall and had big eyes.It was dusty and had silver coating.It was dead as a doorbell battery.I found the charger.But I'm for sure that my mom would not let me keep it.So I suck it into our separate garage.I cleaned it off and plugged it in.My friends left because they thought I wouldn't come out alive.It took awhile to charge,but it finally did.I  figured it out when I heard a crash in the garage.I looked in and saw two big eyes staring at me they really freaked me out,so I ran inside and sat in a corner and sat sat and sat for hours.Then I heard nothing,just silence.I went out to see what was going on.The robot died.Not like die die.There was no  battery in it.Hooray.So I put it back in the Jensen's shed and never dealt with it again.

Item_Response: There was a little girl named Katherine who lived in New York and had short brown hair and freckles.She invented a robot for her project and named it  Lucile and she was working on her report to present with her robot. Her parents were very proud of her.She rushed off to her school Sun land Elementary and when she was gone there was a large amount of noise in her room but her parents did not suspect anything so they went to work.Later when she got home she ran up to her room anxious to see if her robot had came alive.but it was the same.Katherine wondered why her room was a mess but she kept it to herself.           The next week while she was working on her report she heard a noise behind her and she turned around and nothing was there The noise came again but no-one was there.The third time she caught it.She was overjoyed to see that her robot  had walked and breathed.Over the past few weeks she worked to get to her goal of a full stimulated robot. She succeeded and was so happy.Later on in her life she invented many other robots.Some could play with her some could read to her some could climb trees or cook or even make the bed.She invented a nanny bot to help take care of her while she was sick so her parents could go to work.           Remember if you think of robots as a thing of the future, think again.Robots are around today but you just do not notice it.Some help save lives or help doctors or even go down in volcanoes.Also one that can mine.

Item_Response: THE ROBOT                                          My brother and I have decided to create a robot. This robot will just a toy for certain fun occasions. We will need hot glue, a sharpie to draw the face, and cardboard boxes. So far we've have the legs, the body that we haven't glued on yet, the head, and a hat. I have decided that I should name the robot, Mexor. Mexor's personality will be playful and wild but he will also have an angry personality but that won't be shown too often. Another good thin Mexor will have is he is limber to become a ninja.                             My brother went downstairs at 3:00 in the morning and got coffee right where Mexor was at. My brother also saw that Mexor's arm was flinching and found that Mexor had came to life.'He put on his hat and started dancing,' my brother said. Although Mexor was just made yesterday, he could only dance. Everyday he could do something different like one day he able to sing which came much, much, later. One day he acted like a dog and started barking at other dogs and chased cats up trees. But sometimes he would act sad and mad when my brother and I would leave for sports.                                                Without warning, Mexor went all ferious and started trashing and messing up the house in any way he could think of.When my family got back to the house , my parents were mad. Before I could say anything, I was told to go find Mexor so he doesn't do anything to the city. A matter of fact, I couldn't even find evidence of Mexor. I had figured out that Mexor needed a friend or someone who is also lonely. So we made another robot that was the name Lexor. So, by then, Mexor had already destroyed half of the city and people were calling the airforce so it wouldn't turn out too good for Mexor.                                I had brought Lexor with me to calm down Mexor and so Mexor has a friend so he doesn't get mad like that in the future. The airforce had already fired stuff at Mexor. I said, 'Mexor, Come here.'They had both became friends and no more destruction was caused to the city.They both lived happily in a cardboard house full of pictures of them both with their good memories they've made

Item_Response: It seemed that it going to be standard procedure, just another accident that needed search and rescue. The scientists, four in total, suspected nothing. Their names were Robert, Bob, Ben, and Joe. They were the scientists that created the Gemini Scout. It is a robot for search and rescue in mineshaft.         So when they got a call that's what they thought it was going to be. And that's what it was for a time. The Gemini Scout was being maneuvered down an eery dark tunnel of rock and splintered wood. The scientists were studying air samples to make sure the lost miners weren't poisoned. They were also looking through it's many cameras to see if they could find any miners.         After around thirty minutes the Gemini became harder to control and would occasionally stray off course. Although they felt with all the ground they'd covered and having not found any miners they couldn't pull back now. Then suddenly the main camera went out! Then then the thermal camera too! Now with not being able to see what the Gemini was doing they'd have to go retrieve it manually.         Then a message was sent from the Gemini saying 'Help me I cannot see,' the scientists thought they had accidentally found a miner who was using the Gemini's communications. They decided that now they had to go into the mineshaft because, not just the Gemini was in danger, but someone's life. So they decided to send Robert down with all the necessary gear and if it was to much he could always call them down on his walkie-talkie.         So Robert began his journey into what was now just a black hole waiting to envelope him. He started by simply following the trail that the Gemini had left behind.It was along and perilous decent into total darkness. It was many hours later when the others first heard of him. He said that he had found the Gemini, but no miner. He later explained that the Gemini sent the message by it's own will and that down here it had devoloped feelings.         When Robert and the Gemini surfaced from the blackness they were friends. Every mission afterward the Gemini acted on it's own and it's team of friends helped it rescue more miners.

Item_Response: The Freindly Robot                 One day a scientist named professor Jillan  Hawk was working on a robot that can do peoples chores.  One day Jillan was finished with his robot.  It was a success,he won a ton of money.  Everyone wanted to be him.  He had his own robot and a penthouse.  One night  Jillan said that if only his creation was alive.  Lucky for him right when he said that a shooting stars based by.  The next morning Jillan woke up from a noise.  It was his robot making breakfast for him.  The robot said,'Good morning master'.  Jillan was shocked he yelled out,'How are you alive'!  The robot said that when you wished for me to be alive the wish came true.  Jillan didn't feel so scared any more after the robot explained why he was alive.           Jillan said that we should give you a name.  The robot said that he always wanted to be named Carl.  Jillan said,'Ok i will name you Carl.  Jillan said that now that your alive what kind of things can you do.  Carl said that I can drive a car, make food, and do your chores.Jillan was so happy that day.            The next day Jillan went to work and Carl stayed home. Carl did all the chores made lunch and drove Jillan's car to get it   washed.When Jillan came he home he was shocked everything was clean.  Carl said if is everything ok master.Jillan said nothing and went to Carl and hugged him and said thank you.Carl hugged him back.          The next day Jillan said to carl,'Your coming to work with me'.  When Jillan and Carl arived everybody stared at him.  Jillan said to ignore them.  When they went in to a meeting Jillan's boss was amazed.He said that he never seen nothing like it.Carl said if he was talking to him. The boss said yes.  the boss man said,'How much do you want for him.  Jillan said that he's not for sale. The boss man got Carl by the hand and took him,but Jillan just in time stoped him and ran out the door with Carl. The boss man was chasing after him. Jillan and Carl ran out the door. Item_Response: THE ROBOT THAT CAME ALIVE                    Once upon a time there was a  seventeen year old girl named Bella. She was kind and sweet and loved just about everything. She had maids and servants to take care of her every  need. She was always very greatful every one of them. Athough it seemed that she had a wonderful life she didnt. Her father died when she was just a little girl and had been taken care of what her fathers money bought her. Ever since the tragedy she has wished on a star that something would come alive , so she could talk to her father.                 It was a clear day in Forks , no big news had come in ,just another simple day for her. Which is usually school and hanging out  with her friend Kayla. Bella was outside during lunch , having her usual chicken sandwhich. When all of a sudden little can fell from the sky. Bella with much curiosity picked it up and headed home.                 When she got home Silvia one her maids asked her , ' what do you havethere Bella.'   'o nothing ', and as fast as she could she raced upstairs . She was so curious of what it was , but had so much school work to do. So  she decided to do her work and then she would see what it was. In about two hours of homework she was getting  really tired. then decided to wait till tomorrow to investigate it . Bella  then started to pray that a blessing would help her communicate with her father. Then when she finally fell asleep the can came alive.                  After a long night of rest she woke up.Then all of a sudden heard a  CLANK. It startled her so much she jumped right out of bed to see what it was. She looked carefully into the closet and saw the live can. AHH she screamed . Then as soon as possible came a maid and said,' are you ok ?'. Bella murmured ,' the closet.' She looked into the closet and saw nothing. 'o bella it's nothing.'                  After the maid left she looked into the closet and shouted ,' there it is .', but nobody came. But the robot still remained. Bella said ,' are you gonna hurt me ?' no it replied.Then why are you here bella said in a scared way.To help you co mmunicate with your father.                   Bella time to go to school.She ate breakfast and  then she went . At school she was so eager to get home. She did'nt even touch her lunch and after her classes she rushed home.                  Could this be true? Can you communicate with him right now.   . Yes it said. Then is amazment it stared to communicate .And she heard he father! They talked for hours and hours. Then ended. She was still shocked  that that that was her father . In all of these years she never thought she could comminicate with her father ever again, but then came along a little can from heaven.

Item_Response: It was 1:00  in the morning. Thunder struck in the city of  New York. A boy named Marty had a science project due in two weeks. He stood up all night just thinking what he was going to do. The topic was science fiction and he was frustrated because he was more into history. Marty decided to go to sleep just hoping that an idea will come to mind when he wakes up with the sun rising. It was Sunday and Marty decided to take a walk in Times Square. He promised his mom that he would be home by 7:00 for dinner. He stopped by Mr.Bill's Candy Shop because he was really into sugar. He bought three sour punch straws, four tootsie rolls and eight mini lollipops. He walked by the Empire State Building admiring the sky scraper when a brilliant idea came to mind!                                                                                                 He was going to create a robot that looked exactly like a dinosaur because he was also really into dinosaurs, but the big question is how will he do it. He knew the idea was bizarre, but he thought he could do it. He looked at his watch and it was 7:13! He quickly got into the first bus he could see and gave the bus driver his home address. The bus driver demanded 50 cents but Marty forgot that he spent all of his money on the candy! Instead, he gave the bus driver 4 mini lollipops and the bus driver accepted it. By the time he got home his mother and his four older siblings (all sisters) were eating on the table. His mother or sisters didn't mind that he was late. Since they were in a happy mood, Marty told them all about his project. They were actually surprised that he was tempting to do that. Suddenly his dad came really excited. He said that he won the lottery for 17.5 million dollars! All you could here in the house is 'we're rich, we're rich, we're rich!' It was the happiest day of their lives.                  The next day, Marty got started on building his dinosaur robot. Four hours later, he got too frustrated and smashed everything on the floor. He was making really good progress, but it probably wasn't the project he wanted. He got his raincoat and took another walk through Times Square really mad. It was raining harder than ever before in the history of New York! Suddenly, he didn't know where he was. He ran through the aisles of New York really scared. He bumped into something hard and tripped. He saw that it was the size of a microwave but it had more details. It looked almost like a robot! He was about to touch it when suddenly, he saw that thunder struck the microwave-shaped item. He was scared than ever before. He started running when the microwave-shaped item started chasing him. It looked like it had wheels, but then it got up on its legs and also started running. Marty had fainted scared out of his mind!                    It was Monday morning and it was a school day. Marty woke up with the living robot on his chest. He also saw his dad (a police officer) slapping his face. He suddenly screamed out of his mind. His dad covered his mouth because there was reporters shoving microphones in his face. He saw CNN, ABC News, and also HLN! They were all his favorite news channels. He almost forgot about the robot. He screamed again with his dad covering his mouth again. His dad took him home to explain what happened last night with the robot listening. He explained everything even the robot. His dad said that he is not going to school because then those reporters will get in his face again. Marty accepted his rules and didn't go to school until next week.                   Saturday was coming and Marty was excited! He really felt great about how cool his life is. He was rich, he was famous and on top of that, he had his project due for Thursday! The only problem was that he didn't know how he was going to present his robot. He called his robot MJ2 which means Marty Junior the second. He was staring at his robot and the robot was staring at him. He told the robot to speak and so the robot said ''Marty.' Marty was really shocked! He told the robot to do tricks and so the robot was flying higher than Marty! The robot can also act like a human, sing and walk! Marty knew that he was gonna get a A++++++++++++++. He couldn't hold himself so he just waited until Thursday to present his project.                    It was Thursday, and Marty was ready to present his project. When he arrived in school, the MJ2 was walking right behind him. Students were asking questions like 'how did you make that?'' or girls were saying comments like ' you guys look so cute together!' Marty was the party of the school! Other students created projects like statues of aliens or pretending to dissect a frog. Marty was the last in line to present his project. He was excited, but also nervous. He didn't know what to say, but he remembered what MJ2 can say, 'Marty.' He was too sure of himself that he would get more than a A+. Forty minutes passed and it was Marty's turn to present his project. Marty presented his project by telling the MJ2 to stand up, fly and say his name. He also said a speech about it. One of his lines were I didn't come to the MJ2, the MJ2 came to me. Everybody gave him a good round of applause because Marty's project was so great, and Marty also got a A++.                      Twenty Five years passed and Marty was all grown up. He had a nice family, and he works for the C.I.A. Marty creates more robots and a lot of spy equipment. The MJ2 still lives better than ever. He got new upgrades like laser eyes and a better body. Marty never forgot the day he got an A++. Marty is 37 years old. He has two kids and a wife. His kids names are Marty Robinson and Maple Robinson. His wife's name is also Maple Robinson. Marty is a billionaire and also one of the richest men in the world. His four sisters are superstars in hip-hop. His mom and dad own the Empire State Building now. People offered more than a billion dollars for the MJ2. Marty always ignored them because he thought about something. He didn't come to the MJ2, the MJ2 came to him!

Item_Response: Tick-tick..program 101 secured, program 102 all set. 'Whew, we finally created the perfect robot,' said scientist Ziggs. 'We created him with everything anyone could wish for.' 'It has the power of a Mr. Gower, carrying things up to 500 pounds.' 'It has the intelligence of the Gemini-Scout, being able to collect information anywhere.' 'It also has the playfulness of the HRP-4c, singing and dancing when asked to.' 'I will finally boot up this robot, and show its glory to the world!' yelled Ziggs. However, the robot suddenly emits pulsing waves throughout the lab, shattering vials of chemicals. The robot comes to life, and Ziggs didn't even touch it yet. The robot takes a moment to look at Ziggs, then tackles through the lab's walls, making a thundering sound and vanishing with the wind. Ziggs remains baffled, curious to what made the robot suddenly come to life...                  The robot appears in a friendly town, not knowing where it is. The robot seems to be in the shape of a little boy, featuring all the components of one. The robot decides to learn where he is, and who he is. He names himself Tim, and goes on to a sidewalk. It seems that Ziggs implanted emotional circuits into Tim, making him have emotions. While walking along the sidewalk, Tim comes across a girl named Annie, who is looking for her teddy bear named Tibbers. Tim finds Tibbers in a bush, and gives it to Annie. Annie thanks Tim, and invites him into her house. Tim asks very many questions, and learns this neighborhood is called Valoran. The country it is in is Demacia, a shining country who rules with peace. Tim meets the parents of Annie, and they greet him. The parents ask, 'Where are your parents? Do they live around here?' Tim tells them that he doesn't have a mother, but he is a robot with emotions. The parents gasp, feeling sorry for him. Tim quietly cries to himself, feeling sorry too. The parents ask, 'Would you like to live with us' Tim immediatly replies, 'Yes, I would love too!' After a few days, Tim enrolls into Annie's class, being brother and sister. Tim makes new friends, and loves it at Annie's house. Ziggs on the other hand, is still confused of all the events that happened. Ziggs only knows he has to clean up this mess, all by himself. Ziggs then says to himself, 'Well, I may have only known that robot for a long time, but he is quite the troublemaker...' Tim makes his way home with Annie, and he lives quite happily for the rest of his life.                                                                             ~THE END~

Item_Response: It all started in sixth grade when we went on our field trip. We were going to the farm. I was so excited to see all the animals and finally see the Agribot robot!                       As we got off the buss the sun was really bright. The farmer greeted us with a big smile. He said, 'Hello kids, who's ready for a tour of the farm?' Everybody said, 'Me!' He gave us a tour of the animals and pond, but then he showed me the most amazing thing i had ever seen! The Agribot robot! It was picking fruits and putting them in a basket, but that s all i saw because when i walked over to take a second look the farmer said we must go. I knew I had to see it again!                  It was about one o'clock and we had already eaten lunch. The tour was over, and all the kids were asking the farmer lots of questions. So I sneaked of to look at the Agribot. I walked to tree that the Agribot was at. 'Hello.', I said to myself. And guess what! It said hello back. I was stunned.  And then he talked again. 'What's your name?' it said. 'Joey', I said back. 'My name is Buster, how may I help you?' he said. I almost dropped dead! 'You, you,you can talk?' I said shakily. 'Why yes, all robots can talk.', said Buster.                             Once I got used to Buster talking to me, he was actually really cool! We talked about all the different kinds of robots and how they worked. He also talked about how he was on a secret mission to save planet Earth. He told me that aliens portray to be evil and take over Earth in books and movies, but some are actually nice creatures. Buster said I couldn't tell anyone about his secret, and I swore. To be honest , I was a little scared! Bad aliens from Jupiter were trying to destroy Earth, so him and his alien buddies were saving Earth by working to help farmers and doctors, but fighting crime at night.                        I was a little freaked out when everything was over with. Who wouldn't be though? Honestly I didn't know if I was imagining all this or if it were real. Finally I realized it was time to go back before the bus left. 'Good by Buster it was really nice meeting you.', I said. 'Nice meeting you too.', Buster said. I told him good luck on him mission and that if he was ever in town again, call me. Buster was a really cool robot.                       When I got back to the lunch site it was time to go. I said thank you to the farmer for having me at his farm, but he didn't really say anything. That day was probably the most interesting day of my life! I mean who else has met a good robot that was on a secret mission to save Earth from evil aliens? No one I know. I never told anybody about that day, and don't plan on it. People will just think I am crazy. So if you ever meet an robot named Buster that's on a secret mission trying to save Earth from evil aliens, tell him his friend Joey said hi.

Item_Response: Phil walked to school in a cold winter day feeling a little annoyed and tiered of school, but it wasn't really a choice he knew he had to go because if his mom found out he ditched school he would be in big trouble. So he continued to walk down on the side walk and finally when it seemed forever he reached his junior high and went to his first period class. When he entered math (first period) he flopped down on his seat right in the back of the class. Mrs.Quinn smiled and cleared her through'hello and good morning class. I hope you all did last nights work.' Phil shrugged and sighed of boredom he could already tell it was going to be a long day. After about 30-40 minutes the bell rang to go to second period. With an other long sigh Phil stod up and gathered all his things and shoved them into his backpack. Befor he could leave Mrs.Quinn called him over to the front of the class. 'Phil may i please have a word with you?' Phil walked over a little scared thinking he had done something wrong or bad. With a small smile Mrs.Quinn gave to phil she said 'i would like to give you something.' she went to the back of the room and came back with a small box and handed it to Phil 'here open it when you get home.' Phil faked a smile 'thanks i guess...well i gotta go to second period bye Mrs.Quinn.' when Phil got home he went up to his room and took out the small box from his backpack. 'hmm i wonder why its so small. It might have a pencil in it or somethig.'he opened it and saw a tiny robot in side. 'wow who needs this for?!' he tosed it a side and it moved he jumped and got a little closer to pick it up. the robot stod up and befor it did anything else Phil picked it up and put it back in the box. 'why would Mrs.Quinn give me this?' he thought to himself. The next day when he got to school he took the box with the robot inside of it and put it on Mrs.Quinn's desk.

Item_Response: Who Knew                   Synthia stood clueless of what Dr.Ed was even   saying. She was an A+ student and he didn't make sense to her. She replied to the crazy scientist, 'Forget it Ed, you can't make a machine that walks and talks, it's not possible.       'Oh Synthia, why don't you understand? I'm Dr.Ed, I can and will do anything and everything.!' I'll show her one day, I'm gonna build a robot! , Ed thought.Synthia just ignored him and walked to her things.       'I have to go now Dr.Ed. I'll be back tomorrow.'Synthia grabbed her things and placed them neatly in her bag.She began walked out when Dr.Ed replied, 'But it's the weekend tomorrow, don't you ever have fun?' 'Dad, I don't have stuff to do on the weekend. Plus, even you are more fun than listening to mom howl her weekend song.' Synthia walked out leaving her father, Ed , with a smile on his face.       Synthia's parents divorced when she was young. Leaving the young blonde to wonder.                                 3 weeks later           The machine lay on Ed's lab table. Nobody was there, But then...    a clatter of metal stuck the floor. The robot was actually alive!   It opened the door and left the lab.           Synthia walked the streets and saw people running. What in the world? Synthia wondered. She saw a robot... HER FATHERS ROBOT! She ran to her fathers, yanked him out of bed and yelled, 'THE ROBOTS ALIVE YOU HAVE TO WAKE UP!!!!' Together they ran to the scene. 'How do we... catch it?' Synthia asked. 'RUN FOR IT!' they ran and caught the robot.           'Dad, I cant believe you brought it to life!' Synthia hugged her father. 'To the lab Dr.Ed?' 'To the lab Miss.Peirce.'

Item_Response: It is Los Angeles in the year 2079. Down by the bad part of town with  gangs and all that, well that's were I'm from. My name is Cornelius and I'm fourteen years old and I'm going to tell you a story of how a got a job at the most expensive companies in the world. it started when I was twelve. I was living in the dirtiest place you could think of. But, one day some people from the s.o.s.a.s. or school of space age science came and did whats called a swep in this place and find kids that have at lest some brains and take a test and if they pass they get a job at the s.o.s.a.s. when hey are old enough.so when they came by this really nice lady looked at me for one moment and sprayed me with a hose! then they grabbed me and I was out of there. Finally! In the van there are about nine kids and I'm the youngest here.When we get there the build was huge! It was maybe a hundred and fivety floors.When we got out and inside the same lady that sprayed me came up and said,'hello, I am Emily Night and I run the robotics division here. Today you will take a test and if you pass you just may get a job here.'   'You have robots?'   'Yes, and if you are good I might show you.'   So  off we went up to the 85th floor  and into a test room. But, before I sat down that girl Emily took me out of the room and said 'How you doing?'   'Still a little wet.' I said.   'Well sorry about that but you need to look 5% decent,what's your name?'   I paused for a sec to get my thoughts strait.   'C-Cornelius.' I said.   'Welcome to the s.o.s.a.s.   'but I have not even taken the test yet!'   'Your smart, figure it out.'   a few minutes later I was in the lab with m new best friend Steve. he is six feet tall and is a robot. In the nextthree weeks I had learned how to make robots program them and teach Steve how to play soccer!

Item_Response: There was once a robot that was destroyed and was buried in the crust of the Earth 10,000,000 years ago. After that much years, the robot somehow got brought back to life and started drilling up. The robot finally got out and enjoyed the sun light. The robot enjoyed until a grandpa decided to shoot him with a rocket launcher because the robot looked creepy. It was rusted to the max, had a broken eye,his head was sticking out, and had very old oil dripping. The robot exploded and quickly reformed itself adding a bunch of other new metal materials such as steel, iron, and titanium. The robot looked brand new but right after that, it fell over and wasn't alive anymore. The grandpa left and a boy came and picked it up.           The boy brought it home and played with it until he saw a place that said,' Shine Sunlight Here!' Out of curiosity, the boy did it. The robot instantly came to life. Apprently the boy didn't have a family and was an orphan. The robot saw that and was sad. The robot figured out he was bigger than the boy and had an opening and had a space inside him for the boy to live in. The robot left,stole a carpet, clothes, game systems, games, and equiped a thing that can make any food, and a tiny hospital. The robot came back and said,' Live in me,' so the boy went inside. The robot basically became his parent until he wasd an adult. The robot was sad to see the boy go away. The boy was thinking for a second and he let the robot follow him.              50 years later the 'boy' died an the robot was losing power for some reason. The next day the robot shut down and the dead boy was in him. 1,000,000 years later, of course the boy shattered into dust, some miners found the robot.The miners observed thr robot.After a while, they saw a sign that said,'Shine Sunlight Here!', and it broke into thosands of pieces but the head.

Item_Response: ' We did it!!!!' I exclaimed as we made our first robots eye's open up. We finally did it. ' If only we could get it to sit up now.' my partner says. 'We mustn't tell anybody in town until we can at least get it to stand up properly.' I said. We were in our laboratory in our small town in the year 2060. we were the first scientists to figure out how to make a robot come alive and talk. Well, we haven't quite gotten to the talking part, but in the very near future we will be there.       We were trying to get a robot that will help people with special needs. This was a hopeful statement considering our robot can't even stand up. 'Well maybe we should just call it a day' I said sadly. We walked out of our laboratory, which is just a basement of an old building nobody uses anymore, when we heard a great crashing sound. We ran as fast as we could to see what had happened. When we got there all of our chemicals had fallen on top of our robot who had closed its eye's. After we had cleaned our floor, we realized the robot had disappeared. We had to search all over the basement when we saw the door propped open. We ran up the steps two stairs at a time hoping to catch the robot before it made its grand escape to downtown.           We caught the robot quickly because it had barely made it passed the hallway. It had died down before it got to the main entrance. It was then that we realized the chemicals were the reason our robot had woken up and had started to work. We then went back to work on getting more of those chemicals that we had had in our laboratory. we were going to see if this really was the case of our robot mysteriously coming to life.           The next day we got back to work early in the morning. We had all the supplies ready to go so we set to work.First we propped up the robot, then we mixed all of the chemicals, then we poured the mixture all over the robot. At first it didn't work, but then somehow, someway it opened it's eyes and said hello to us. At first I was a little freaked out, but then I thought that it's only a robot.           After a few days we had to get more chemicals. I then realized we need to figure out a way to not have the chemicals wear off.I then thought of trying to only mix certain chemicals together.' I finally got the perfect mixture' I said to myself. We tried it out and sure enough it turned out perfect. We then made our robot public. It brought so much attention to our small town. This robot then went to the hospital to help perform surgeries on patients. These surgeries were special though. They were surgeries to help blind people get their eyesight back,  deaf people get their hearing back, and  paralyzed people get the feelings back in their bodies. This robot helped to save millions of lives. She even helped save my live after I was in an explosion in my very own laboratory. I then thought of the perfect name for my robot.       Hero.           My buddy and I then decided to make many more robots. None quite as special as Hero. Hero is still in the hospitals today, but nowhere near me. This is because she is needed where more people are injured. Robots are a mans, or woman's, best friend! This is a story of how robots came to save many lives of humans and including my own. I now hope you love robots as much as myself. Maybe someday you'll get to see Hero my best friend and life-saver.
